research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0014.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current best family may need cleaner support suppression rather than another additive or multiplicative residual path. An adaptive-threshold TopK encoder that keeps the proven linear logits as the anchor but learns an input-dependent nonnegative per-latent suppression term could reduce false activations at K=128 and materially improve FVU without abandoning the strong baseline initialization.","summary":"The gated probe was a clear regression, so this round moves to a new architecture edit instead of more parameter-only tuning on weak recent families. The new `adaptive_threshold_topk` family starts exactly from plain TopK behavior and only learns to suppress linear logits, making it a focused quality-first prototype to test at the K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor under proxy.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"adaptive_threshold_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent architectural bet grounded in the strongest observed prior: keeping the linear TopK path intact. The main risk is that suppression-only flexibility may still be too weak to beat hybrid_topk, but it is safer and more targeted than the recent families that replaced or loosely mixed the baseline encoder.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"adaptive_threshold_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/adaptive_threshold_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 14 adds a new adaptive_threshold_topk family that preserves the plain linear TopK encoder at initialization and learns only input-dependent nonnegative suppression of latent logits.","A quick local import/forward sanity check passed for adaptive_threshold_topk before handing control back to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If adaptive_threshold_topk shows a strong proxy gain, promote it to full as the next mainline quality candidate.","If adaptive_threshold_topk is flat or weak, the next round should bias toward a more expressive new architecture or a hybrid-family training-dynamics experiment rather than revisiting gated or jumprelu local sweeps."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0007.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A hybrid encoder that preserves the strong linear topk path and adds a gated nonlinear residual to latent logits can improve quality without discarding the baseline behavior that already works. Test a new hybrid_topk family at K=128 as a quality-first architecture probe.","summary":"factorized_topk improved from its worst prototype but is still far from the K=128 anchor, and the current built-in families are not showing a path to the target. This round opens a new family designed to be safer than pure nonlinear encoders by keeping the baseline linear path intact and only learning a nonlinear correction on top.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a broader architecture move, but it is still a single coherent bet: combine the proven linear encoder with a nonlinear residual branch instead of replacing it. The new family adds compute, so even a promising quality signal would need later cost validation.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/hybrid_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The fixed factorized_topk stabilization improved proxy FVU from 0.4431915953755379 to 0.3485000617802143 without runtime regression, but it remains far from the K=128 topk anchor.","Round 7 opens hybrid_topk, a new family that keeps the baseline linear topk encoder and adds a gated nonlinear residual to latent logits rather than replacing the linear path outright."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk shows a clear proxy gain, follow with a stabilization pass on optimizer or nonlinear branch width before promotion.","If hybrid_topk is also flat or worse, pause family proliferation and reconsider whether quality gains are more likely to come from topk-mainline training dynamics than from encoder architecture alone."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0018.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent architecture edits have mostly tried to improve support selection, yet multiple distinct families have converged to the same proxy FVU plateau under normal runtime. A stronger next bet is that support is not the main bottleneck at K=128; instead, the selected coefficients are too crude. A refined_topk family that keeps the proven linear top-k support but recomputes the chosen coefficients with a small per-example ridge solve against the decoder atoms could materially lower FVU by directly reducing reconstruction error on the selected support.","summary":"Pivot away from branch-union follow-ups and add a new refined_topk family. It preserves the baseline linear top-k proposal, but replaces the final coefficients with a ridge-refined fit on the chosen decoder features, targeting reconstruction quality directly rather than adding more routing machinery. This is a single proxy prototype for a more radical quality-first hypothesis at the K=128 anchor.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"refined_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a coherent architecture pivot after two flat union_topk rounds under normal runtime. The main risk is that the per-example solve may add overhead or overfit weak supports, but it tests a meaningfully different failure hypothesis than the recent support-selection families and keeps the launcher interface unchanged.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"refined_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/refined_topk_sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/config.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/sparse_coder.py","/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/__init__.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 18 adds a new refined_topk family that keeps the baseline linear top-k support but refits the selected coefficients with a small ridge solve against the decoder atoms.","The refined_topk implementation uses a straight-through blend so the forward path uses refined coefficients while preserving gradient flow through the baseline top-k activations.","A local import/forward/backward sanity check passed for refined_topk before handing control back to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If refined_topk materially improves proxy FVU, follow with a family-specific stabilization pass on the coefficient refinement strength or support source before considering promotion.","If refined_topk is flat or regresses under normal runtime, that is evidence that coefficient refitting alone is not enough and the next round should pivot to a genuinely different encoder family rather than more top-k refinements."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0002.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A soft mixture-of-experts encoder may beat the current K=128 topk anchor by giving the encoder more routing expressivity without the hard-capacity bottlenecks of grouped routing. Test the existing mixture_topk family at the same K=128 and expansion factor as a quality-first proxy comparison.","summary":"The K=128 topk full baseline is now anchored at FVU 0.1853. The next round should probe a more expressive encoder family at the same K rather than shrinking K or spending another round on local topk tuning.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"mixture_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the right point to open architecture exploration, but it is still a first incubation pass, so the result may be noisy or need follow-up tuning before judging the family. I kept the rest of the setup close to the anchor to preserve interpretability.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"mixture_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Established full K=128 topk anchor is FVU 0.18532327562570572; future lower-K or cost-driven moves should clear that quality bar first.","Round 2 opens the first new architecture family by testing mixture_topk as a quality-first encoder at the same K=128 anchor point."],"next_hypotheses":["If mixture_topk shows even modest proxy FVU gain, follow with a stabilization pass on optimizer or expansion factor before judging promotion.","If mixture_topk is flat or worse under normal runtime, try another expressive family such as residual_topk or factorized_topk at the same K=128 anchor."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0010.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"hybrid_topk may now be limited by using the nonlinear branch only as an additive correction; letting it multiplicatively modulate the linear logits should improve support shaping while preserving the strong baseline path. Re-test hybrid_topk at the best-known K=128, expansion_factor=8, optimizer=adam setting after this targeted hybrid-family stabilization edit.","summary":"The expansion_factor=16 follow-up did not improve full FVU and cost substantial throughput, so the next move should be a targeted architecture refinement rather than more brute-force scaling. This round keeps the winning hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 setup and upgrades the nonlinear branch to modulate linear logits as well as add residual logits.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a narrow, defensible follow-up on the current best family and it directly addresses the likely limit of the present hybrid design without reopening the broader search space. It still adds encoder complexity, so any quality gain will need later cost scrutiny against the ef=8 Adam mainline.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/hybrid_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["hybrid_topk with Adam and expansion_factor=16 achieved better proxy FVU but slightly worse full FVU (0.1623645443469286 vs 0.16189537942409515) and a clear throughput regression, so brute-force scaling is not the next priority.","Round 10 stabilizes hybrid_topk by adding a zero-initialized multiplicative modulation path on top of the existing additive nonlinear residual, keeping the model anchored to the proven linear encoder at initialization."],"next_hypotheses":["If the modulated hybrid_topk improves proxy FVU, promote it to full as the next mainline quality candidate.","If the modulated hybrid_topk is flat or worse, keep the current hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 checkpoint as mainline and revisit training dynamics or a genuinely new family instead of more local hybrid edits."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0005.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"factorized_topk likely failed because its hidden mixer is too narrow and lossy; widening that stage and adding a gate should preserve more information before latent selection and materially improve FVU. Re-test factorized_topk at K=128 after this single architectural stabilization edit.","summary":"The first factorized_topk prototype was much worse than the anchor, but its implementation used a plain hidden layer with width equal to d_in, which is a likely bottleneck rather than a decisive family verdict. This round keeps the same family and K while upgrading the encoder to a wider gated mixer.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a coherent follow-up on the only family that produced a strongly different signal, and it targets an obvious implementation bottleneck instead of abandoning the branch too early. The edit increases encoder compute, so even a quality gain still needs later cost scrutiny.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The original factorized_topk prototype likely suffered from an overly narrow d_in-sized hidden bottleneck rather than only a bad family prior.","Round 5 stabilizes factorized_topk by replacing the narrow ReLU mixer with a wider gated hidden stage before latent projection."],"next_hypotheses":["If the stabilized factorized_topk proxy improves substantially, consider promotion or a follow-up quality pass with optimizer tuning.","If the stabilized factorized_topk remains poor under normal runtime, deprioritize the current built-in families and move to a genuinely new encoder family rather than more local tuning."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0001.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Because the frontier is empty, the next highest-value move is to establish a trustworthy K=128 quality anchor with the simplest mainline architecture before rewarding smaller K or drawing conclusions about new families. Run a proxy topk baseline at K=128 with the default expansion and optimizer explicitly pinned so later rounds can measure real FVU gains against a stable reference.","summary":"No reliable K=128 anchor exists in memory yet. This round should spend one proxy run on an explicitly pinned mainline topk baseline so subsequent architecture work can target material FVU improvement rather than comparing against an implicit or drifting default.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is intentionally conservative, but the memory is empty and the primary objective depends on having a trustworthy K=128 reference. I avoided architecture edits because there is not yet enough evidence to justify a new family over first establishing the anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 0 starts with empty frontier and no trustworthy K=128 anchor, so anchor establishment takes priority over lower-K comparisons.","Treat this run as the baseline reference point for future aggressive FVU-improvement bets."],"next_hypotheses":["If this anchor is stable, escalate immediately to a higher-capacity or more expressive encoder family that could materially beat its FVU at the same K=128.","If the anchor quality is already much better than expected, then test quality-first upgrades such as mixture/factorized/residual encoders before considering smaller K."]}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0013.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A gated SAE may materially lower proxy FVU at K=128 by decoupling support selection from coefficient magnitude, letting one branch learn which features should fire while another learns how strongly they should reconstruct. After two flat jumprelu stabilization rounds and stalled hybrid local search, this is the cleanest untried quality-first family already supported by the execution layer.","summary":"JumpReLU did not produce a meaningful stabilization gain, and recent local tuning around the current hybrid mainline has not closed the quality gap. This round shifts to a new existing architecture family with a distinct encoder bias: independent gating and magnitude branches at the same K=128/ef=8/Adam anchor, evaluated first as a proxy quality probe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single coherent family exploration, not another weak local sweep. The main risk is that sigmoid-gated selection could saturate and undertrain, but the architectural change is clean, already implemented, and directly targets support quality rather than cost.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 13 opens the previously untested gated family as a quality-first K=128 proxy probe after jumprelu threshold tuning remained flat around 0.275 proxy FVU.","The gated architecture decouples latent support selection from activation magnitude, which is a substantively different encoder bias from hybrid additive correction and jumprelu thresholding."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated shows a strong proxy signal, promote it to full before returning to smaller-K or cost work.","If gated is also weak, bias the next round toward another genuinely different encoder family or a code edit for a new architecture rather than more parameter-only tuning on recent families."]}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The stabilized gated regime has now improved both K=128 and K=64, so the next clean Pareto probe is to test whether that same family extends to K=32 and can displace the older JumpReLU low-K point. A gated K=32 proxy run under the same validated settings will show whether the current best family can dominate more of the frontier rather than remaining a high-K-only solution.","summary":"Run the stabilized gated configuration in proxy at K=32 with AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 to test whether the improved gated family can replace the current JumpReLU K=32 Pareto point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"pareto","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the search on the strongest validated family and changes only K, which gives a clean low-K comparison against the existing frontier. The main risk is that gated may degrade too sharply at K=32, but that outcome is still useful for defining the family’s viable sparsity range.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"32"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated family now holds the best full results at both K=128 and K=64 under the stabilized AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 regime.","This round tests whether the same gated regime can also improve the K=32 Pareto point, potentially unifying the frontier under one family.","Using the same architecture, optimizer, learning rate, and expansion factor isolates K as the only changed variable for a direct comparison with the existing JumpReLU K=32 result."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated K=32 proxy is clearly better than the current JumpReLU K=32 point, promote it to full and treat gated as the new mainline family across the tested K range.","If gated K=32 is close but not clearly better, test whether reducing expansion factor improves the low-K tradeoff within the gated family.","If gated K=32 is substantially worse, keep gated focused on K>=64 and resume architecture exploration specifically for the ultra-low-K regime."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0037.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Now that gated holds the full frontier at K=128, K=64, and K=32, the next informative move is to test whether the low-K regime is over-capacitated rather than quality-limited. Reducing gated expansion_factor from 16 to 8 at K=32 may preserve most of the newly won quality while improving cost signals and possibly sharpening feature competition enough to strengthen the Pareto tradeoff.","summary":"Run a proxy gated K=32 stabilization pass with AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 and EXPANSION_FACTOR=8 to test for a better low-K cost-quality tradeoff.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"pareto","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the search on the strongest validated family and changes only expansion factor, which is the cleanest next family-specific axis after gated swept the tested K values. The main risk is a quality drop from reduced capacity, but the K=32 regime is the most plausible place for over-capacity to be hurting efficiency rather than helping reconstruction.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"32"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated family now owns the full frontier across K=128, K=64, and K=32 under AUXK_ALPHA=0.01, so follow-up should shift from architecture replacement to family-specific tradeoff shaping.","This round probes whether the new gated K=32 point is over-capacitated at EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 and can be improved or made cheaper by reducing latent width.","Keeping architecture, optimizer, learning rate, AUXK_ALPHA, and K fixed isolates expansion factor as the only changed variable for a clean low-K cost-quality comparison."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated K=32 with EXPANSION_FACTOR=8 maintains similar quality with better runtime or memory, treat it as the preferred low-K Pareto point and consider the same capacity reduction at K=64.","If EXPANSION_FACTOR=8 improves K=32 proxy FVU outright, promote it to full and treat the earlier EF=16 setting as unnecessarily wide for the ultra-low-K regime.","If EXPANSION_FACTOR=8 degrades K=32 substantially, keep EF=16 as the low-K gated default and test a different family only if new architecture exploration becomes necessary again."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0017.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The union_topk prototype likely failed because its nonlinear branch proposed candidates from the same centered input as the linear branch, so it mostly duplicated baseline support. Conditioning the nonlinear proposer on the linear branch residual, widening that branch, and letting it over-propose candidates before the final global top-k should increase support complementarity at K=128 and lower proxy FVU.","summary":"Stabilize the new union_topk family with a complementary-proposal encoder: the linear path still anchors selection, but the nonlinear branch now reads the linear residual and can surface extra candidates that the baseline top-k misses. This is a single quality-first proxy follow-up on the most recent new family, rather than another local sweep on hybrid_topk.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"union_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within one coherent family hypothesis and directly targets the main weakness of the round-16 prototype: redundant candidate proposals. The main risk is that proxy training may still be too short for the wider residual-conditioned branch to separate from the linear anchor, but this is a more informative family-specific follow-up than pivoting away after one near-baseline prototype.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"union_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/union_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 17 stabilizes union_topk by making the nonlinear proposal branch residual-conditioned on the linear partial reconstruction instead of reading the same centered input.","The union_topk stabilization also widens the nonlinear branch and lets it over-propose 2k candidates before the final global top-k, aiming to improve candidate diversity without changing decode semantics.","A local import/forward/backward sanity check passed for the edited union_topk implementation before handing control back to the runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If residual-conditioned union_topk materially improves proxy FVU, promote this family toward mainline comparison and consider a full run.","If it remains near the recent 0.275 proxy plateau under normal runtime, pivot away from branch-union variants to a more radical encoder family rather than spending more rounds on local union_topk tuning."]}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0068.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` did not fail on quality grounds; it failed because the execution layer still rejects the architecture name before training starts. The smallest informative move is a narrow code-fix round inside `sparsify/` that registers and wires `lowrank_residual` into config validation and SAE class dispatch so the intended K=128 proxy prototype can finally produce a real signal.","summary":"Register and implement the `lowrank_residual` architecture in `sparsify/`, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the blocker-first guidance by fixing the concrete architecture-selection failure instead of drawing conclusions from a non-run. The main risk is that additional compatibility issues appear after registration, but clearing the explicit selection gate is still the correct next step and keeps the architecture hypothesis intact.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 67 produced a concrete architecture-registration blocker for `lowrank_residual`: the runtime still rejects the architecture name in config validation before training begins.","This is stronger evidence of incomplete code integration than of a bad architecture, so `lowrank_residual` still has no usable quality signal.","The next round should keep the original `lowrank_residual` K=128 proxy target fixed and change only the code needed to make the family selectable and runnable by the existing launcher."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` runs and shows competitive proxy FVU, keep the family alive and stabilize its trunk width next.","If it runs cleanly but is clearly worse than gated and not better than prior archived families, archive it quickly and move to another genuinely new family.","If it still fails after registration and dispatch are fixed, treat the remaining issue as a deeper implementation incompatibility and shift effort elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0049.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`factorized_topk` has now failed for a concrete architecture-registration reason rather than an ambiguous quality or runtime signal: the execution layer rejects the architecture name in `SparseCoderConfig` before training begins. The next coherent move is a narrow code-fix round that wires `factorized_topk` into the existing config/class registry and forward path so the prototype can finally receive one real K=128 proxy measurement under the strongest current regime.","summary":"Register and enable the `factorized_topk` architecture in `sparsify/`, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the smallest defensible next step because the latest failure is an explicit compatibility bug, not a quality result, and continuing to retry without fixing registration would waste rounds. The main risk is that the family still underperforms once it runs, but one valid proxy result is required before deciding whether to stabilize or retire it.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 48 produced a concrete execution-layer error for `factorized_topk`: the architecture name is not registered in `SparseCoderConfig`, so the family still has no usable quality signal.","This is stronger evidence of a missing code integration step than of a bad architecture, so the family should not be retired on quality grounds yet.","This round keeps the original `factorized_topk` K=128 proxy target fixed and changes only the code needed to make the architecture selectable and runnable by the existing launcher."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registered `factorized_topk` run completes and beats plain `topk`, keep the family alive and begin stabilizing its internal factorization design.","If the run completes normally but remains far behind gated, retire shallow factorization and move to a different encoder-expressivity direction.","If `factorized_topk` still fails after registration is fixed, treat the remaining issue as a deeper implementation incompatibility and shift effort elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The stabilized factorized_topk crash was caused by an implementation bug in the widened hidden-path projection, not by the architecture itself. Fix the hidden-to-latent projection and rerun the same K=128 factorized_topk stabilization pass to recover a valid quality signal.","summary":"Round 5 produced a shape-mismatch crash inside factorized_topk after the widening edit, so the next move is a direct bug-fix rerun rather than abandoning the family. This keeps the hypothesis narrow: validate the intended wider gated factorized encoder before making any new architectural decision.","change_type":"edit_architecture","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the correct response to the last round because the failure was a concrete code bug, not a training-quality outcome. The rerun is still only worth one more round; if the fixed version remains poor, this branch should be deprioritized.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"}],"touched_files":["/root/sparsify-ascend/sparsify/factorized_topk_sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 5 factorized_topk crashed due to a hidden-to-latent shape mismatch in the widened encoder path, so that result should not be treated as architectural evidence.","Round 6 fixes factorized_topk by adding an explicit hidden-to-latent projection and excluding the unused base encoder from optimization before re-running the same stabilization test."],"next_hypotheses":["If the fixed factorized_topk now yields a valid proxy improvement, keep incubating the family with quality-focused tuning.","If the fixed factorized_topk still performs poorly under normal runtime, stop spending rounds on current built-in families and move to a genuinely new encoder design."]}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash recovery mode requires returning to the best known working gated path with only a minor parameter adjustment. The safest informative move is to reuse the strongest stable recipe and probe the adjacent lower-K point `K=64`, which is already a validated Pareto setting and avoids the blocked architecture-code path entirely.","summary":"Run a gated proxy stabilization pass on the current best EF=16 signum configuration with `K=64`, keeping LR=1.6e-3 and AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash-recovery constraints exactly by avoiding code edits and using the strongest validated family with one small parameter change. The main risk is limited novelty because K=64 is already known, but this is the least risky way to recover a clean signal after consecutive architecture-path crashes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"64"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode requires a param-only round on the current best working configuration, so this round returns to the stable gated recipe.","The `factorized_topk` path has now crashed repeatedly for implementation-layer reasons, so it should not be touched again until session stability is re-established.","Using gated K=64 preserves the strongest known architecture and training regime while testing a previously healthy lower-cost Pareto point."],"next_hypotheses":["If the K=64 proxy run is healthy and matches its prior behavior, keep using the gated family for recovery until crashes stop.","If K=64 regresses unexpectedly under the same stable regime, return to the exact K=128 anchor on the next round to separate runtime noise from configuration effects.","If stability is restored after this round, resume broader exploration only with a clear implementation plan that avoids the recent factorized-topk registration failure mode."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After multiple rounds dominated by gated-local tuning and unresolved crash recovery, the most informative next move is to advance an already-incubating alternate family rather than spend another round near the current gated anchor. A clean `topk` K=128 proxy run under the current strongest gated training regime tests whether simpler support selection benefits more from the improved optimizer and regularization settings than it did in earlier comparisons.","summary":"Run a fresh `topk` K=128 proxy mainline comparison using the current strongest signum gated regime to see whether the improved training setup materially closes the quality gap for the incubating top-k family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a better use of the round than another gated-adjacent parameter tweak because the search has gone too long without advancing a distinct family, and `topk` already has working runs that can cleanly absorb the stronger regime. The main risk is that top-k remains well behind gated on FVU, but that negative result is still useful because it would retire a lingering incumbent alternative and narrow future exploration toward more novel architectures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The search has now gone eight rounds without advancing a new family, so architecture exploration should take priority over more local gated tuning.","`topk` remains incubating with older K=128 proxy evidence taken under weaker regimes, so it deserves one clean comparison against the current strongest training setup before being retired or promoted.","This round keeps the regime fixed to the current gated anchor settings and changes only architecture, giving a direct read on whether simpler global top-k selection benefits from the newer training recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `topk` improves materially over its prior proxy results and is competitive with gated at K=128, promote it to full and begin family-specific stabilization from this stronger anchor.","If `topk` runs normally but remains clearly worse than gated, retire it from near-term focus and move to a more expressive new architecture family.","If `topk` is still worse on FVU but shows meaningfully better runtime or memory behavior, keep it alive as a cost-quality tradeoff family rather than a main quality contender."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU at K=128 appears limited more by encoder capacity than by auxk tuning, so increasing expansion_factor from 8 to 16 while holding the improved LR=1.6e-3 and AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125 fixed may reduce proxy FVU below the current JumpReLU proxy anchor.","summary":"Keep the best K=128 JumpReLU quality anchor fixed and begin the expansion-factor sweep with EXPANSION_FACTOR=16, since the recent auxk sweep underperformed and capacity is the next clean one-parameter probe.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the runtime exploitation guidance and changes exactly one primary variable after two auxk reductions both degraded proxy quality. The main risk is extra capacity may not help at fixed optimization settings, but EF=16 is the most justified next test before broader architecture changes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 14-15 showed AUXK_ALPHA=0 and 0.01 both worsening proxy FVU versus the K=128 JumpReLU anchor, so auxk reduction is not the near-term path to lower FVU.","This round shifts the single-variable sweep from regularization to capacity by testing EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 at the established K=128 JumpReLU baseline.","If EF=16 improves proxy quality without a major throughput drop, promote to full before considering smaller K or cost-focused follow-ups."],"next_hypotheses":["If EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 improves proxy FVU, promote to full and then decide whether to stabilize EF further or tune LR on the higher-capacity model.","If EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 is worse or neutral, test EXPANSION_FACTOR=4 to map whether the current EF=8 is already near-optimal.","If both EF=16 and EF=4 fail, conclude local JumpReLU capacity sweeps are exhausted and return to architecture exploration or a fresh optimizer-level change."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0012.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"jumprelu looks promising enough to deserve a family-specific stabilization pass, and its current default threshold initialization is likely too weak to realize the benefit of learned gating. Test jumprelu at K=128 with Adam using a higher initial threshold and smoother STE bandwidth so the encoder starts from a more selective regime.","summary":"The first jumprelu proxy was slightly better than the recent hybrid proxy points, but not strong enough to justify an immediate full run. This round keeps the new family and optimizer fixed and tunes its threshold dynamics directly, which is the most important family-specific lever for quality.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the right follow-up because JumpReLU's distinctive mechanism is its learned thresholding, so the defaults deserve at least one targeted pass before judging the family. The chosen threshold and bandwidth may still be off, but the hypothesis is clean and easy to evaluate.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.01"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.01"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["jumprelu at K=128/ef8/adam reached proxy FVU 0.2749013416469097, which is modestly competitive with recent hybrid proxy points but not yet enough for promotion.","Round 12 performs the first family-specific jumprelu stabilization pass by increasing the initial threshold and STE bandwidth to encourage more meaningful learned gating."],"next_hypotheses":["If stabilized jumprelu materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full before spending more rounds on hybrid variants.","If stabilized jumprelu is flat or worse, keep hybrid_topk Adam ef=8 as mainline and either try another new family or return to a training-dynamics experiment on the hybrid checkpoint."]}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0030.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed family did not get a fair read because its initial support selection was too close to baseline top-k and tripped the identical-to-baseline guard. Making routed support depend on an independently initialized router with a direct, non-monotone routing bonus should produce a genuine architecture signal in proxy and reveal whether separate support selection can outperform the stalled gated search.","summary":"Fix the routed prototype so its initial routing behavior is observably different from baseline top-k, then rerun routed in proxy at K=128 under the current strongest training regime.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a coherent architecture follow-up under severe stagnation: it repairs a blocked fundamentally different family instead of spending another round on minor parameter tuning. The main risk is that routed still underperforms on quality, but the previous crash was not informative, so this code-fix probe is higher value than more local gated adjustments.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Adjusted routed initialization so the router is independently initialized instead of near-copying the magnitude encoder, avoiding baseline-equivalent startup behavior.","Changed routed support scoring to include a direct router bonus, making selection meaningfully different from plain top-k while still decoding with gated magnitudes.","Local sanity checks now show routed top-k indices and top activations differ from baseline at initialization, and forward/backward both succeed."],"next_hypotheses":["If routed now runs cleanly and beats gated proxy materially, promote it and begin routed-specific stabilization as the main architecture path.","If routed runs but remains clearly worse, retire this version of the family and redirect architecture exploration elsewhere.","If routed quality is competitive but runtime is poor, keep the family alive and follow with a performance-focused code pass rather than discarding it on throughput alone."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/logs/agent_action_0015.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent new families have all clustered far above the current hybrid full frontier, so the most credible next move is a training-dynamics pass on the one family that has actually improved full FVU. Adding a modest orthogonality penalty to hybrid_topk may reduce decoder interference between active features, sharpen the effective support at K=128, and improve reconstruction quality without changing the proven architecture.","summary":"Adaptive-threshold TopK matched the jumprelu-level proxy plateau rather than breaking through, so architecture exploration has not yet produced a stronger mainline candidate. This round returns to the best-known hybrid_topk K=128/ef=8/Adam setup and tests a single quality-focused regularization change, using proxy first to see whether reduced decoder interference can move FVU meaningfully below the recent 0.27 proxy band.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"hybrid_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a narrow follow-up on the only family with a verified full win, not another broad sweep. The risk is that orthogonality regularization could trade away too much fitting capacity, but it is a clean way to test whether the remaining bottleneck is feature interference rather than encoder expressivity.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"hybrid_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"ORTHO_LAMBDA","value":"1e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Adaptive_threshold_topk did not improve beyond the recent jumprelu-level proxy plateau, so support-suppression alone is not enough to beat the current hybrid mainline.","Round 15 returns to hybrid_topk for a training-dynamics probe, testing whether mild decoder orthogonality regularization can improve K=128 quality by reducing active-feature interference."],"next_hypotheses":["If hybrid_topk with ortho regularization improves proxy FVU materially, promote it to full as the next mainline quality test.","If the ortho pass is flat or worse, bias the next round toward a more expressive new architecture edit rather than more local regularization sweeps."]}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0056.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The EF=32 `factorized_topk` variant improved with more capacity, but lowering LR regressed sharply, so the family now looks more sensitive to support-shaping regularization than to further optimizer slowdown. The cleanest remaining single-variable stabilization check is to raise `AUXK_ALPHA` on the best factorized recipe (EF=32, LR=1.6e-3) and test whether stronger dead-feature recovery improves utilization enough to recover proxy FVU.","summary":"Run a `factorized_topk` proxy stabilization pass at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, `K=128`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` to test whether stronger aux-k regularization improves the best current factorized setup.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays in exploitation mode on the only active incubating family, changes exactly one variable, and follows the remaining obvious stabilization axis after the LR regression. The main risk is that aux-k also fails to help, but that outcome would be useful evidence that the family is near exhaustion and ready to archive.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`factorized_topk` at EF=32 improved over EF=16, but reducing LR from 1.6e-3 to 8e-4 regressed from proxy FVU 0.3188326023519039 to 0.3457685150206089, so lower LR is not the right stabilization direction.","The best current factorized recipe remains EF=32, LR=1.6e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 at K=128.","This round tests the remaining obvious non-architectural stabilizer on that best recipe: stronger aux-k pressure for feature recovery and usage balance."],"next_hypotheses":["If higher AUXK improves `factorized_topk`, continue with one final nearby AUXK check or consider promotion pressure only if the gain is substantial.","If higher AUXK does not help, archive `factorized_topk` as exhausted under the current execution layer and return to a different search direction.","If AUXK improves quality but hurts runtime or stability, consider a small code/performance follow-up only if the quality gain is meaningful."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0022.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Top-k was only modestly competitive and still far from the K=128 quality target, so the next fundamentally different probe is the gated SAE family using only launcher-safe overrides; separating support selection from magnitude may recover cleaner latent routing than both JumpReLU and plain top-k.","summary":"Launch a proxy gated-family prototype at K=128 using the strongest validated training regime, but avoid architecture-specific override keys that previously caused invalid-env crashes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps the round focused on a real architecture change rather than another exhausted local sweep, and it directly addresses the recent gated launch failures by using only confirmed-safe env overrides. The main risk is that gated remains worse than top-k and JumpReLU, but that is the most informative remaining architecture probe available without code changes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Top-k produced a clean proxy run but remained far above the current full K=128 JumpReLU frontier, so a stronger architecture change is still needed.","Recent gated crashes were caused by invalid env overrides rather than confirmed model failure, so the family deserves one clean retry with only generic override keys.","This round tests whether gated routing can provide a more meaningful architecture departure than plain top-k while keeping the optimization regime fixed."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated runs cleanly and improves proxy FVU, stabilize the family with a follow-up that tunes gate-specific parameters or promotes to full if the gain is large enough.","If gated runs cleanly but is still uncompetitive, conclude that the current non-code architecture set is exhausted and plan a code-backed new family next.","If gated still crashes under launcher-safe overrides, retire it as an execution-layer mismatch and focus future architecture exploration on families that can be expressed with the current valid override surface."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0048.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`factorized_topk` still lacks a usable proxy quality signal, and the most recent failure evidence points to the sanity invocation itself rather than a meaningful architecture outcome. The least-bad next move is to rerun the same `factorized_topk` K=128 proxy comparison without further code churn so the family can receive one clean measurement under the current strongest regime.","summary":"Retry the `factorized_topk` K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline, keeping the same regime and avoiding additional code changes so the family can get its first real quality read.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is narrower and better justified than another code-edit round because the latest recorded failure mode does not provide evidence that the architecture implementation itself is wrong. The main risk is another blocked run, but a clean retry is necessary before either stabilizing or retiring the family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`factorized_topk` still has no valid proxy quality measurement despite multiple attempts, so the family remains unresolved rather than negatively established.","The latest recorded sanity failure shows a syntax error in the generated check command, which is stronger evidence of a runtime invocation problem than of an architecture-quality issue.","This round keeps the exact `factorized_topk` prototype target fixed and changes nothing except giving the family another clean chance to produce a real proxy result."],"next_hypotheses":["If the retry completes and materially beats plain `topk`, keep `factorized_topk` alive and begin family-specific stabilization on its internal factorization design.","If the retry completes normally but remains far behind gated, retire shallow factorization and move to a different encoder-expressivity direction.","If the retry still fails before producing usable metrics, treat the blockage as an execution-layer issue around this prototype path and shift effort elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0066.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The gated family now appears locally exhausted: the aux, LR, expansion, low-K, and optimizer sweeps have not moved the K=128 full frontier, and the recent `adam` trial regressed badly in full despite a decent proxy. The least-bad next informative move is to switch the single primary variable back to architecture and re-benchmark the strongest alternative promoted family, `jumprelu`, at K=128 under the current strongest shared training regime to see whether it can reopen a path toward better mainline quality.","summary":"Run a `jumprelu` proxy comparison at `K=128` under the current strongest signum regime to refresh the best non-gated architecture against the stalled mainline.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This changes only the architecture while keeping the training recipe otherwise anchored to the current strongest regime, which makes the comparison interpretable after gated stagnation. The main risk is low novelty because JumpReLU was explored earlier, but it is the cleanest already-implemented alternative with prior evidence that is closer to the frontier than the archived families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated mainline is now saturated enough that further local param sweeps are lower value than a fresh comparison against the best already-implemented alternative family.","The recent `adam` run showed that proxy optimism on gated did not transfer to full, reinforcing that the current bottleneck is not obviously optimizer-specific.","`jumprelu` remains the strongest previously promoted non-gated family, so refreshing it under the current shared regime is the most defensible architecture-side move before inventing a new family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` is competitive in proxy under the refreshed regime, keep it alive with a stabilization pass on its own family-specific settings next.","If `jumprelu` remains clearly behind gated, treat the promoted legacy families as exhausted and shift to a genuinely new architecture family afterward.","If `jumprelu` improves early-curve behavior but not final quality, follow up with a conservative family-specific tuning round rather than returning immediately to more gated sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five rounds of factorized-topk stabilization failed to approach the gated frontier, so that direction is now effectively exhausted rather than merely under-tuned. The next mandatory informative move is a fundamentally different architecture family: a `residual_topk` SAE that spends the same total K budget across two sequential sparse stages, letting a second sparse pass model the first-pass residual instead of forcing one flat support set to capture everything at once.","summary":"Add a `residual_topk` prototype in `sparsify/` and run a K=128 proxy comparison under the current best signum regime to test whether two-stage sparse residual coding can beat flat top-k-style encoders.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"residual_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the runtime mandate to stop minor parameter tweaks and switch to a genuinely different architecture approach after repeated stagnation. The main risk is implementation complexity or slow runtime, but a minimal two-stage prototype is still the cleanest next discriminator because it changes the coding mechanism itself rather than repeating another local sweep.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`factorized_topk` now appears near-exhausted: EF=32 improved modestly over EF=16, but lower LR regressed and higher AUXK was effectively flat versus the best factorized result.","Severe stagnation rules out another minor parameter tweak; the next round must test a genuinely different sparse-coding mechanism.","`residual_topk` is intended as a two-stage sparse residual encoder that preserves comparable evaluation semantics while changing how the K budget is allocated internally."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_topk` runs and materially improves proxy FVU, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal K split next.","If it runs cleanly but is clearly worse than gated and not better than factorized-topk, archive it quickly and move to another architecture family.","If quality looks promising but runtime is poor, follow with a focused performance/code-fix round instead of discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0062.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`residual_topk` still has no quality signal because the latest prototype attempt failed at the same architecture-selection gate before training began. The smallest informative move remains a narrow code-fix round inside `sparsify/` that explicitly registers `residual_topk` in config validation and SAE class dispatch, so the intended K=128 proxy prototype can finally clear selection and reach a real sanity/training signal.","summary":"Fix `residual_topk` architecture registration and dispatch under `sparsify/`, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"residual_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps the round focused on the repeated blocker instead of spending another cycle on exhausted gated sweeps. The main risk is that registration is only the first missing piece, but resolving the concrete selection failure is still the cleanest next step and preserves comparability of the intended prototype run.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 61 repeated the same `Unknown architecture: 'residual_topk'` failure, so the family is still blocked at architecture registration rather than judged on quality or runtime.","The stable gated frontier remains useful as an anchor, but further local gated sweeps are currently less informative than unblocking a new family that still has no valid proxy signal.","This round should remain a minimal blocker-removal pass limited to making `residual_topk` selectable and constructible by the existing execution layer."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_topk` clears sanity and yields a competitive proxy result, keep the family alive and tune its internal allocation next.","If `residual_topk` runs but is clearly uncompetitive, archive it quickly and move to a different architecture family.","If the run still fails after registration and dispatch are fixed, treat the remaining issue as deeper architecture compatibility and switch to another new family rather than returning to more gated local tuning."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0031.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Seven non-improving rounds indicate the current gated-centered search is fundamentally stalled, and the updated routed encoder is now the highest-value different architecture to test because it separates support selection from reconstruction magnitude without relying on the same gated monotone ranking. A clean proxy run of routed at K=128 under the best validated training regime can reveal whether this support-selection change opens a new quality path that top-k and gated did not.","summary":"Run the routed architecture in proxy at K=128 using the current strongest training settings to test a fundamentally different support-selection mechanism.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the required mode shift away from minor parameter sweeps and uses the most defensible alternative architecture currently available in the codebase. The main risk is that routed still underperforms, but that outcome would be more informative than another local gated adjustment because it tests whether the current search direction is structurally limited.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated-local search now appears exhausted, so this round shifts to the routed family as the most meaningful architecture alternative presently available.","Routed should now provide a genuinely different support-selection behavior from plain top-k and gated, making this proxy result informative even if it does not beat the frontier.","This run keeps the strongest validated training regime fixed so the readout focuses on the routed selection mechanism rather than confounded optimization changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If routed proxy FVU is competitive with or better than top-k and gated, keep the family alive and promote or stabilize it as the next main architecture path.","If routed runs cleanly but is clearly worse, conclude that this support-selection variant is not the missing ingredient and deprioritize it.","If routed quality is promising but throughput regresses, follow with a routed-specific performance pass rather than discarding the family on speed alone."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0024.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The new gated K=128 frontier at EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 may still be under-optimized at LR=1.6e-3, and increasing the signum learning rate to 3.2e-3 could improve reconstruction further now that the higher-capacity gated encoder has shown clear full-run gains.","summary":"Keep the promoted gated K=128 EF=16 architecture fixed and begin a gated-specific learning-rate stabilization sweep with LR=3.2e-3 in proxy.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This builds directly on the first full gated win and changes one generic, launcher-safe parameter while holding the successful architecture fixed. The main risk is overshooting and losing the newly gained quality, but LR is the cleanest next stabilization axis after capacity produced a clear improvement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Gated at K=128 with EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 established a new full frontier, confirming the family is now the mainline quality leader.","This round starts gated-family stabilization by testing whether the higher-capacity model benefits from a higher learning rate than the inherited 1.6e-3 baseline.","Quality remains far from the aggressive target, so the focus stays on improving K=128 gated reconstruction rather than reducing K or cost."],"next_hypotheses":["If LR=3.2e-3 improves gated proxy FVU, promote to full and continue local LR refinement around the new optimum.","If LR=3.2e-3 is worse, test a lower LR such as 8e-4 or 4e-4 while keeping gated EF=16 fixed.","If LR sweeps plateau quickly, move to gated-specific regularization or architecture refinements rather than returning to older families."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU can reduce FVU further at K=128 by making its gating sharper and more selective; increasing the initial threshold while narrowing the bandwidth should suppress weak activations more aggressively and improve reconstruction quality.","summary":"Advance the `jumprelu` family from prototype to stabilization with a single family-specific parameter sweep point at the K=128 anchor. Keep architecture and optimizer fixed and test a sharper thresholded encoder to see whether the current 0.1888 full FVU can be pushed materially lower before considering any cost tradeoffs.","change_type":"parameter_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is a focused follow-up on the only family with positive evidence so far. The main risk is over-sparsifying early and hurting reconstruction, but that is the right failure mode to test next because the current signal suggests threshold behavior is the key family-specific lever.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.30"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.05"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["JumpReLU established the current K=128 full frontier at FVU 0.1887873373925686, so the next round should tune its threshold dynamics rather than reduce K.","Round 3 tests a sharper JumpReLU gate via higher init threshold and lower bandwidth as the first stabilization pass."],"next_hypotheses":["If the sharper JumpReLU setting improves proxy FVU, continue stabilizing within the family by tuning threshold strength before any K reduction.","If sharper gating hurts quality, try a softer stabilization point with moderate threshold and bandwidth rather than abandoning JumpReLU immediately.","If JumpReLU plateaus after a few threshold sweeps, introduce a new routing-focused family instead of continuing weak local search."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU at the K=128 quality anchor may be undertrained at the current signum learning rate, and lowering LR to 4e-4 could improve optimization stability enough to beat the current 0.1888 full-FVU baseline.","summary":"Return to the best-quality JumpReLU K=128 configuration and start a systematic LR sweep with 4e-4, keeping all other settings fixed so the round cleanly tests whether optimization, not architecture, is limiting quality.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round narrowly focused on a single LR change on the strongest quality anchor after completing the required K ladder. The main risk is that lower LR may simply slow progress without improving FVU, but it is the cleanest next exploitation step given that K=64 and K=32 both trailed the K=128 baseline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Completed the required K exploration ladder: K=64 and K=32 both remained workable but did not beat the K=128 quality anchor.","Round 11 returns to the best-quality JumpReLU K=128 setup and begins the requested single-parameter LR sweep.","Testing LR=4e-4 first probes whether the current baseline is limited by overly aggressive signum updates rather than by model capacity or sparsity budget."],"next_hypotheses":["If LR=4e-4 improves proxy FVU, promote to full and continue LR refinement around the K=128 anchor before revisiting smaller K.","If LR=4e-4 is flat or worse, test LR=1.6e-3 next on the same K=128 JumpReLU baseline to probe the opposite optimization direction.","If LR sweeps fail to move quality, keep K=128 fixed and sweep auxk_alpha next, starting with 0 or 0.01."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0013.json:55:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0014.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU at K=128 may be paying unnecessary reconstruction cost to the auxiliary dead-feature objective, and removing auxk pressure could lower primary FVU below the current 0.1724 full frontier.","summary":"Hold the improved JumpReLU K=128 setup fixed at LR=1.6e-3 and start the auxk sweep by setting AUXK_ALPHA=0 to test whether pure reconstruction training beats the current anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"The LR sweep already found a clear improvement and 3.2e-3 only gave a marginal archive result, so shifting to auxk is the cleanest next one-variable probe. The main risk is increased dead features or weaker long-run stability, but proxy is the right stage to test whether the auxiliary term is helping or hurting frontier quality.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["LR=3.2e-3 slightly improved over 1.6e-3 in full FVU but only marginally, so optimization gains from LR alone appear to be flattening.","Round 14 begins the requested AUXK sweep on the strongest K=128 JumpReLU anchor rather than continuing ever-higher LR exploration.","This round tests whether the auxiliary dead-feature objective is now constraining primary reconstruction quality at the improved learning rate regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If AUXK_ALPHA=0 improves proxy FVU, promote to full and then refine auxk near zero, such as 0.01, on the same K=128 anchor.","If AUXK_ALPHA=0 is worse, restore auxk and test AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 next to probe whether a smaller but nonzero auxiliary weight is optimal.","If auxk changes do not improve quality, keep K=128 fixed and start expansion-factor sweeps, beginning with EXPANSION_FACTOR=16."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0045.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The lower-LR gated sweep was a clean regression, so the next narrow exploitation move is to test the remaining untried capacity point on the best stable family. Reducing gated `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 4 at K=128 may reveal a non-dominated quality-cost tradeoff and will close the last obvious one-parameter sweep on the current anchor before returning to broader architecture work.","summary":"Run a gated K=128 proxy stabilization pass with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` on the current signum baseline, keeping LR, AUXK, and architecture fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps to one parameter, follows the current exploitation guidance, and resolves the remaining obvious gated sweep dimension rather than introducing another unstable architecture prototype. The main risk is a clear FVU regression from reduced capacity, but that result would still be informative because it closes the current gated sweep and sharpens the case for returning to architecture exploration.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"4"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`LR=2e-4` was a healthy but worse gated K=128 run, so lower-LR exploitation does not currently look promising.","This round closes the remaining obvious one-parameter gated sweep by testing the untried `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` point on the strongest stable anchor.","Keeping architecture, K, optimizer, LR, and AUXK fixed isolates expansion factor as the only changed variable and gives a direct read on the quality-capacity tradeoff at the anchor K."],"next_hypotheses":["If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` is unexpectedly competitive, keep it alive as a quality-cost tradeoff candidate and consider checking runtime or memory benefits before discarding it.","If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` is clearly worse, conclude that the obvious gated one-parameter sweep is exhausted and resume architecture exploration or fix the blocked `factorized_topk` sanity issue.","If `EXPANSION_FACTOR=4` materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full and treat lower-width gated training as the new mainline stabilization candidate."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0007.json:83:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The obvious gated one-parameter sweep is now exhausted after clean regressions on both lower LR and lower expansion, so the next least-bad informative move is to unblock the incubating `factorized_topk` family rather than introduce another fresh direction. Its only evidence so far is a `sanity_failed` prototype, which should be treated as an architecture-compatibility issue, not a quality result. A narrow code fix inside `sparsify/` to make `factorized_topk` forward/backward compatible with the runtime should recover one valid proxy measurement at K=128 under the existing strongest regime.","summary":"Fix the `factorized_topk` implementation in `sparsify/` so it passes sanity, then rerun the same K=128 proxy prototype under the current signum baseline.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the current priority order: resolve the blocked sanity failure on an already-incubating family before expanding the search space again. The main risk is spending a round on implementation recovery for a family that still underperforms, but one clean run is necessary before making any architecture judgment.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The gated exploitation sweep has now tested the remaining obvious one-parameter moves at K=128 and both lower LR and lower expansion regressed cleanly.","`factorized_topk` still has no usable quality signal because its first prototype failed at sanity, so it should not be treated as an architecture-quality miss yet.","This round keeps the original `factorized_topk` proxy target and changes only the architecture code needed for forward/backward compatibility under the fixed runtime."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `factorized_topk` run completes and beats plain `topk`, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal factorization width or activation design next.","If the repaired run completes normally but remains far behind gated, retire shallow factorization and move to a different encoder-expressivity direction such as low-rank-plus-residual or routed multi-branch designs.","If `factorized_topk` still fails sanity after the focused fix, conclude that this prototype path is currently not viable in the stack and shift effort to another architecture family with a cleaner integration path."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0064.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The standard gated hyperparameter sweeps at K=128 are exhausted and the recent `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` recovery check regressed, so the cleanest exploitation move is to reuse the best validated aux-free gated regime and probe the remaining adjacent lower-K point. Changing only K from the strongest K=128 anchor to K=32 tests whether the recovered gated recipe can strengthen the low-cost frontier without reopening blocked architecture paths.","summary":"Run a gated proxy comparison at `K=32` with the recovered aux-free signum recipe to test whether the stable K=128/K=64 regime also improves the remaining lower-K frontier point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays in exploitation mode on the strongest working family, avoids further exhausted LR/aux/EF sweeps at K=128, and changes a single dimension relative to the best anchor. The main risk is that K=32 remains too far from the quality target, but this is still the most informative remaining low-risk sweep inside the validated gated regime.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"32"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated K=128 recovery check with `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` regressed badly, so the aux-free regime remains the best current working anchor for exploitation.","Standard gated LR, aux, and expansion sweeps are exhausted at K=128, so the most defensible remaining exploitation move is to map the adjacent K frontier under the recovered aux-free recipe.","This round keeps the family and optimization fixed and changes only K to test whether the restored gated regime improves the unresolved K=32 tradeoff."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated K=32 with `AUXK_ALPHA=0` improves over the current K=32 point, keep the aux-free regime alive across the low-K frontier.","If K=32 regresses, treat `AUXK_ALPHA=0` as beneficial mainly for K=64/128 and keep the canonical K=32 recipe when needed.","If the low-K gated sweep is exhausted without meaningful gains, shift the next round back toward architecture exploration once crash pressure is no longer dominant."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The cleanest next move is to stay on the strongest stable gated K=128 anchor and test a lower learning rate as a single-variable stabilization sweep. If the current `1.6e-3` regime is slightly overshooting, `2e-4` may improve reconstruction quality without changing architecture, sparsity mechanism, or expansion.","summary":"Run a gated K=128 proxy stabilization pass at `LR=2e-4` on the current EF=16 signum baseline to test whether a lower learning rate improves FVU on the main quality anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round narrow, avoids mixing code and architecture changes, and targets the current best validated family with a plausible quality-oriented hyperparameter sweep. The main risk is undertraining in proxy, but that still gives a useful bound on whether lower-LR gated tuning is worth further attention.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The most recent valid alternate-family result left `topk` clearly behind gated, so this round returns to the best stable gated anchor for a one-variable sweep.","Older crashes should not be treated as architecture-quality evidence, so this round avoids reopening unstable code paths and instead seeks a clean proxy signal.","Keeping architecture, K, optimizer, AUXK, and expansion fixed isolates learning rate as the only changed variable on the strongest current baseline."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=2e-4` improves proxy FVU, promote it to full and treat lower-LR gated training as the new stabilization candidate.","If `LR=2e-4` is worse but training is healthy, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and test the remaining expansion-factor sweep only if exploitation continues.","If `LR=2e-4` undertrains badly, conclude that remaining gated gains are unlikely to come from lower LR and resume broader architecture exploration after closing any required sweep points."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0001.json:78:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Returning to the best known working JumpReLU K=128 configuration and modestly increasing AUXK_ALPHA to 0.0625 may improve training stability and feature health without changing the core architecture or optimization regime, potentially recovering some proxy quality after the recent stalled sweeps.","summary":"Use the current best working JumpReLU K=128 setup as the stability anchor and make one minor parameter adjustment by testing AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 in proxy.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This respects crash-recovery constraints by avoiding code edits and new architectures, and it returns to the strongest validated configuration with a single conservative parameter change. The main risk is that higher auxk may over-regularize reconstruction, but it is a safer stability-oriented probe than another architecture shift.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0625"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash-recovery mode requires returning to the best known working configuration and limiting the round to a minor parameter-only adjustment.","This round restores the strongest JumpReLU K=128 baseline and tests a slightly stronger auxiliary dead-feature objective for a stability-oriented probe.","If AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 does not help, the remaining conservative fallback is an LR reduction on the same baseline rather than another architecture change."],"next_hypotheses":["If AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 improves proxy FVU, promote to full and treat the higher-auxk regime as the new stable JumpReLU anchor.","If AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 is worse but training remains healthy, test LR=2e-4 on the same restored baseline as the next stability-oriented adjustment.","If stability problems persist even on the restored baseline, pause architecture exploration and continue only with conservative recovery steps around the known-good JumpReLU configuration."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0027.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The gated K=128 EF=16 model has now regressed at both 3.2e-3 and 8e-4, so the remaining clean learning-rate check is whether a more conservative signum step size of 4e-4 recovers a smoother optimization path and improves proxy FVU relative to the failed lower-LR probe.","summary":"Keep the gated K=128 EF=16 architecture fixed and continue the gated stabilization sweep by testing LR=4e-4 in proxy.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within the current best family and changes exactly one launcher-safe parameter in line with the exploitation guidance. The main risk is that the model is already under-updating and 4e-4 will be even worse, but it is the highest-priority untested LR in the remaining systematic sweep.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated EF=16 mainline has now failed at both higher and moderately lower LRs, so this round closes the remaining conservative LR bracket before moving to other single-parameter sweeps.","This round keeps the strongest validated gated architecture fixed at K=128 and tests only LR=4e-4 in proxy.","If LR=4e-4 also regresses, the next exploitation axis should shift from LR to gated-specific regularization such as AUXK_ALPHA rather than continuing to shrink step size blindly."],"next_hypotheses":["If LR=4e-4 improves proxy FVU materially, promote to full and compare against the current gated K=128 frontier.","If LR=4e-4 is also worse, begin a gated AUXK sweep with AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 as the next stabilization probe.","If conservative LR sweeps all fail, treat optimization as bracketed and focus subsequent rounds on auxiliary regularization or expansion changes within gated rather than more LR-only tuning."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0015.json:56:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0033.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After nine non-improving rounds and non-competitive K=128 results from topk and routed, the current global support-ranking direction looks structurally weak. The newly added `group_topk` family is the next fundamentally different architecture probe because it imposes local winner-take-all competition before global selection, which may improve feature diversity and reduce redundant support allocation under the same validated training regime.","summary":"Run the new `group_topk` architecture in proxy at K=128 with the current strongest gated training settings to test whether local competition produces a better quality or cost-quality tradeoff than topk, routed, and gated.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the severe-stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture rather than another minor sweep. The main risk is that the grouping prior is too restrictive at K=128, but it is a cleaner structural change than more tuning on already underperforming families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"GROUP_TOPK_SIZE","value":"4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The topk and routed K=128 probes were both materially worse than the gated anchor, which strengthens the case that plain global support ranking is not the missing ingredient.","This round gives the newly introduced `group_topk` family its first proxy read under the strongest validated training regime so the architecture comparison stays clean.","`group_topk` changes the support-selection inductive bias through local competition rather than another optimizer or learning-rate tweak, which is the right mode under continued stagnation."],"next_hypotheses":["If `group_topk` proxy FVU is competitive with or better than topk and routed, keep the family alive and stabilize `group_topk_size` as the next family-specific axis.","If `group_topk` is only modest on quality but shows better runtime or memory behavior, evaluate it as a Pareto-tradeoff family rather than discarding it immediately.","If `group_topk` is clearly worse on both quality and cost signals, retire this local-competition idea and move to a more expressive multi-branch or factorized encoder family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0034.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"In crash recovery mode, the safest informative move is to return to the best known working gated K=128 configuration and make the smallest remaining stabilization adjustment. A milder auxiliary pressure of AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 may preserve the strong gated baseline while avoiding the degradation seen at 0.0625, giving a cleaner read on whether the current anchor is slightly over-regularized.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass on the best gated K=128 EF=16 configuration with AUXK_ALPHA reduced from 0.03125 to 0.01.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"stability","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash recovery requirements by using the current best working architecture with a single minor parameter change and no code edits. The main risk is that this remains another non-improving local probe, but it is the lowest-risk unresolved stabilization axis around the strongest validated baseline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode shifted the search back to the strongest validated gated K=128 baseline rather than continuing architecture exploration.","The higher AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 probe was worse, so this round tests the opposite low-regularization direction with the smallest reasonable change.","This run isolates auxiliary-loss pressure as the only changed variable on the current best working configuration."],"next_hypotheses":["If AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 improves proxy FVU or training stability, promote it to full as the new gated stabilization candidate.","If AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 is also worse, conclude that the current gated anchor is not improved by AUXK retuning and keep the original 0.03125 setting as the stable baseline.","If this run shows instability despite using the best known working setup, continue crash recovery with another minimal gated parameter adjustment rather than returning to architecture exploration immediately."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0012.json:55:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0026.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent gated LR sweeps regressed, which suggests the quality ceiling is now architectural rather than a simple optimizer bracket. A new routed SAE family that separates top-k selection scores from decoded magnitudes, while warm-starting the support branch from the magnitude encoder, may preserve useful medium-strength features that plain gated currently suppresses too early and thus reduce FVU at K=128.","summary":"Prototype a new `routed` SAE family and run it in proxy at K=128 using the current strongest gated training regime as the comparison anchor.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is one coherent architecture bet: add a launcher-compatible family under `sparsify/` and evaluate it with otherwise fixed training settings. It responds directly to the stalled gated LR search without drifting into multi-axis tuning. The main risk is that the extra routing branch may not beat gated immediately, but proxy is the right incubation tier for that uncertainty.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added a new `routed` SAE family that uses support-aware top-k scores but decodes with gated magnitudes, so routing and coefficient shrinkage are no longer the same operation.","The routed family warm-starts its gate projection from the magnitude encoder instead of an all-zero gate branch, aiming to reduce optimization drag seen in later gated stabilization sweeps.","A local forward/backward sanity check passed for the new architecture before launching training."],"next_hypotheses":["If routed proxy FVU beats gated proxy materially, promote it and treat routed-specific stabilization as the new main quality path.","If routed quality is competitive but throughput regresses, keep the family alive and follow with a performance-focused implementation pass rather than discarding it on speed alone.","If routed is clearly worse, conclude that gated-family architectural refinement needs a different mechanism and try a different new family instead of more LR-only sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0053.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Stable gated low-K refreshes have restored a clean baseline but are not advancing the quality target, and the session is overdue for a real new-family readout. The least-bad informative move is to run the now-registered `factorized_topk` prototype at K=128 under the current strongest signum regime so the family finally gets a comparable proxy measurement.","summary":"Run the `factorized_topk` K=128 proxy prototype under the current best signum settings to measure whether low-rank encoder mixing improves over the existing top-k-style baselines.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps the round to one variable by changing only architecture at fixed K, LR, optimizer, and expansion. The main risk is that the new family is slower or clearly worse than gated, but one clean proxy result is still more valuable than another local gated sweep that is unlikely to move the frontier meaningfully.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`factorized_topk` is now wired into `sparsify/` and should be evaluated as a normal proxy architecture rather than treated as blocked by registration.","The stable gated K=32 and K=64 confirmations improved confidence in the current frontier shape but did not close the quality gap to the K=128 anchor, so another local gated sweep would be low-value.","This round is the first intended real quality measurement for `factorized_topk` after resolving its earlier execution-layer blocker."],"next_hypotheses":["If `factorized_topk` shows promising proxy FVU, keep the family alive and tune its internal width or routing shape next.","If it runs normally but is clearly behind gated and plain top-k, archive this factorized path and move to a different architecture family.","If runtime is the main failure mode while quality looks plausible, follow with a focused performance/code-fix round on the factorized encoder path."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0040.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"In crash recovery mode, the safest informative move is to return to the current best working gated K=128 configuration and make the smallest remaining stabilization adjustment. Setting AUXK_ALPHA from 0.01 to 0 tests whether the new gated anchor is still slightly over-regularized while keeping architecture, K, expansion factor, optimizer, and learning rate fixed.","summary":"Run a proxy stabilization pass on the best gated K=128 EF=16 configuration with AUXK disabled to test whether pure reconstruction training can improve the current anchor without changing the core regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows crash-recovery requirements by using the strongest validated configuration with one minor parameter change and no code edits. The main risk is that removing auxk hurts feature health or quality, but it is the cleanest remaining stability-oriented probe on the current best baseline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash recovery mode requires returning to the best known working configuration and limiting the round to a minor parameter-only adjustment.","The gated K=128 EF=16 AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 setting remains the strongest validated full baseline, so this round probes the adjacent zero-auxk point for possible over-regularization.","Keeping architecture, K, expansion factor, optimizer, and learning rate fixed isolates AUXK_ALPHA as the only changed variable on the current anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If AUXK_ALPHA=0 improves proxy FVU, promote it to full and treat auxk-free gated training as the new stabilization candidate.","If AUXK_ALPHA=0 is worse but training remains healthy, restore AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 and test a nearby small nonzero value only if policy still requires stability-first tuning.","If AUXK removal degrades quality clearly, keep AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 as the gated default and resume broader exploration only after crash recovery ends."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0008.json:81:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0009.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current best JumpReLU configuration may retain enough selectivity at K=64 to improve cost meaningfully while staying close enough to the K=128 quality regime to identify whether this family has a viable smaller-K path.","summary":"Run the current best JumpReLU setup at K=64 as the first required smaller-K probe, keeping the rest of the working configuration fixed so the round cleanly measures K sensitivity before any further LR, auxk, or expansion sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"cost","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This follows the required K exploration order and changes only the experimental dimension of K while keeping the best known JumpReLU settings fixed. The main risk is a sharp FVU regression because the current quality target is still far from satisfied, but that is the required information gap to close before more local tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"64"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 9 starts the required smaller-K exploration on the current best working family rather than introducing another architecture.","The K=64 test keeps the best known JumpReLU anchor settings fixed so any movement is attributable primarily to lower sparsity budget.","This round is about establishing whether JumpReLU has a credible smaller-K path before continuing systematic LR, auxk, or expansion sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If K=64 holds quality reasonably well, run K=32 next with the same fixed JumpReLU settings to complete the required K exploration ladder.","If K=64 quality collapses, return to K=128 and continue exploitation with a single-parameter LR or auxk sweep on JumpReLU.","If K=64 is promising but slower or less stable than expected, keep K fixed and do one follow-up stabilization sweep on LR before moving to K=32."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0014.json:57:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0043.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`topk` has now repeated the same K=128 proxy result under the stronger regime and remains far from the gated frontier, so more selector-only variants are unlikely to close the quality gap. The next informative move is to prototype a more expressive encoder family inside `sparsify/`: a factorized top-k SAE that inserts a learned intermediate bottleneck and nonlinearity before latent selection. This changes the encoder hypothesis, not the training recipe, and tests whether extra pre-selection mixing can recover substantially lower FVU without committing to full gating complexity.","summary":"Add a prototype `factorized_topk` architecture with a two-stage encoder inside `sparsify/`, then run it at K=128 in proxy under the current strongest signum regime as a clean new-family comparison.","change_type":"edit_arch_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the least-bad next step because the search has gone too long without a new family and the current alternate family (`topk`) appears locally exhausted. The main risk is that the extra encoder depth adds compute without enough quality gain, but that is still a useful read because it directly tests whether encoder expressivity, rather than support rule choice alone, is the missing ingredient.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["`topk` repeated its prior K=128 proxy FVU exactly under the stronger regime, which is stronger evidence of family-level stagnation than of a missed hyperparameter.","After nine rounds without a new family, the search should shift from selector tweaks to encoder-expressivity exploration.","This round introduces a `factorized_topk` prototype that keeps the same decoding and training loop but changes the encoder to a two-stage projection, isolating architecture as the primary new variable."],"next_hypotheses":["If `factorized_topk` shows a meaningful proxy gain over plain `topk` and approaches gated quality, keep the family alive and stabilize its internal width or activation design in follow-up rounds.","If `factorized_topk` runs normally but is still clearly uncompetitive, conclude that shallow factorization is insufficient and move to a more strongly routed or multi-branch encoder family.","If `factorized_topk` is only modestly better on FVU but has materially better throughput or memory than gated, evaluate it as a cost-quality frontier candidate rather than a pure quality replacement."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0023.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Gated routing has now produced a clean proxy result and slightly outperformed plain top-k, so the next meaningful architecture follow-up is to test whether the family was capacity-limited by increasing expansion_factor from 8 to 16 at K=128 under the same training regime.","summary":"Keep the gated family active and run a proxy stabilization pass at K=128 with EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 to test whether extra encoder capacity unlocks a better regime than the initial prototype.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays on a fundamentally different architecture path rather than returning to exhausted JumpReLU-local tuning, and it changes one generic override that is known to be launcher-safe. The main risk is that gated is not capacity-limited, but EF=16 is a cleaner stabilization probe than jumping back to minor optimizer tweaks.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The gated family has now run cleanly with launcher-safe overrides and slightly outperformed the plain top-k probe, so it remains the strongest non-JumpReLU architecture candidate.","This round begins gated-family stabilization by testing whether the initial prototype was capacity-limited at EXPANSION_FACTOR=8.","Using only generic overrides avoids the invalid-env failure mode seen in earlier gated attempts."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated with EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 improves proxy FVU materially, keep stabilizing gated and consider promotion only if the gain is strong enough.","If EF=16 is neutral or worse, conclude that generic parameter stabilization is not enough for gated and plan a code-backed family refinement instead of more blind sweeps.","If runtime degrades sharply while quality improves, keep the family alive and follow with a performance-focused round rather than discarding it."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0019.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU tuning appears fundamentally stalled, so the next credible move is to test the gated SAE family at K=128, where a separate sigmoid routing branch may learn cleaner support patterns than JumpReLU and reduce FVU under the same strong optimization settings.","summary":"Switch from exhausted JumpReLU sweeps to a proxy gated-family prototype at K=128 using the current best optimizer and training settings as the control.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the severe-stagnation requirement to leave minor JumpReLU tweaks and try a fundamentally different architecture. The main risk is another gated-family failure, but that is more informative now than continuing a search direction that has stalled for six rounds.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"GATED_TEMPERATURE","value":"1.0"},{"key":"GATED_INIT_LOGIT","value":"2.0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Six consecutive non-improving rounds indicate the local JumpReLU search direction is exhausted for now.","This round promotes the incubating gated family back into active testing as the required fundamentally different architecture probe.","Keeping the best-known training regime fixed isolates whether routing design, rather than another optimizer tweak, is the missing ingredient for lower FVU."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated improves proxy FVU at acceptable throughput, stabilize the family by tuning gate-specific parameters such as temperature or init_logit.","If gated shows quality promise but runtime regresses, follow with a code/performance round instead of discarding the architecture outright.","If gated is clearly worse or crashes again, retire it and move to a different architecture family rather than returning to more JumpReLU-local tuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/07_20260321_004359/round_summaries/round_0010.json:57:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0021.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU local search appears exhausted, and reverting to the fundamentally different plain top-k SAE may provide a cleaner reconstruction-support tradeoff at K=128 under the same strong optimization settings, serving as a robust architecture reset after the failed gated launch attempts.","summary":"Switch from stalled JumpReLU tuning to a proxy top-k architecture run at K=128 while keeping the strongest validated training settings fixed for a clean architecture comparison.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This satisfies the requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture approach after prolonged stagnation, while avoiding the invalid gated-only overrides that caused recent crashes. The main risk is top-k underperforming JumpReLU, but it is the cleanest valid architecture pivot available without editing code.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Recent gated attempts failed at the launcher interface due to invalid env overrides, so a different architecture probe should avoid architecture-specific override keys unless confirmed valid.","Eight non-improving rounds indicate the current JumpReLU search direction is fundamentally stalled.","This round uses the plain top-k SAE as a clean architecture reset under the same best-known training regime to measure whether JumpReLU-specific gating is part of the quality bottleneck."],"next_hypotheses":["If top-k improves proxy FVU, promote to full and then stabilize the top-k family before revisiting cost or smaller-K tradeoffs.","If top-k is competitive but not better, compare its runtime and stability against JumpReLU to decide whether it is a better base for further architecture work.","If top-k is clearly worse, conclude that a stronger new family is needed and plan a code-backed architecture exploration round rather than more JumpReLU-local parameter sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `K=40`, `EF=8` search cluster now looks broadly exhausted across low-rank residual, batch/global allocation, adaptive-budget routing, bucketed routing, and JumpReLU, so the next informative move is to test a qualitatively different representation family rather than another sparse-support variant. `codebook_topk` is the strongest remaining same-EF architecture probe because it changes the problem from pure sparse combination to coarse prototype retrieval plus sparse residual correction.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=codebook_topk`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether a discrete codebook-plus-residual mechanism can improve the lower-K frontier where the current small-EF sparse families have failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"codebook_topk","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This satisfies the required pivot to a fundamentally different architecture approach, keeps the comparison at the same lower-K and same-EF target, and avoids reopening minor hyperparameter search. The main risk is another clear regression or a policy/runtime rejection, but that result would still narrow the remaining viable search space and clarify whether the current failure is specific to sparse-support mechanisms more broadly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"codebook_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 56 showed `jumprelu` is also weak at `K=40`, `EF=8` (`val_fvu=0.36313553526997566`), so changing the sparse activation rule alone does not rescue the current lower-K small-capacity regime.","Next severe-stagnation move is a same-EF comparison with a discrete retrieval-style architecture: test `codebook_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` before escalating to more invasive code or objective changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `codebook_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `codebook_topk` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak or rejected, treat the current `K=40`, `EF=8` regime as broadly exhausted and pivot next to a more radical architecture or objective reformulation rather than another nearby variant."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
