research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0060.json:20:    "summary": "Run one matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `jumprelu`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its thresholded support path may reduce LUTurbo online selection overhead versus a full gating branch; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0060.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0060.json:105:    "description": "Run one matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `jumprelu`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its thresholded support path may reduce LUTurbo online selection overhead versus a full gating branch; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0050.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` also regressed badly in proxy, so the current question is no longer whether the leading family survives small capacity but whether any other architecture does better at the same lower-K, same-EF target. The next cleanest move is to hold `K=40`, `EF=8`, optimizer, LR, and aux fixed and switch only the architecture to `two_stage_residual`, which has prior nontrivial full-signal evidence and is the strongest remaining fair challenger in this small-EF comparison band.","summary":"Run a proxy architecture comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=40`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=8`, keeping `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This preserves single-variable isolation, respects the `EF<=16` cap and `EF=8` default, continues the lower-K priority at `K=40`, and tests whether hierarchical residual allocation is a better small-capacity architecture than both `lowrank_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` at the same budget.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"medium","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is the cleanest next comparison after both small-EF low-rank families underperformed at `K=40`. It keeps the search on the prioritized lower-K track, avoids banned `EF=32` continuation, and changes only architecture.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"two_stage_residual","K":"40","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"8","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0.0"},"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 49 showed `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also weak in proxy (`val_fvu=0.17895471677184105`), so the small-EF rebuild of the frontier should not stay family-local.","Both `lowrank_residual` and `lowrank_gated_residual` now look uncompetitive at `K=40`, `EF=8`, which strengthens the case for a same-K, same-EF comparison against `two_stage_residual` rather than any EF increase.","Keep `K=40` as the current lower-K anchor while rebuilding fair `EF=8` architecture comparisons; do not resume `EF=32` runs."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full as the first fair small-EF lower-K challenger with nontrivial signal.","If `two_stage_residual` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also weak, end this small-EF comparison cluster and pivot to a different mechanism family at the same `K=40`, `EF=8` target rather than increasing EF.","If `two_stage_residual` shows better quality but poor runtime behavior, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code fix instead of discarding the family on proxy quality alone."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
