research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0090.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With incubation slots saturated and recent fresh-family probes weak or blocked, the least-bad informative move is to return to the strongest existing alternative architecture at the active low-K target. `lowrank_residual` is the closest non-gated same-`(K=32, EF=12)` competitor seen so far, so rerunning that exact architecture point is the best available architecture-level comparison against the weak discrete branch and the slightly better gated local baseline.","summary":"Run a proxy mainline comparison for `lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This avoids another minor parameter tweak, stays in the exact low-K neighborhood, and uses an already-implemented fundamentally different family while the incubation limit blocks opening more new families.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round architecture-focused without spending another incubation slot, and it compares families fairly at the same `K` and `EF`. The downside is that this exact point has prior evidence and may simply confirm weakness, but under the current slot pressure it is the most defensible architecture move available.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 90 uses the strongest already-implemented non-gated alternative, `lowrank_residual`, for a same-`(K=32, EF=12)` architecture comparison because incubation slots are saturated.","This round is intended to refresh the exact low-K local comparison against `lowrank_gated_residual` and `residual_vq` without introducing another new family."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` is now competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40, EF=12` before touching EF.","If it remains weak, archive stale incubating families that are clearly uncompetitive and use the freed slot for a genuinely new low-K architecture family rather than more local retuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
