research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0018.json:78:    "description": "Continue the active topk low-K frontier mapping: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the deployable cost-quality frontier extends one more step down.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0036.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eleven no-improve rounds indicate the fixed-per-sample sparse allocation direction is fundamentally flawed, and recent alternatives like `jumprelu`, `two_stage_residual`, and `adaptive_budget_topk` still stayed far behind the frontier. The next coherent architecture move is to test a cleaner batch-level sparsity mechanism: add `batch_topk`, which enforces the same total activation budget across the batch but selects features globally rather than distributing them per sample or via a heuristic quota. If the main failure mode is rigid per-sample support allocation, true batch-level competition could improve reconstruction quality at fixed average sparsity.","summary":"Add a new `batch_topk` family under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe that directly tests batch-level global support allocation instead of continuing any low-signal tuning on the current mainline.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"batch_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This round changes one core variable only, the sparse allocation mechanism, and keeps the execution layer untouched. The implementation is confined to `sparsify/`, registers through the existing config/factory path, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed with visibly non-uniform per-sample active counts under a shared batch budget.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"batch_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `batch_topk`, a new sparse architecture that selects features under a global batch-level budget instead of enforcing fixed per-sample K.","Registered `batch_topk` in the existing architecture validation and factory paths under `sparsify/` only.","Local smoke test passed for `batch_topk` forward/backward execution, and the encoded supports showed non-uniform per-sample active counts under batch execution."],"next_hypotheses":["If `batch_topk` is competitive at K=128 proxy, keep the family alive and promote to full before local tuning.","If `batch_topk` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented `code_fix` on the batch-global selection path rather than discarding the family immediately.","If `batch_topk` remains clearly behind, archive batch-level global allocation and pivot to another fundamentally different mechanism rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0100.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The low-K lane has repeatedly rejected support-selection tweaks, whitening variants, and discrete residual families, so the strongest pending informative move is to execute the newly added `bucketed_lowrank_residual` reformulation at the exact active target. Conditioning the residual dictionary on coarse sample regime may recover useful low-K capacity where single-dictionary residual models and other mechanism swaps have stalled, without changing K or EF.","summary":"Run the first proxy measurement for `bucketed_lowrank_residual` at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This keeps the experiment in the active low-K lane, preserves same-EF comparability, and tests the new conditional-dictionary reformulation before opening another family or touching EF.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the cleanest next step because the family was just added and directly targets the current suspected failure mode of heterogeneous residual structure at low K. The main risk is that norm-based bucketing is too crude to help, but running it now is still more informative than another minor local tweak or another cross-family detour.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 100 executes the first proxy run for `bucketed_lowrank_residual` at the active low-K target `K=32, EF=12` after the round-99 architecture addition.","This remains a same-EF low-K comparison and tests conditional residual specialization rather than another support-selection or VQ-style mechanism swap.","If the family is weak here, that further supports moving the next architecture step toward a deeper objective or problem reformulation instead of continuing to add more incubating low-K families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and map it to `K=40, EF=12` before any EF work.","If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is clearly weak under normal runtime, archive stale weak incubating families and pivot the next move toward a stronger objective-level reformulation rather than another architecture-local tweak."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
