research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0085_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The crash is a pure registration blocker: `residual_vq` is missing from the architecture whitelist in `sparsify/config.py` and likely not wired into the constructor dispatch in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`. Patch only that registration path so the unchanged `K=32, EF=12`, `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` proxy can instantiate.","summary":"Apply a narrow registration repair for `residual_vq` inside `sparsify/` and relaunch the exact same proxy target. Do not change the experiment recipe; only make the architecture name legal and constructible by the existing config/factory flow.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"Convert the current unknown-architecture crash into a real startup/training signal for the original `residual_vq` target.","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a tight repair scoped directly to the observed `Unknown architecture` error. It preserves the original experiment exactly and avoids mixing in any new search variable.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":{"ARCHITECTURE":"residual_vq","K":"32","EXPANSION_FACTOR":"12","OPTIMIZER":"signum","LR":"1.6e-3","AUXK_ALPHA":"0"},"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/residual_vq.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 85 repair attempt 1 targets only the concrete registration failure for `residual_vq`; no recipe changes are allowed.","Observed blocker: `ValueError: Unknown architecture: 'residual_vq'` raised in `sparsify/config.py::__post_init__` before training starts.","Keep follow-up repairs, if needed, constrained to making the existing architecture constructible under the unchanged launcher path."],"next_hypotheses":["If the registration repair works and the run completes, evaluate `residual_vq` on quality before any further edits.","If a new concrete constructor or DDP compatibility error appears after registration is fixed, do one more pinpoint repair on the same target.","If the repaired prototype runs and is clearly weak, archive it on quality grounds rather than extending repair work."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0247.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factorized scorer \u53ea\u6539\u53d8\u5355\u6837\u672c\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u7684\u6253\u5206\u4e0e\u9009\u62e9\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u7aef\u7684\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u5bfc\u51fa\u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r246 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `K=64`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u5df2\u786e\u8ba4\u53ef\u5f62\u6210 0.14x \u5de6\u7aef\u70b9\u4e4b\u540e\uff0c\u8fdb\u4e00\u6b65\u628a\u90e8\u7f72\u67e5\u8868\u6210\u672c\u538b\u4f4e\u5230\u66f4\u5de6\u4fa7\u65f6\uff0cFVU \u662f\u5426\u4ecd\u57fa\u672c\u7ef4\u6301\u5728\u540c\u4e00\u91cf\u7ea7\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u8865\u51fa\u66f4\u5b8c\u6574\u7684\u8d85\u4f4e\u6210\u672c Pareto \u5de6\u8fb9\u754c\u3002",
