research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0013.json:18:    "summary": "Stay on the `topk` mainline and move to the next recipe axis after LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=1.7e-3` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to answer whether lighter auxiliary regularization yields a better training curve and lower final FVU.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0013.json:27:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0065.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The gated family has now exhausted the standard signum-side LR, aux, expansion, and low-K sweeps, while the research objective still needs a materially better K=128-quality signal. The least-bad next exploitation move is to keep the best gated K=128, EF=16, `AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe fixed and change only the optimizer from `signum` to `adam` to test whether a different optimization dynamic can break through the current quality plateau without introducing new architectural risk.","summary":"Run a gated proxy comparison at `K=128` with the current best architecture and hyperparameters, changing only the optimizer from `signum` to `adam`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the search in exploitation mode on the strongest validated family and changes a single dimension after the signum-local search appears saturated. The main risk is that adam underperforms immediately, but it is the cleanest remaining non-architectural lever with a plausible chance to alter training behavior at the main quality anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The aux-free gated regime now covers the full K frontier and remains the best validated family, but the signum path appears saturated on quality rather than obviously unstable.","Recent exploitation rounds improved the low-K Pareto points slightly, yet they did not move the main K=128 quality anchor enough to satisfy the current objective.","This round keeps the best gated K=128 recipe fixed and changes only the optimizer to test whether optimization dynamics, not architecture or sparsity level, are the main remaining local bottleneck."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` improves the gated K=128 proxy signal, stabilize the optimizer choice around the same architecture before resuming broader search.","If `adam` is clearly worse, treat the signum optimizer as part of the current gated optimum and return to architecture exploration once policy allows.","If optimizer choice changes training behavior but not final quality much, follow up with a conservative LR adjustment under the better optimizer in a later round."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/round_summaries/round_0032.json:36:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0051.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Stability has returned on the gated path, and the K=64 point was reconfirmed exactly in both proxy and full. The next least-risk informative move is to refresh the adjacent lower-cost gated Pareto point at K=32 under the same strongest regime, keeping architecture, optimizer, LR, AUXK, and expansion fixed so only K changes.","summary":"Run a gated proxy stabilization pass on the current best EF=16 signum configuration with `K=32`, keeping LR=1.6e-3 and AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the session on the stable best-known family, changes only one parameter, and updates the next lower-K Pareto point after K=64 was reconfirmed cleanly. The main risk is low novelty because K=32 is already on the frontier, but it is still the safest informative move before reintroducing any blocked architecture work.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"32"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 50 restored a clean working baseline: gated K=64 reproduced its prior proxy and full behavior under the strongest stable regime.","This round stays on the same gated recipe and changes only K, moving to the adjacent lower-cost Pareto point at K=32.","After repeated factorized-topk crashes, continued progress should come from stable gated runs until there is a concrete implementation plan for any new architecture attempt."],"next_hypotheses":["If K=32 matches or improves its prior proxy behavior, keep the gated low-K frontier confirmed and consider cost-focused comparisons within the stable family.","If K=32 regresses unexpectedly under the same stable recipe, treat recent results as noisy and return to the exact K=128 anchor to recheck baseline stability.","If stability remains clean after this round, resume broader architecture exploration only with an implementation plan that avoids the recent unregistered-architecture failure mode."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0167.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0167.json:57:      "If it is similar in FVU with comparable or better throughput, the next single-variable follow-up is `STAGE1_RATIO` tuning within this family rather than opening another new architecture.",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/round_summaries/round_0066.json:64:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0060.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Stability has been restored on the gated path, and the `AUXK_ALPHA=0` K=128 run essentially matched the prior best full result, so the safest informative move is to refresh the adjacent lower-cost Pareto point under the same newly revalidated regime. Changing only K from 128 to 64 tests whether the aux-free gated recipe can strengthen the lower-K frontier without reopening unstable architecture paths.","summary":"Run a gated proxy comparison at `K=64` with the recovered `AUXK_ALPHA=0`, EF=16, signum, LR=1.6e-3 recipe to test whether the stable aux-free regime improves the lower-cost frontier.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the session in the strongest working family, changes a single parameter, and uses the recovered K=128 recipe as the new anchor for a lower-cost comparison. The main risk is limited novelty because K=64 is already on the frontier, but this is the least risky way to leverage restored stability while still searching for a non-dominated point.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"64"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 59 restored a clean stable anchor on gated with `AUXK_ALPHA=0`; the full FVU 0.1598195917904377 essentially matches the previous best full K=128 gated result.","With stability back, the safest next search step is to reuse that recovered recipe and probe an adjacent lower-K point instead of returning immediately to blocked architecture-code paths.","This round changes only K, using the aux-free gated regime to test whether the lower-cost frontier can improve or become more robust under the recovered baseline."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated K=64 with `AUXK_ALPHA=0` improves over the existing K=64 point, keep the aux-free regime alive for lower-K frontier work.","If K=64 regresses, treat `AUXK_ALPHA=0` as a K=128-only recovery setting and return to the canonical K=64 recipe with `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` when needed.","If the lower-K aux-free run stays healthy, consider the same regime at K=32 before reopening architecture exploration."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0221.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: lowrank_factorized_residual\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_r \u03b2_r u_r + \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {u_r} \u662f\u9759\u6001 trunk \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\u3001{b_i} \u662f\u9759\u6001 residual \u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ea\u8ba1\u7b97 \u03b2_r \u4e0e \u03b1_i\uff0c\u518d\u6267\u884c trunk \u67e5\u8868 + residual \u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u7684\u201c\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u201d\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u6269\u5c55\u517c\u5bb9\u3002r220 \u7684 blocker \u4e0d\u662f\u8d28\u91cf\uff0c\u800c\u662f TRUNK_RANK override \u6ca1\u6709\u771f\u6b63\u8fdb\u5165\u8bad\u7ec3\u914d\u7f6e\uff1b\u5f53\u524d\u6267\u884c\u94fe\u5df2\u5177\u5907 `TRUNK_RANK -> --trunk_rank -> sae.trunk_rank` \u8def\u5f84\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u672c\u8f6e\u5e94\u4e25\u683c\u951a\u5b9a\u6709\u6548\u53c2\u8003\u8f6e r210\uff0c\u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `TRUNK_RANK=32`\uff0c\u5148\u9a8c\u8bc1 `research/history/logs/round*.config.json` \u4e0e checkpoint `config.json` \u90fd\u8bb0\u5f55 `sae.trunk_rank=32`\uff0c\u518d\u5224\u65ad\u8be5 family \u662f\u5426\u80fd\u4ee5\u9884\u4f30 total_cost\u22480.36x \u4fdd\u6301\u663e\u8457\u4f18\u4e8e <0.5x \u533a\u57df topk \u524d\u6cbf\u7684 FVU\uff0c\u540c\u65f6\u4fdd\u4f4f\u5176\u66f4\u9ad8\u541e\u5410/\u66f4\u77ed\u603b\u65f6\u957f\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0221.json:20:    "summary": "\u590d\u8dd1 r220 \u7684\u79d1\u5b66\u95ee\u9898\uff0c\u4f46\u6309\u5408\u6cd5 `param_only` \u5f62\u5f0f\u4e25\u683c\u951a\u5b9a\u6709\u6548\u53c2\u8003\u8f6e r210\uff0c\u4ec5\u4e0b\u53d1 `TRUNK_RANK=32`\u3002\u672c\u8f6e\u5148\u505a\u53c2\u6570\u751f\u6548\u786e\u8ba4\uff0c\u518d\u8bc4\u4f30 lowrank_factorized_residual \u662f\u5426\u80fd\u4ee5\u7ea6 0.36x total_cost \u8fdb\u5165 <0.5x Pareto \u4e3b\u524d\u6cbf\u3002",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0221.json:25:    "self_review": "\u8fd9\u8f6e\u7ee7\u7eed\u9075\u5b88\u5355\u53d8\u91cf\u539f\u5219\uff1a\u76f8\u5bf9\u6709\u6548 reference r210 \u53ea\u6539 `TRUNK_RANK`\uff0c\u4e0d\u91cd\u590d\u628a `ARCHITECTURE/K/EF/LR` \u5199\u8fdb patch\uff0c\u4e5f\u4e0d\u4f7f\u7528\u5df2\u7ecf\u88ab\u5ba1\u8ba1\u6807\u8bb0\u65e0\u6548\u7684 r220 \u4f5c\u4e3a\u951a\u70b9\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u590d\u8dd1 `TRUNK_RANK=32` \u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u76f4\u63a5\u53bb `16`\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u9ad8\u4f18\u5148\u7ea7\u662f\u5148\u6d88\u9664\u53d8\u91cf\u9694\u79bb\u5931\u6548\u8fd9\u4e2a blocker\uff0c\u5e76\u62ff\u5230\u7b2c\u4e00\u6761\u771f\u5b9e\u6709\u6548\u7684\u4f4e trunk-rank \u8bc1\u636e\uff1b\u5728\u5ba1\u8ba1\u901a\u8fc7\u4e4b\u524d\uff0c\u4e0d\u5e94\u628a\u7ed3\u679c\u5f53\u6210\u67b6\u6784\u7ed3\u8bba\u3002",
