research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/round_summaries/round_0009.json:80:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0053.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 52 was policy-rejected because it tried to retune `LR` on `gated@4`, which implicitly changed both `lr` and `k` relative to the family reference recipe. The corrected next single question is therefore to retune `LR` exactly on the current `gated` anchor itself: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=128, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed and the now-proven `USE_HADAMARD=1` preprocessing kept on, does raising `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3` improve the full curve further, or is `2.0e-3` still the best step size even after Hadamard strengthened conditioning?",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0053.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the family reference point so the round passes single-variable policy cleanly. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if Hadamard has genuinely widened the stable step-size range, `2.4e-3` should preserve or improve early and mid descent and finish below the current `0.142923` anchor; if the curve gets flatter, noisier, or regresses, keep `2.0e-3` as the operative shared recipe and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0053.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0053.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the family reference point so the round passes single-variable policy cleanly. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if Hadamard has genuinely widened the stable step-size range, `2.4e-3` should preserve or improve early and mid descent and finish below the current `0.142923` anchor; if the curve gets flatter, noisier, or regresses, keep `2.0e-3` as the operative shared recipe and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0017.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU at K=128 may be overprovisioned at expansion_factor=8 for the current optimization regime, so reducing expansion_factor to 4 while holding LR=1.6e-3 and AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125 fixed could improve proxy FVU by enforcing a more efficient latent basis.","summary":"Keep the best K=128 JumpReLU anchor fixed and continue the single-parameter expansion-factor sweep with EXPANSION_FACTOR=4 after EF=16 was only archive-level.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the current exploitation plan and isolates the last untested expansion-factor setting before moving to a different parameter axis. The main risk is reduced capacity worsening reconstruction, but EF=4 is the cleanest remaining test to determine whether EF=8 is actually near-optimal.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"4"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["EXPANSION_FACTOR=16 did not beat the existing JumpReLU proxy anchor, so higher capacity alone is not an obvious path to lower FVU.","This round completes the planned one-variable expansion-factor sweep by testing EXPANSION_FACTOR=4 on the same K=128 JumpReLU baseline.","If EF=4 also fails to improve proxy quality, local JumpReLU expansion-factor search should be considered exhausted and the next round should move to another remaining hyperparameter axis."],"next_hypotheses":["If EXPANSION_FACTOR=4 improves proxy FVU, promote to full and then refine around the lower-capacity regime before considering cost-focused reductions at smaller K.","If EXPANSION_FACTOR=4 is worse or neutral, finish the current exploitation slate by testing AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625 or LR=2e-4 as the next single-parameter probe.","If the remaining param sweeps also fail, conclude local JumpReLU tuning is exhausted and return to stabilizing an incubating family or introducing a new architecture direction."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
