research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0018.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current JumpReLU search direction appears locally exhausted, and a gated SAE that separates support selection from reconstruction magnitude may unlock a lower-FVU regime at K=128 by learning support with an explicit sigmoid routing branch while keeping the strong baseline optimization settings.","summary":"Stop minor JumpReLU sweeps and switch to a proxy gated-family prototype at K=128 using the current best training regime as the comparison anchor.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"quality","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation requirement to move to a fundamentally different architecture after repeated no-improvement rounds on JumpReLU. The main risk is another gated-family failure, but the existing implementation path makes a clean architecture probe more justified than continuing exhausted local tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"GATED_TEMPERATURE","value":"1.0"},{"key":"GATED_INIT_LOGIT","value":"2.0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Five consecutive non-improving rounds indicate the local JumpReLU sweep is exhausted for now.","This round switches to the incubating gated family as a fundamentally different encoder-routing approach while preserving the strongest known optimization settings for a fair comparison.","A clean gated proxy result is needed before deciding whether to stabilize the family or abandon it in favor of another architecture direction."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated improves proxy FVU at acceptable throughput, keep the family alive and tune gate-specific parameters such as temperature or init_logit in a stabilization follow-up.","If gated quality is promising but runtime regresses, do a code/performance follow-up rather than concluding the architecture is bad.","If gated crashes again or is clearly worse, retire this family and move to a different architecture branch instead of returning to minor JumpReLU tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
