research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0055.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`factorized_topk` responded to more capacity, which suggests the family is not purely dead-on-arrival and now merits an optimization stabilization pass rather than another architectural change. The most informative single-variable follow-up is to reduce LR on the stronger EF=32 setup, since the deeper factorized encoder may be underperforming because the gated baseline's aggressive signum LR is too high for this family.","summary":"Run a `factorized_topk` proxy stabilization pass at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, `K=128`, and `LR=8e-4` under the same signum regime to test whether a lower LR improves proxy FVU on the stronger factorized configuration.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps the round tightly scoped to one variable, stays in exploitation mode on the only active incubating family, and tests the next most plausible reason for the gap after capacity helped a bit. The main risk is that the family is simply too weak and LR tuning will not rescue it, but one LR check is a cheaper discriminator than continuing to scale width blindly.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["`factorized_topk` improved from proxy FVU 0.3275916539132595 to 0.3188326023519039 when expansion increased from 16 to 32, so the family shows at least some positive capacity sensitivity.","After that capacity gain, the next clean stabilization question is optimization sensitivity rather than another immediate architectural or code change.","This round keeps architecture, K, optimizer, AUXK, and expansion fixed and changes only LR to test whether the factorized encoder wants a milder signum step size than gated."],"next_hypotheses":["If lower LR improves `factorized_topk` materially, continue stabilizing the family with a small AUXK sweep on the improved recipe.","If lower LR does not help, treat the family as near-exhausted and archive it unless there is a clear performance-based reason to continue.","If the lower-LR run is healthier late in training but still not competitive, consider one final throughput-quality tradeoff check before retiring the family."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0048.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `32` to `24` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=24` control (`0.272262`), then `gated` has established a meaningful mid-low-K foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=32` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.",
