research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0067.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The best existing promoted alternatives have now been refreshed and still sit well behind the gated frontier, so the least-bad next informative move is a genuinely new architecture family rather than another local sweep. A `lowrank_residual` SAE that uses a learned low-rank linear trunk plus a sparse residual coder could remove shared dense structure before TopK selection, which is a materially different way to attack the K=128 quality ceiling without changing the execution layer.","summary":"Add a `lowrank_residual` prototype under `sparsify/` and run a K=128 proxy comparison under the current strongest signum regime.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a clean architecture exploration step after both gated and refreshed JumpReLU evidence failed to reopen the mainline frontier. The main risk is prototype underperformance, but the proposed family tests a genuinely different structural hypothesis rather than repeating exhausted sparse-mechanism variants.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 66 refreshed the strongest non-gated legacy family and it remained far from the gated anchor, so the promoted existing alternatives should now be treated as close to exhausted.","The next search step should test a structurally different hypothesis rather than another local change to gating, thresholds, or optimizer.","A low-rank-trunk plus sparse-residual encoder directly targets the possibility that the activation space contains a shared dense component that current flat sparse coders are wasting K to model."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` runs and shows competitive proxy FVU, keep the family alive and stabilize its trunk width next.","If it runs cleanly but is clearly worse than gated and not better than prior archived families, archive it quickly and move to another genuinely new family.","If it fails at sanity or selection, treat that as an architecture-compatibility blocker and do one narrow code-fix follow-up before judging the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0010.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"JumpReLU may still deliver a usable smaller-K regime at K=32, and measuring that directly is the highest-value next step now that K=64 stayed stable enough to earn a full run.","summary":"Run the current best JumpReLU configuration at K=32 to complete the required smaller-K exploration ladder before returning to LR, auxk, or expansion sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"cost","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This cleanly isolates K as the only changed variable and follows the required exploration order after the successful K=64 full run. The main downside is likely further FVU degradation relative to K=64 and K=128, but that evidence is necessary before resuming exploitation on other parameters.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"8e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_INIT_THRESHOLD","value":"0.15"},{"key":"JUMPRELU_BANDWIDTH","value":"0.1"},{"key":"K","value":"32"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 10 completes the required K exploration ladder by testing the best working JumpReLU setup at K=32.","K=64 was viable enough to warrant a full run, so K=32 is now the cleanest remaining smaller-K measurement before more parameter sweeps.","This round keeps all non-K settings fixed to preserve interpretability of the K scaling curve within JumpReLU."],"next_hypotheses":["If K=32 remains reasonably competitive, return to the better of K=64 or K=32 and begin systematic LR sweeps on JumpReLU.","If K=32 quality drops too far, return to K=128 or K=64 and resume exploitation with a single-parameter LR sweep, starting with 4e-4 or 1.6e-3.","If K=32 shows instability rather than just worse FVU, keep JumpReLU and test a small auxk_alpha change on the best-performing K setting."],"primary_variable":"k"}
