research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0039.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`group_topk` still has no valid quality signal because its first actual proxy run timed out at the first step, which is stronger evidence of an implementation bottleneck than of a bad architecture. The next coherent move is a performance-focused code pass that makes the `group_topk` encoder path more execution-friendly so the family can receive one clean proxy measurement at K=128 under the strongest current regime.","summary":"Optimize the `group_topk` encoder implementation in `sparsify/` to eliminate the first-step timeout, then rerun the same K=128 proxy comparison under the current gated anchor settings.","change_type":"edit_perf_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is the narrowest informative follow-up because round 38 failed before producing architectural evidence, and another family switch would leave the existing prototype unresolved. The main risk is spending a round on a bottleneck that still leaves `group_topk` uncompetitive, but that is preferable to misclassifying a timeout as a negative quality result.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"128"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py","sparsify/fused_encoder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 produced a `first_step_timeout` for `group_topk`, so the family still lacks a real proxy quality measurement.","Treat the timeout as an implementation issue first, not as evidence that local grouped competition is architecturally bad.","This round keeps the same `group_topk` K=128 comparison target and changes only the code path needed to obtain a valid run."],"next_hypotheses":["If the optimized `group_topk` path runs normally and is competitive with gated at K=128, keep the family alive and begin architectural refinement within the grouped-selection idea.","If the optimized run completes but remains clearly worse on FVU, retire hard local grouping and move to a more expressive encoder family.","If `group_topk` still times out after the code fix, conclude that this implementation path is not viable in the current stack and shift architecture exploration elsewhere."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
