research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0001.json:105:    "description": "\u6267\u884c\u4e3b\u7ebf topk \u53c2\u8003\u914d\u65b9\u7684 clean baseline\uff0c\u4e0d\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u4ee3\u7801\uff0c\u4e0d\u5148\u52a8 K\u3002\u7528\u5b8c\u6574 env_overrides \u663e\u5f0f\u9501\u5b9a ARCHITECTURE=topk\u3001K=128\u3001EXPANSION_FACTOR=12\u3001OPTIMIZER=signum\u3001LR=8e-4 \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u5173\u952e\u8fd0\u884c\u53c2\u6570\uff0c\u4f18\u5148\u6d88\u9664\u53d8\u91cf\u9694\u79bb\u5931\u6548\u98ce\u9669\uff0c\u5e76\u5efa\u7acb round 1 \u7684\u53ef\u6bd4\u8f83\u57fa\u7ebf\u3002",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/round_summaries/round_0019.json:36:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0032.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Severe stagnation and two non-competitive K=128 architecture probes suggest the current global-ranking support mechanisms are locally exhausted. A new `group_topk` prototype that enforces one local winner per small latent group before the global top-k may reduce redundant feature selection and improve reconstruction quality or cost under the same validated training regime.","summary":"Prototype a `group_topk` SAE family in `sparsify/` and run it in proxy at K=128 with the current strongest gated training settings to test whether local competition yields a better Pareto direction than plain top-k, gated, or routed support selection.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"group_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a single architecture bet under severe stagnation and avoids more minor gated tuning. The main risk is that group-wise competition may be too restrictive at K=128, but it is a genuinely different sparse selection mechanism with a plausible diversity and throughput upside, and the code passed a local forward/backward sanity check.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"group_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"GROUP_TOPK_SIZE","value":"4"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added a new `group_topk` SAE family that selects one winner per local latent group before the global top-k stage, creating a different support-selection bias from top-k, gated, and routed.","Extended config validation with `group_topk_size` and registered `group_topk` in architecture dispatch so checkpoints and training can instantiate it through the existing execution layer.","Local sanity check passed for `group_topk`: forward/backward succeeded and returned the expected `(batch, k)` latent activations and indices."],"next_hypotheses":["If `group_topk` proxy FVU is competitive with gated and better than top-k/routed, keep the family alive and stabilize the group size as the next family-specific axis.","If `group_topk` quality is mediocre but throughput is materially better, treat it as a cost-quality tradeoff family and compare at smaller K rather than discarding it immediately.","If `group_topk` is clearly worse on both quality and runtime, retire local-competition support selection and move to a more expressive multi-branch or factorized encoder family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improved the full K=64 frontier, so the next clean stabilization move is to test whether the same added residual capacity also improves the smallest-K point. Increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=32 may further strengthen the low-cost end of the Pareto frontier if the K=32 residual branch is currently capacity-limited.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` stabilization pass at `K=32` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, keeping the rest of the winning recipe fixed (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This checks whether the capacity gain that helped at K=64 also improves the K=32 frontier point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps variable isolation clean and extends the only confirmed positive family-specific tuning signal to the most cost-sensitive frontier point. The main risk is that EF=32 helps at K=64 but not at K=32, adding cost without enough quality gain, but that boundary is important to establish before trying aux or K=128 capacity tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 20 extends the successful `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` stabilization signal within `lowrank_residual` from K=64 down to K=32.","The next missing question for this family-specific capacity axis is whether the smallest-K frontier point is also residual-capacity limited or whether EF=16 is already sufficient there."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improves proxy FVU at K=32, promote it to full and then consider the same capacity increase at K=128.","If EF=32 is flat or worse at K=32, keep EF=16 for that point and test a different single stabilization axis such as `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` on one of the winning anchors.","If EF=32 improves K=32 quality but causes clear runtime or memory regression, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code pass rather than discarding the higher-capacity variant outright."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
