research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/round_summaries/round_0016.json:88:    "summary": "Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_residual` at K=128 using the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe after the `two_stage_residual` LR sweep failed to improve the frontier.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/round_summaries/round_0016.json:98:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/round_summaries/round_0043.json:39:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/11_20260322_021455/logs/agent_action_0035.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the gated family now improved at K=128 via AUXK_ALPHA=0.01, the next clean move is to test whether that stronger regime transfers to a smaller sparsity budget and improves the Pareto frontier rather than only the anchor point. A gated K=64 proxy run under the same stabilized settings can reveal whether the current best family can materially outperform the old JumpReLU K=64 point.","summary":"Run the stabilized gated configuration in proxy at K=64 with AUXK_ALPHA=0.01 to test whether the improved K=128 regime yields a stronger low-K Pareto point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"pareto","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps one coherent change on the current best working family and directly targets Pareto improvement at lower K instead of reopening weaker architecture branches immediately. The main risk is that gated may not transfer well to lower K, but that outcome is still informative because the existing K=64 frontier is substantially weaker than the current gated anchor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"},{"key":"K","value":"64"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Reducing AUXK_ALPHA to 0.01 produced a new best full K=128 gated result, so this setting is the new gated stability anchor.","This round tests whether the improved gated regime transfers to lower K and can strengthen the Pareto frontier rather than only refining the anchor point.","Using the same architecture and optimizer isolates K as the only changed variable for a clean low-K comparison against the existing JumpReLU K=64 frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If gated K=64 proxy is clearly better than the current JumpReLU K=64 point, promote it to full and consider gated the new mainline family across multiple K values.","If gated K=64 is competitive but not clearly better, test whether a smaller expansion factor improves the low-K cost-quality tradeoff within the gated family.","If gated K=64 is poor, keep gated focused on K=128 quality work and revisit a different architecture family for lower-K exploration."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0081.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`, keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge the run by the full trajectory versus the `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, especially whether the higher LR preserves stability while improving early/mid descent and final FVU; if it overshoots or degrades late, close the signum LR branch and keep `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0081.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0081.json:81:    "description": "Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `2.4e-3`, keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge the run by the full trajectory versus the `2.0e-3` and `1.6e-3` runs, especially whether the higher LR preserves stability while improving early/mid descent and final FVU; if it overshoots or degrades late, close the signum LR branch and keep `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0033.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eight no-improve rounds indicate the current lowrank_gated_residual tuning track is exhausted, and the frontier already covers K={32,64,128}, so the next informative move must switch the single primary variable back to architecture. The cleanest fundamentally different probe is to re-benchmark `jumprelu` at K=128 under the current strongest shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`) to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism benefits from the stronger mainline training regime that earlier non-gated families did not fully share.","summary":"Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu` at K=128 using the current strong shared lowrank_gated_residual training recipe, changing only architecture. This satisfies the mandatory architecture pivot after repeated stagnation while avoiding new code risk and giving the only remaining incubating family a fair comparison under today's strongest stable setup.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This round stops the failed minor-parameter loop on `lowrank_gated_residual` and isolates a genuine architecture change with no code edits. It also uses an existing working architecture path, which is lower risk than opening another new family after recent crash and identical-to-baseline failures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation forced a pivot away from further lowrank_gated_residual parameter sweeps and back to a fundamentally different architecture.","`jumprelu` is the selected comparison target because it is the only remaining incubating family with a stable existing code path and no new implementation risk this round.","This run tests whether the current strongest shared recipe changes the verdict on `jumprelu` relative to its much weaker earlier evidence."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` is competitive at K=128 proxy, promote it to full before any further family-local tuning.","If `jumprelu` remains clearly behind, archive it and plan the next round around a different architecture mechanism rather than more lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning.","If `jumprelu` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code fix instead of discarding the architecture on quality grounds."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
