research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0037.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Because `gated` beat the matched `topk` control at `K=96`, the next single question is whether that advantage extends one more step down the support ladder; testing `ARCHITECTURE=gated, K=64, EF=12, OPTIMIZER=signum, LR=1.6e-3` will show whether `gated` is broadly stronger across high-K frontier points or only wins near the very top end.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0037.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0075.json:20:    "summary": "Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its simpler single-stage lookup path may lower LUTurbo online cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0075.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0075.json:101:    "description": "Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `topk`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `topk` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its simpler single-stage lookup path may lower LUTurbo online cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
