research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0016.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five no-improve rounds suggest the current `two_stage_residual` direction is locally exhausted, so this round should switch the single primary variable back to architecture. The strongest informative alternative is `lowrank_residual`, which attacks the plateau by modeling shared dense structure with a low-rank trunk before sparse residual coding, and should be re-tested at K=128 under the current strongest shared recipe for a clean apples-to-apples comparison.","summary":"Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_residual` at K=128 using the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=16`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This is a fundamentally different architecture probe after the `two_stage_residual` LR sweep failed to improve the frontier.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the mandatory pivot away from minor parameter tweaks, keeps one primary variable isolated at the architecture level, and chooses the most plausible incubating alternative rather than opening a brand-new family. The main risk is that `lowrank_residual` remains clearly behind the frontier or exposes residual implementation fragility, but that is still more informative than another local sweep on the stalled mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 16 obeys the severe-stagnation pivot by abandoning further `two_stage_residual` micro-sweeps and changing only architecture.","`lowrank_residual` is the selected comparison target because it is the strongest recent fundamentally different incubating family and directly tests whether separating dense trunk structure from sparse residual coding can break the K=128 plateau."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_residual` materially improves proxy FVU, keep incubating it and consider a family-specific stabilization pass or promotion depending on margin.","If `lowrank_residual` runs but stays clearly behind, pivot to another fundamentally different incubating family such as `whitened_topk` rather than returning to `two_stage_residual` micro-tuning.","If `lowrank_residual` shows promising quality with poor throughput or instability, follow with a narrow code-focused stabilization or performance pass instead of discarding the family outright."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
