research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0087.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At low K, the residual after the low-rank trunk is likely still poorly conditioned at `EF=12`, so support selection is wasting budget on scale/correlation artifacts. A new `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual` family that RMS-centers and lightly mixes the residual before gated top-k selection may improve same-`(K=40, EF=12)` FVU over the discarded `lowrank_gated_residual` local baseline without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Added a new prototype architecture, `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual`, under `sparsify/` and registered it in config/class dispatch. The family keeps the proven low-rank trunk, but preconditions the residual with per-sample centering, RMS normalization, a small rolled mix, and a light learned low-rank correction before gated support selection. A local forward/backward smoke test passed, so the next move is a proxy run at the active comparison point `K=40, EF=12` with the stable `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3` recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This stays within the edit budget, respects the EF<=16 cap, and makes one architecture-only change at the same `(K, EF)` local comparison point. The main risk is that whitening-like conditioning could misalign encoder scores with the unchanged decoder basis, so this should be treated as an informative prototype rather than a presumed win.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 87 introduces `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual`, a low-K prototype that keeps the low-rank trunk but preconditions the residual before gated support selection.","The prototype was wired into config validation and class dispatch, and a local forward/backward smoke test succeeded."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=40, EF=12` runs cleanly and beats the local `lowrank_gated_residual` baseline, compare the same family at `K=32, EF=12` to test whether conditioning helps recover lower-K quality.","If it runs cleanly but is weak, keep the space-first direction alive only if diagnostics suggest healthier support usage; otherwise pivot to a more structurally different low-K family rather than more minor gating tweaks."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0071.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent fixed-point `K=48`, `EF=16` mechanism probes were both clearly weak, so the next informative move is to change the search framing and test a routing-based sparse mechanism at a smaller K in the preferred mainline band. Run `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=12` with the shared `signum`/`LR=1.6e-3`/`AUXK_ALPHA=0` recipe to check whether explicit support routing recovers a viable low-K tradeoff better than magnitude-style TopK variants.","summary":"Pivot from the failed `K=48` TopK-mechanism cluster to a routing-based architecture at lower K. This uses `EF=12` as the default refreshed comparison band and keeps optimizer settings fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round architecture-led under severe stagnation and shifts to a genuinely different mechanism instead of another local tweak. The main risk is that `routed` was already weak at `EF=8`, but rerunning it in the preferred `EF=12` band at the same low-K target is a cleaner read than continuing archived TopK-style families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 71 abandons the weak `K=48` TopK-style comparison cluster and pivots to a routing-based mechanism at lower K.","`routed` is refreshed in the preferred mainline band with `EF=12` rather than returning to `EF=8`, which should separate architecture quality from the earlier capacity floor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=40` before touching EF.","If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=12` is still weak, pivot to another fundamentally different non-TopK direction in the same mainline band rather than reopening archived TopK-family comparisons."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0177.json:23:    "self_review": "Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes, while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe is intentionally chosen to answer a clean architectural question under the new budget regime: whether routing is inherently worth carrying forward once low-EF cost feasibility is enforced.",
