research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0045.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` still yields valid non-dominated frontier points as K decreases, but the new `K=72` full result is now nearing the `K=64` quality regime. The most informative K-first follow-up is a lower boundary probe at `K=56` on the unchanged recipe, which tests whether the family can still produce a worthwhile smaller-K tradeoff below the current `K=64` point before switching effort back to architecture exploration.","summary":"Run a parameter-only proxy experiment for `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=56`, holding the current best recipe fixed (`EF=32`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This extends the prioritized lower-K sweep below the current frontier and avoids mixing in EF or architecture changes while the remaining open question is the lower-K boundary.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This remains a conservative within-family K probe rather than a new-family step. That is warranted because lower-K exploration still has explicit priority, `K=72` did not collapse enough to close the track, and a single sharper boundary check at `K=56` is more informative than reopening EF tuning. Main risk: the result may regress enough to add little beyond confirming that this family’s practical frontier bends sharply below `K=64`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"56"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 44 full showed `K=72` remains non-dominated but is approaching the existing `K=64` regime, so the next informative K-first move is a sharper lower boundary test rather than more interpolation near 80.","`K=56` is an untested same-family, same-EF probe that directly measures whether `lowrank_gated_residual` can keep extending the Pareto frontier below `K=64` before architecture search resumes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=56` is competitive enough to promote, run full to determine whether it creates a new smaller-K Pareto point below `K=64`.","If `K=56` regresses clearly past the useful frontier range, pivot next to a same-EF architecture comparison or a new family rather than continuing this K sweep."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0022.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The current `lowrank_residual` family has finished a clean EF=32 stabilization sweep across K={32,64,128}, and the search has gone many rounds without a new family. A narrow next bet is to keep the winning low-rank trunk intact and change only the sparse residual selector: add a gated residual branch so support selection can focus sparse capacity on the hardest residual directions at the K=128 quality anchor. If low-rank decomposition is already the right backbone, this should be a higher-signal architecture probe than another local sweep on the existing family.","summary":"Implemented a new `lowrank_gated_residual` architecture under `sparsify/` and validated it with a local import + forward/backward sanity check. Run a proxy K=128 comparison against the current winning low-rank recipe, holding EF=32, signum, LR=1.6e-3, and AUXK_ALPHA=0 fixed while switching only the architecture.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps the round to one coherent primary variable: architecture. The new family is intentionally minimal, reusing the proven low-rank trunk and existing gated mechanics to reduce implementation risk while still testing a genuinely new support-selection hypothesis at the main quality anchor.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added `lowrank_gated_residual`, which keeps the successful low-rank dense trunk but gates sparse residual support selection with a learned residual router.","Local CPU import plus forward/backward sanity check passed for `lowrank_gated_residual`; the new family is ready for runtime sanity and proxy evaluation."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` shows better proxy FVU at K=128, promote it to full before exploring lower-K variants.","If proxy quality is close but runtime is flagged as a perf regression, follow with an `edit_perf_code` pass rather than discarding the family.","If the gated residual selector is clearly worse at K=128, keep `lowrank_residual` as mainline and explore a different new family rather than more local retuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
