research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_gated_residual` continues to produce smooth, non-dominated tradeoffs as K is reduced, and the new `K=80` full point now cleanly fills the gap between `K=64` and `K=96`. The next highest-value K-only probe is `K=72` on the same recipe, which directly tests whether the frontier can be pushed further downward in K while staying materially above the `K=64` quality floor.","summary":"Run a parameter-only proxy experiment for `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=72`, holding the current best recipe fixed (`EF=32`, `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This continues the prioritized lower-K Pareto mapping and avoids reopening EF or architecture while a strong within-family K frontier remains active.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is another conservative K-frontier interpolation rather than a new-family step. That is justified because the runtime guidance explicitly prioritizes lower K over EF, the same-EF mainline family is still yielding useful non-dominated points, and `K=72` is the cleanest next informative move after `K=80` held up in full. Main risk: the result may collapse toward the existing `K=64` regime and add little beyond confirming the local slope.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"72"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 43 full confirmed `K=80` as a real intermediate frontier point for `lowrank_gated_residual`, strengthening the case for a denser local K sweep below 80 before any EF change.","`K=72` is the next clean same-family, same-EF probe to test how far the current lowrank_gated_residual frontier can be extended toward smaller K without reopening architecture search."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=72` is promoted and remains clearly above the `K=64` quality level, promote it to full as another likely non-dominated Pareto point.","If `K=72` falls close to the existing `K=64` regime, continue one more lower-K boundary check at `K=56` or pivot to a new same-EF architecture comparison rather than expanding EF."],"primary_variable":"k"}
