research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0030.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent lowrank_gated_residual sweeps exhausted local LR/aux/EF tuning without improving the K=128 anchor, and policy blocks opening a third incubating family. The least-bad informative move is to advance the existing incubating `whitened_topk` family by strengthening its preconditioner: normalize activations first, then apply a low-rank residual mixer around identity before TopK selection. If the earlier `whitened_topk` result failed because its shallow raw linear map was too weak and poorly conditioned, this stabilized geometry change could reopen quality gains under the current strong recipe.","summary":"Edit `whitened_topk` in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py` so it uses RMS-normalized inputs plus a low-rank residual preconditioner instead of a single dense raw linear map, then run a proxy comparison at K=128 with the current strong shared recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`). This keeps the round focused on one architectural variable while advancing an existing incubating family rather than opening a policy-risky new one.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This respects the severe-stagnation guidance by pivoting away from more lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning, but avoids the likely incubation-limit rejection of a brand-new family. The code change is confined to `sparsify/`, keeps the execution layer untouched, and a local forward/backward smoke test passed for the edited `whitened_topk` path.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Advanced the existing incubating `whitened_topk` family instead of opening a new family, to avoid incubation-limit risk during severe stagnation.","Reworked `WhitenedTopKSparseCoder` to encode from RMS-normalized activations passed through a low-rank residual preconditioner initialized near identity, replacing the earlier shallow dense raw preconditioner.","Local CPU forward/backward smoke test passed for the edited `whitened_topk` implementation."],"next_hypotheses":["If the stabilized `whitened_topk` proxy becomes competitive, promote to full before any further family-local tuning.","If proxy quality improves but throughput regresses, follow with a narrow `edit_perf_code` pass on the new preconditioner path rather than discarding the family.","If the stronger preconditioner still leaves `whitened_topk` far behind, archive input-preconditioning-only approaches and pivot back to a different architecture mechanism rather than more local retuning."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
