research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0034.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Nine no-improve rounds indicate the current search direction around lowrank_gated_residual is exhausted, and the latest architecture pivot to `jumprelu` remained clearly uncompetitive even under the strongest shared recipe. The least-bad next informative move is to switch the single primary variable to a different existing architecture mechanism with real prior signal: rerun `two_stage_residual` at K=128 under the current strongest stable recipe (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, signum, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0`) to test whether hierarchical residual allocation benefits from the stronger modern training regime.","summary":"Run a proxy comparison with `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual` at K=128 using the current strong shared training recipe, changing only architecture. This is a fundamentally different sparse-mechanism probe after both lowrank_gated_residual tuning and the refreshed `jumprelu` comparison failed to improve the frontier.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This round follows the mandatory architecture pivot and avoids another minor lowrank_gated_residual tweak after repeated stagnation. It also stays on an already implemented, previously working family with some real full-signal evidence, which is lower risk than opening a brand-new code path immediately after multiple failed directions.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After the refreshed `jumprelu` probe stayed far behind, the next architecture pivot moves to `two_stage_residual` rather than returning to lowrank_gated_residual micro-tuning.","`two_stage_residual` is chosen because it is a genuinely different hierarchical sparse-allocation mechanism with prior working evidence, but it has not yet been re-tested under the strongest current shared recipe.","This round isolates architecture only and checks whether residual reconstruction staged across two passes can recover quality that single-pass alternatives are missing at the K=128 anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` is competitive at K=128 proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `two_stage_residual` remains clearly behind, archive it as a current mainline challenger and plan the next round around a new architecture mechanism rather than more local sweeps.","If `two_stage_residual` shows promising quality with poor throughput, follow with a narrow performance-oriented code fix instead of discarding the family on architecture grounds."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0239.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u53ea\u505a\u5355\u6837\u672c top-k \u9009\u62e9\u4e0e\u7cfb\u6570\u8ba1\u7b97\uff0c\u90e8\u7f72\u4fa7\u4ecd\u662f\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r238 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `K=48`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003`\u3001`AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u5728\u7ea6 0.30x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u5904\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u628a\u521a\u5efa\u7acb\u7684\u5de6\u7aef\u70b9 `topk@K32` \u7684 FVU=0.3199 \u7ee7\u7eed\u660e\u663e\u538b\u4f4e\uff0c\u5e76\u8865\u51fa `0.28x -> 0.31x` \u4e4b\u95f4\u7f3a\u5931\u7684 Pareto \u8fc7\u6e21\u70b9\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u8fd9\u4e00\u6b65\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u5f00\u65b0 family\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a r238 \u5df2\u8bc1\u660e\u6700\u7b80\u5355\u5355\u5e93\u7ed3\u6784\u5728\u8d85\u4f4e K \u5de6\u7aef\u4f18\u4e8e `factorized_topk@0.30x`\uff0c\u5f53\u524d\u6700\u9ad8\u4fe1\u606f\u91cf\u95ee\u9898\u53d8\u6210 topk \u5de6\u4fa7\u524d\u6cbf\u7684\u771f\u5b9e\u659c\u7387\uff0c\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u518d\u6b21\u5207\u5230\u6700\u8fd1\u5df2\u7ed9\u51fa\u8d1f\u4fe1\u53f7\u7684 `codebook_topk`\u3001`factorized_topk` \u6216 recipe \u5fae\u8c03\u7ebf\u3002",
