research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0049.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the current recipe improvement extends to the next allowed lower-cost support level. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=16` control (`0.308437`), then `gated` has established a meaningful foothold in the low-K regime; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above that control, treat `K=24` as the practical lower bound of the current gated recipe.",
