research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0098.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The exact active point `(K=40, EF=12)` has now rejected several fundamentally different mechanisms, and the one non-TopK family with the best remaining same-EF low-K signal is `two_code_residual_vq`. Since lower K is the top priority and `K=32, EF=12` is still sparsely explored outside the residual baseline, the next informative move is to map this discrete coarse-plus-residual family down to `K=32` before spending another round on EF or another new local tweak.","summary":"Run a proxy `two_code_residual_vq` experiment at `K=32, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`, `lr=1.6e-3`, `auxk_alpha=0` recipe. This keeps the comparison in the low-K tradeoff lane, uses the default same-EF band, tests a fundamentally different architecture family from the residual/gating path, and prioritizes lower-K exploration over more EF work.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"two_code_residual_vq","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This is a single-variable low-K probe on an already repaired and runnable discrete family, so the result should be interpretable. The risk is that `two_code_residual_vq` simply degrades too much at `K=32`, but that is still more useful than another minor recipe tweak or another same-K mechanism swap after 46 no-improve rounds.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_code_residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 98 maps `two_code_residual_vq` from `K=40` to `K=32` at the same `EF=12` mainline band to honor the low-K priority while keeping a fundamentally different architecture family alive.","This is a same-EF low-K tradeoff test, not a claim of architecture improvement from added capacity.","If `two_code_residual_vq` is also weak at `K=32`, that is additional evidence that the current low-K reconstruction-only discrete-family path is not closing the frontier gap and the next move should be a stronger reformulation rather than another small mechanism swap."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_code_residual_vq` is competitive at `K=32, EF=12`, keep the family fixed and judge it as a real low-K tradeoff candidate before any EF follow-up.","If `two_code_residual_vq` is clearly weak at `K=32, EF=12`, pivot next to a genuinely new problem reformulation or architecture family rather than more local low-K retuning within the current mechanism set."],"primary_variable":"k"}
