research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0062.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A separate support router may preserve more useful structure than pure magnitude TopK at very low sparsity, so a `routed` SAE at `K=32`, `EF=8` is the next clean architecture pivot to test whether low-K quality improves through different support selection rather than more residual-branch variants.","summary":"Pivot away from the weak grouped-residual path and run a fresh same-EF architecture probe with `routed` at the lower-K target `K=32`. This keeps capacity fixed in the preferred small-EF band while testing a fundamentally different low-K mechanism that perturbs support selection directly instead of relying on grouped residual competition.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture and keeps the focus on lower K without using a larger EF. Main risk is that `routed` may behave similarly to existing gated variants, but it is still a distinct support-selection mechanism and a cleaner next probe than more local tuning.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 62 pivots away from `lowrank_grouped_residual` after its `K=40`, `EF=8` proxy remained weak, and tests a fundamentally different low-K routing mechanism instead of another residual-family follow-up.","`routed` is being probed at `K=32`, `EF=8` to keep lower-K exploration primary while preserving same-EF comparability.","If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak, treat direct support-selection variants as another negative signal in the small-EF low-K band and continue pivoting rather than resuming minor sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, keep the family fixed and map a nearby K such as `K=40` before touching EF.","If `routed` at `K=32`, `EF=8` is weak, try another fundamentally different low-K family at the same `EF=8` target, such as a preprocessing-oriented or mixture-style direction, rather than increasing expansion factor."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
