research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five rounds of gated-local tuning have failed to move the frontier, so the current search direction is likely locally exhausted. The least-disruptive fundamentally different probe is to switch the single primary variable back to architecture and run `jumprelu` at K=128 under the strongest shared signum recipe to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism can reopen quality gains without introducing new code risk.","summary":"Run a `jumprelu` proxy comparison at K=128 under the stable signum/EF=16/aux-free regime, changing only architecture from gated to jumprelu.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This satisfies the severe-stagnation requirement by abandoning minor gated parameter tweaks and switching to a fundamentally different existing architecture family with prior full-signal evidence. It keeps the round isolated to one variable, avoids blocked code-fix paths, and uses proxy first.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation triggered an architecture pivot away from further gated-local tuning.","This round revisits the best existing non-gated family under the current strongest shared recipe to test whether the search failure is specific to gated rather than the whole regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` materially improves proxy FVU, promote it to full and treat it as the main alternative trunk for further stabilization.","If `jumprelu` remains clearly behind gated under the shared strong recipe, the next move should be a different architecture path or a narrow compatibility repair for an incubating family rather than more gated parameter sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0083.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the stable `signum` reference recipe, changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against the current anchor, especially whether removing the auxiliary loss improves or smooths late descent; if it regresses or destabilizes, restore the default loss and only then consider preprocess.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0083.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0083.json:81:    "description": "Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and revert to the stable `signum` reference recipe, changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.03125` to `0.0` while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3` fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against the current anchor, especially whether removing the auxiliary loss improves or smooths late descent; if it regresses or destabilizes, restore the default loss and only then consider preprocess.",
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0042.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Crash-recovery policy forces a param-only round on the best proven working family. Rather than retrying already-regressed LR/aux/EF sweeps at the K=128 anchor, the cleanest stable move is to hold the winning `lowrank_gated_residual` recipe fixed and lower only `K` to 96 in proxy. This maps a missing mid-Pareto point between 64 and 128 and could yield a non-dominated tradeoff if quality stays close to the K=128 anchor while reducing active feature count.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_gated_residual` experiment at `K=96` using the current best working recipe otherwise unchanged: `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`, `BATCH_SIZE=1`, `GRAD_ACC_STEPS=8`, `MICRO_ACC_STEPS=1`, `DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD=10000000`, `USE_HADAMARD=0`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This obeys the param-only crash-recovery constraint, stays on the strongest validated family, and changes one substantive experimental variable: `K`. It does not chase a weakly motivated LR/aux retry, and it targets Pareto expansion directly. Main risk: the project runtime may still judge this too close to existing K sweeps, but it is the safest informative probe available without code changes.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Crash-recovery policy required a param-only round on the best working configuration; this round uses `lowrank_gated_residual` with only `K` changed substantively.","`K=96` is an explicit mid-frontier probe between the established `K=64` and `K=128` points, aimed at expanding Pareto coverage rather than only improving the anchor."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=96` proxy is close to the `K=128` proxy anchor, promote it to full as a likely non-dominated Pareto point.","If `K=96` falls much closer to the `K=64` quality level than the `K=128` level, keep `K` focus but try a nearby midpoint like `K=80` only if policy still prefers stable param-only frontier mapping."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0237.json:19:    "hypothesis": "\u5019\u9009 family: factorized_topk\u3002\u6700\u7ec8\u91cd\u6784\u516c\u5f0f\u4e3a x_hat = \u03a3_i \u03b1_i b_i\uff0c\u5176\u4e2d {b_i} \u6765\u81ea\u5355\u4e2a\u9759\u6001\u5411\u91cf\u5e93\uff1b\u4f4e\u79e9 factorized scorer \u53ea\u6539\u53d8\u5728\u7ebf\u4fa7\u7684\u652f\u6301\u6253\u5206\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u4e0d\u6539\u53d8 decoder \u7aef\u7684\u9759\u6001\u5355\u5e93\u67e5\u8868 + \u52a0\u6743\u6c42\u548c + \u9009\u62e9\u6027\u8865\u507f\u5bfc\u51fa\u5f62\u5f0f\uff0c\u56e0\u6b64\u53ef\u76f4\u63a5\u5bfc\u51fa\u5230 LUTurbo/Lottable \u63a8\u7406\u94fe\u8def\uff0c\u517c\u5bb9\u6027\u5224\u65ad\u4e3a\u76f4\u63a5\u517c\u5bb9\u3002\u76f8\u5bf9 reference_round=r230 \u53ea\u6539\u4e00\u4e2a env \u53c2\u6570 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=384`\uff0c\u4fdd\u6301 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`\u3001`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`\u3001`K=256`\u3001`OPTIMIZER=signum`\u3001`LR=0.003`\u3001`AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` \u53ca\u5176\u4f59\u914d\u7f6e\u4e0d\u53d8\uff0c\u6d4b\u8bd5\u628a\u6781\u5ea6\u538b\u7f29\u7684 scorer \u5bb9\u91cf\u4ece 96 \u63d0\u5347\u5230\u4ecd\u663e\u8457\u4f4e\u4e8e\u5168\u5bbd\u7684 384 \u540e\uff0c\u662f\u5426\u80fd\u5728\u7ea6 0.44x \u603b\u6210\u672c\u4e0b\u663e\u8457\u6539\u5584 FVU\uff0c\u4ece\u800c\u4e3a `<0.5x` \u533a\u57df\u8865\u51fa\u6bd4\u5f53\u524d `topk@0.44x` \u66f4\u6709\u7ade\u4e89\u529b\u7684\u4f4e\u6210\u672c\u70b9\u3002\u9009\u62e9\u8fd9\u4e00\u6b65\u800c\u4e0d\u662f\u7ee7\u7eed\u6cbf `topk@K248` \u7684 LR \u7ebf\u6216\u56de\u5230 `jumprelu/codebook_topk`\uff0c\u662f\u56e0\u4e3a r236 \u5df2\u660e\u786e\u5426\u5b9a\u4fdd\u5b88 LR \u5fae\u8c03\uff0cr234/r235 \u5219\u5206\u522b\u7ed9\u51fa\u5f02\u5e38\u65f6\u957f\u548c\u660e\u663e\u52a3\u8d28\u4fe1\u53f7\uff1b\u800c\u5f53\u524d\u7b56\u7565\u53c8\u660e\u786e\u9f13\u52b1\u7ee7\u7eed\u63a2\u7d22 factorized scorer \u8fd9\u7c7b\u5929\u7136\u4f4e encoder \u6210\u672c\u65b9\u5411\u3002",
