research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0011.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` remains a real K=128 win, but the front-loaded split change only matched the existing best point instead of extending the frontier, and its lower-K/width behavior still looks brittle. The next informative move is to pivot to a different non-gated family with a different inductive bias: a `multi_branch_gated` SAE that uses several gated encoder branches competing to explain different activation substructures before the final TopK selection, which could preserve the K=128 quality gains while avoiding the narrow tuning sensitivity of the staged-residual prototype.","summary":"Add a `multi_branch_gated` prototype under `sparsify/` and run a proxy comparison at K=128 using the current signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe, changing only architecture.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the observed plateau correctly: the `two_stage_residual` family is no longer extending the frontier through local internal tweaks, so a new architecture family is the least-bad next move. Risk: a first prototype may trail the current winner, but it is a cleaner use of the next round than more blind stabilization on a family that just went flat.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["The front-loaded `two_stage_residual` stabilization pass reproduced the existing K=128 best result but did not improve it, so additional blind family-local tweaks are no longer the best use of the next round.","This round pivots to a new `multi_branch_gated` family to test a different encoder bias at the same K=128 anchor under the strongest current training recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `multi_branch_gated` produces a competitive proxy result, keep incubating it with family-specific branch-width or branch-allocation stabilization.","If it is clearly uncompetitive, deprioritize more multi-branch routing variants and consider a more radically different sparse mechanism next.","If quality is promising but runtime is poor, follow with a targeted performance pass rather than discarding the family immediately."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0011_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`two_stage_residual` remains a real K=128 win, but the front-loaded split change only matched the existing best point instead of extending the frontier, and its lower-K/width behavior still looks brittle. The next informative move is to pivot to a different non-gated family with a different inductive bias: a `multi_branch_gated` SAE that uses several gated encoder branches competing to explain different activation substructures before the final TopK selection, which could preserve the K=128 quality gains while avoiding the narrow tuning sensitivity of the staged-residual prototype.","summary":"Patch the existing `multi_branch_gated` prototype under `sparsify/` so the planned proxy comparison at K=128 can instantiate and run under the current signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"unblock_run","family_name":"multi_branch_gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stays narrowly focused on the concrete blocker: `multi_branch_gated` was missing from architecture validation and SAE factory dispatch, so training crashed before startup. The patch adds registration plus a minimal runnable implementation, and a local instantiate plus forward/backward check passed.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"multi_branch_gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 for round 11 fixed the concrete startup blocker by registering `multi_branch_gated` in config validation and SAE factory dispatch.","Added a minimal `MultiBranchGatedSparseCoder` implementation in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`; local instantiate plus forward/backward sanity passed."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `multi_branch_gated` run now completes and shows competitive proxy FVU, continue the original incubation plan for this family.","If the next failure is another concrete implementation bug, continue repair mode without changing the experiment target.","If the run completes but is slow, consider a later performance-focused follow-up rather than abandoning the family immediately."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
