research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0007_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Recent alternative families remain well behind gated at K=128, so the next informative move is a genuinely different encoder structure rather than another local sweep. A new `two_stage_residual` SAE that allocates the same total K across a coarse sparse pass and a residual sparse pass may recover more variance at fixed sparsity by turning single-shot TopK selection into staged residual reconstruction.","summary":"Patch the existing `two_stage_residual` prototype under `sparsify/` so the planned proxy comparison at K=128 can instantiate and run under the current best signum/EF=16/aux-free recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"unblock_run","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair stays narrowly focused on the concrete blocker: `two_stage_residual` was missing from architecture validation and factory dispatch, so training crashed before startup. The patch adds the architecture registration plus a minimal runnable implementation, and a local forward/backward instantiate check passed.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair attempt 1 for round 7 fixed the concrete startup blocker by registering `two_stage_residual` in config validation and SAE factory dispatch.","Added a minimal `TwoStageResidualSparseCoder` implementation in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`; local instantiate plus forward/backward sanity passed."],"next_hypotheses":["If the repaired `two_stage_residual` run now completes and shows promising proxy FVU, continue the original incubation plan for this family.","If the next failure is another concrete implementation bug, continue repair mode without changing the experiment target.","If the run completes but is slow, consider a later performance-focused follow-up rather than abandoning the family immediately."],"primary_variable":"code_fix"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0056.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The repeated failure of low-rank residual, batch-global, adaptive-budget, and bucketed routing at `K=40`, `EF=8` suggests the current small-EF lower-K bottleneck may be the hard TopK support mechanism itself rather than routing structure. `jumprelu` is the next fundamentally different same-EF comparison because it changes the sparse activation rule without requiring code edits this round.","summary":"Run a proxy same-EF architecture comparison at `K=40`, `EF=8` with `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu`, holding `signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0` fixed to test whether a different sparse activation mechanism improves the lower-K frontier where several TopK-style small-EF families have failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the round on a fundamentally different architecture path under the same lower-K and same-EF comparison target, avoids reopening minor parameter sweeps, and directly tests whether the main failure mode is the TopK mechanism itself. The main risk is that `jumprelu` also underperforms badly at `K=40`, but that would further support that the current small-EF lower-K regime is fundamentally misaligned and may require a broader reformulation rather than more local search.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 55 showed `bucketed_topk` is also weak at `K=40`, `EF=8` (`val_fvu=0.36289801076054573`), so conditional norm-bucket routing does not rescue the current lower-K small-capacity regime.","Next severe-stagnation move is a same-EF comparison with a genuinely different sparse activation mechanism: test `jumprelu` at `K=40`, `EF=8` while holding optimizer and training recipe fixed."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is competitive in proxy, promote it to full before any family-local tuning.","If `jumprelu` at `K=40`, `EF=8` is also clearly weak, treat the current `K=40`, `EF=8` search cluster as broadly exhausted and pivot next to a more radical architecture or objective reformulation rather than another minor variant."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
