research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0095.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`batch_topk` at the exact active point `K=40, EF=12` was decisively weak, so the next informative move is another fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than more residual-family or discrete-trunk tuning. Running `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged `signum`/`lr=1.6e-3`/`auxk_alpha=0` recipe tests whether smoother thresholded support selection recovers low-K quality where routing, residual-VQ, two-code residual-VQ, and batch-budget allocation all failed.","summary":"Run a proxy mainline comparison for `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` with the unchanged recipe. This stays in the exact active low-K neighborhood, uses the default same-EF comparison band, satisfies the stagnation requirement to try a fundamentally different architecture approach, and reopens a previously archived non-TopK sparsity mechanism instead of creating yet another incubating family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"architecture_signal","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"mainline_comparison","self_review":"This keeps the test fair at the same `(K=40, EF=12)` point and changes only architecture. It also follows the strategic pressure to avoid minor retuning and to prefer a structurally different mechanism while not expanding the incubating-family count further.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"40"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 94: `batch_topk` at `K=40, EF=12` was very weak at `0.40311281383037567`, substantially behind the local `lowrank_residual` best `0.17533555254340172`, so the batch-budget hypothesis did not help in the exact low-K neighborhood.","Given the growing incubating set, prefer reopening archived fundamentally different mechanisms with prior signal over starting another brand-new family.","The active low-K point `(K=40, EF=12)` has now rejected routing, two-code residual-VQ, and batch-budget allocation as local winners."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` at `K=40, EF=12` is competitive, keep the family fixed and map `K=32, EF=12` before touching EF.","If `jumprelu` is also weak at the exact active point, archive stale weak incubating families and consider that the current reconstruction-only search objective may be the flawed direction rather than the sparse mechanism alone.","If several distinct sparse-mechanism probes remain weak at `K=40, EF=12`, refocus the next architecture move on a stronger problem reformulation rather than another local mechanism swap."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/12_20260323_013532/logs/agent_action_0021.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_residual` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` improved both K=64 and K=32, so the next clean stabilization move is to complete this capacity sweep at the quality anchor. Increasing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 16 to 32 at K=128 may further lower FVU on the best-quality point if the residual branch is still capacity-limited there.","summary":"Run a proxy `lowrank_residual` stabilization pass at `K=128` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32`, keeping the rest of the winning recipe fixed (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This closes the family-specific capacity sweep across the tested K values.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This keeps one variable isolated and follows the strongest available stabilization signal: EF=32 has already helped at lower K, so K=128 is the remaining missing point in the same coherent sweep. The main risk is that K=128 is already saturated at EF=16 and EF=32 only increases cost, but finishing this axis is higher value than switching to aux before the capacity pattern is complete.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"32"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"HOOKPOINTS","value":"layers.[3].self_attn.o_proj"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 21 completes the `EXPANSION_FACTOR=32` stabilization sweep for `lowrank_residual` by testing the remaining anchor at K=128.","Because EF=32 already improved full frontier pose,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 98's code-edit hypothesis was policy-rejected, so round 99 should return to env-only experiments.","The most valuable unresolved frontier question is whether the routed soft-codebook family also owns the K=32 EF=12 slot under the pinned winning recipe.","A K=32 routed confirmation would extend the routed family farther down the Pareto frontier and strengthen it as the main EF=12 backbone."],"next_hypotheses":["If routed wins at K=32, run the same fixed recipe at K=24 to test whether the routed advantage extends one more step into the smaller-K regime.","If routed is very close but does not win at K=32, keep plain `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=32 and shift follow-up effort to K=24 or K=64 cleanup instead of more K=32 repeats.","If routed clearly loses at K=32, conclude that the routed advantage starts above this band and keep the family focused on K>=64 plus the established K=16 slot."],"primary_variable":"k"}
