research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0039.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 38 cleanly reproduced the `gated` anchor at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3` with the same still-improving late curve, while the only prior LR callback (`1.2e-3`) was uniformly worse. The next single question is therefore whether the current recipe is slightly underdriven rather than overdriven: does a modest LR increase to `2.0e-3` improve the full training trajectory and beat the refreshed anchor?","summary":"Continue on the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active family, respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and changes exactly one core variable: `lr`. It also follows the prescribed order now that the clean baseline has been backfilled successfully. The main risk is that `2.0e-3` could overdrive training, but the evidence so far points the other way: `1.2e-3` was clearly slower/worse, and the refreshed `1.6e-3` baseline was still improving late.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 confirmed the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the anchor almost exactly and still shows late improvement, so baseline reproducibility is no longer the blocker.","Round 39 reopens the LR axis cleanly on the same `gated` mainline by testing an upward callback to `LR=2.0e-3` after the earlier downward callback to `1.2e-3` was uniformly worse."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` improves the trajectory or final FVU while remaining stable, run one final nearby LR confirmation before moving on to optimizer or K.","If `gated` at `LR=2.0e-3` is noisier or worse than the refreshed control, lock `LR=1.6e-3` as the gated mainline anchor and move to the next prescribed recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0093.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed soft-codebook two-stage family has now improved both `K=8` and `K=16`, so the next highest-value test is whether the same routing advantage extends to `K=24`, where the current frontier is still owned by the non-routed variant.","summary":"Run one parameter-only follow-up at `K=24` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This cleanly maps whether the new family is becoming the dominant low/mid-K backbone rather than a narrow win at only `K=8` and `K=16`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This is a straightforward exploitation step with a single changed dimension (`K`). It directly follows the observed frontier gains and avoids unnecessary code churn. The main risk is that routing helps only in tighter-budget regimes and may become neutral or harmful by `K=24`, but that is precisely what this run will resolve.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["r93 should extend the routed soft-codebook family sweep to `K=24` after frontier wins at `K=8` and `K=16`.","Keep the recipe fixed and change only `K` so the result cleanly measures whether routing remains helpful in the mid-K regime.","A `K=24` win would strongly suggest the routed soft-codebook family is the new EF=12 backbone across multiple frontier slots."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` wins at `K=24`, test it at `K=32` under the same recipe to see whether routing can displace the current high end of the EF=12 frontier as well.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=24`, consider a small routed-temperature adjustment as the first targeted tuning step for this family.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, conclude that the routed advantage likely tops out by `K=16` and focus future routed-family work on low-K slots only."],"primary_variable":"k"}
