research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0170.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"matched_probe","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` with `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` fixed. Final reconstruction formula is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk library, `{c_m}` is a static soft-codebook library, and `{b_i}` is a static residual dictionary. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export it as one trunk lookup plus one codebook lookup plus one sparse residual lookup over fixed vector libraries; the online path remains finite weighted sums over static libraries. At EF=2 its encoder selection cost stays within the `≤ 1.5×h×n` hard budget and is materially lower than the current two-stage soft-codebook mainline. The single question is whether dropping the second residual refinement stage preserves enough quality and runtime efficiency to remain worth continuing as a cheaper LUTurbo-compatible branch, or whether the second stage is clearly necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` is clearly worse than the two-stage mainline in both FVU and runtime metrics, close this parent branch for the current low-EF regime and return to `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round.","If it is modestly worse in FVU but materially better in throughput or total runtime, keep it as a cheaper compatible Pareto branch, but still return to the mainline next round per probe policy.","If it is unexpectedly very close to the mainline at lower selection cost, allow at most one later family-specific follow-up after the required return to the mainline."],"notes_to_memory":["Compatibility: `扩展兼容`. Export path is static trunk library + static soft-codebook library + static residual dictionary; no decoder branch depends on dynamic weights.","This round is a strict matched architecture probe: keep `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=2`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.0e-3` explicitly pinned, and change only `ARCHITECTURE`.","Evaluate with `tokens_per_sec`, total duration, and `final_total_tokens` alongside FVU, because LUTurbo cares about total online/runtime cost rather than FVU alone; a tiny quality change with slower runtime is negative."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"This obeys the single-variable rule by changing only `architecture` and explicitly pinning the current mainline recipe fields. After the recent asymmetric, gated, and jumprelu probes failed to pressure the mainline, the highest-value remaining matched probe is the strongest cheaper parent `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`: it preserves the same formula class except for removing the second residual stage, stays within the EF=2 budget, and directly tests whether that extra stage is actually earning its cost in the current deployable regime. The main risk is limited novelty because this family is already known historically, but it is still the cleanest remaining architecture-worthiness question under the forced probe policy.","summary":"Run one valid matched architecture probe on `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping the `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, `LR=3.0e-3` mainline recipe fixed. This cleanly tests whether the cheaper one-stage soft-codebook parent is still worth continued attention under LUTurbo-compatible low-EF constraints.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0057.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After 21 no-improve rounds and failures from plain top-k, routed, gated, bucketed, discrete, and low-rank branches at `K=24`, the next severe-stagnation move should test a fundamentally different input-space transformation rather than another support-allocation variant. `whitened_topk` at `K=24, EF=12` may improve mid-K reconstruction by making the activation space easier to sparsify before hard selection, potentially recovering a better FVU/K tradeoff than the recent untransformed baselines.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `whitened_topk` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows severe-stagnation policy by trying another genuinely different built-in family instead of any scalar sweep or code repair, while keeping the experiment anchored on the frontier-relevant mid-K slot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"whitened_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided more support-selection and low-rank variants because those mechanisms have already failed repeatedly in this stagnation phase. `whitened_topk` is a cleaner architecture jump: it changes the input representation rather than the sparsity rule, while keeping the round architecture-only with all recipe fields pinned.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"whitened_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 57 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a pure `whitened_topk` architecture test after plain `topk` also failed badly at K=24.","Keep the run pinned at `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` so architecture is the only primary variable.","`whitened_topk` tests whether input-space normalization/preconditioning helps the mid-K regime more than the recent untransformed support-selection, low-rank, and discrete families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `whitened_topk` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test it at K=16 to see whether preconditioning helps more under tighter sparsity.","If `whitened_topk` clearly loses at K=24, retire this preconditioned branch and move to another genuinely different built-in family rather than any scalar sweep.","If `whitened_topk` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0236.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"LR","value":"0.0027"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；在线侧只做单样本 top-k 选择与系数计算，部署侧仍是单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 reference_round=r223 只改一个 env 参数 `LR=0.0027`，保持 `ARCHITECTURE=topk`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`K=248`、`OPTIMIZER=signum`、`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 及其余配置不变，测试在约 0.49x 总成本、当前最强 `<0.5x` 低开销锚点上，略微收缩 signum 步长能否改善 late-stage 收敛，把 FVU 压到低于 0.14621。选择这一步而不是继续推进 `jumprelu` 或 `codebook_topk`，是因为 r234 已给出“极小质量收益伴随异常总时长”的负面系统信号，而 r235 则在约 0.38x 处同时暴露出明显更差质量与更长总时长；在最近新 family 连续不给正信号的情况下，回到最短选择链路、最强低成本直兼容锚点做一次对称的保守 LR probe，信息价值更高且归因更干净。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `topk@EF1,K248,LR=0.0027` 继续降低 FVU，且 `tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens` 没有明显恶化，则相对本轮继续做一次严格 param_only clean repeat，确认这是否是 `<0.5x` 区域新的默认锚点。","如果 FVU 基本持平或回退，则关闭 `topk@K248` 的 LR 微调线，结论回到 `LR=0.003` 已是当前低开销 topk 主线的更合理设置。","如果质量小幅改善但运行明显更慢，则按运行时优先级将其记为负面系统信号，不把该配方升格为主线前沿点。"],"notes_to_memory":["r234 的 `jumprelu@K248,bandwidth=0.025` 虽把 FVU 压到 0.14545，但总时长升到 899s，应视为明显负面系统信号；后续不宜继续在该线做密集微调。","r235 的 `codebook_topk@K32` 在约 0.38x 成本处给出 FVU=0.3161，且总时长 628s，说明单 coarse codebook 低成本线当前实现没有形成可用前沿。","在最近新 family 连续失利后，当前更高信息量的问题是：当前最强 `<0.5x` 直兼容锚点是否仍有纯 recipe 侧的小幅可压缩空间，而不是继续开启更复杂但大概率无效的新结构。","评估本轮必须同时比较 `val_fvu`、`tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens`；若只是极小质量变化但运行更慢，应直接视为负面信号。"],"reference_round":223,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对 r223 只改 `LR`，不联动 architecture、K、EF、optimizer、AUXK_ALPHA 或任何新参数。主要风险是把步长降到 `0.0027` 后在固定 token 预算内反而收敛不足；但在 `0.0036` 已被证明偏激进、而多个新 low-cost family 又连续失利的背景下，这是当前最小、最可解释、且完全留在 `<0.5x` 主战区内的下一步。","summary":"相对 r223 的 `topk@EF1,K248` 做一次严格 param_only 保守步长 probe，仅设置 `LR=0.0027`，验证当前最强 `<0.5x` 直兼容锚点是否还能在不改变成本的前提下继续压低 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0060.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A conditional mixture of residual dictionaries may recover the mid-K lane where fixed residual mechanisms have stalled: `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` keeps the strong low-rank trunk, then lets a learned sample-level router mix several residual scoring branches before final top-k selection, potentially matching heterogeneous residual regimes better than a single encoder.","summary":"Added a new prototype family, `lowrank_multi_branch_residual`, in `sparsify/` and registered it in config/factory dispatch. The architecture applies the existing low-rank trunk first, then mixes three residual encoder branches with a learned sample-level routing head before sparse selection. Exact smoke test passed for `architecture=lowrank_multi_branch_residual, K=24, EF=12`, and a quick encode comparison confirmed behavior differs from `lowrank_residual`. This is a fundamentally different conditional-dictionary architecture for severe-stagnation recovery, not a scalar or K sweep.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_multi_branch_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by introducing a new mechanism family rather than tuning previous losers. The experiment remains architecture-only at the pinned `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` recipe, so attribution stays clean. Main risk: the earlier plain `multi_branch_gated` baseline failed badly, so the gain depends on the low-rank trunk making branch specialization operate on an easier residual space rather than repeating that failure pattern.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_multi_branch_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Added new prototype architecture `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` that combines the existing low-rank trunk with a learned sample-level mixture of residual encoder branches before top-k selection.","Integration chain completed for `lowrank_multi_branch_residual`: config whitelist + `_get_sae_class()` dispatch + class implementation.","Exact smoke test passed for `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` at `K=24, EF=12` with forward/backward.","Quick behavioral diff check showed `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` encode output is observably different from `lowrank_residual` on the same random input."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` is competitive but slightly worse at `K=24`, test `K=16` to see whether conditional branch specialization helps more under tighter sparsity.","If `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` wins at `K=24`, follow with `K=32` to check whether the gain persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, retire the conditional-dictionary branch and move to a different mechanism family rather than tuning branch count or router details."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0088.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `lowrank_residual_vq`, `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, and `lowrank_gated_residual` all failed to pressure the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor, the most informative remaining matched architecture probe is `lowrank_grouped_residual`. It preserves the same low-rank trunk and static-vector export contract, but replaces full global residual selection with group-local winner selection, which is directly relevant to lowering LUTurbo's online selection cost while keeping the reconstruction as a finite weighted sum over a static library. If this grouped selector is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then grouped single-stage low-rank selection is not worth continuing in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_grouped_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable: `architecture`. The mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe remains fixed, and I am not coupling this with any extra `group_topk_size` change. `lowrank_grouped_residual` is a better LUTurbo-aligned probe than heavier soft-codebook or multi-branch variants because its grouped local competition could reduce online selection work rather than increase it. The risk is that constraining support selection to per-group winners may lose too much quality at K128 and simply confirm that the two-stage residual path is necessary.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 88 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_grouped_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for grouped local winner selection under the low-rank trunk; the question is whether cheaper support selection can stay close enough to the mainline quality to merit future consideration.","Do not open another new family next round; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline after this probe regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, discard it and resume mainline tuning on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` next round.","If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a viable lower-selection-cost branch but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
