research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0055.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 54 completed the Hadamard-anchor LR localization: both adjacent callbacks around the current `gated@128` recipe (`LR=2.4e-3` in Round 53 and `LR=1.6e-3` in Round 54) stayed healthy but finished slightly worse than the `LR=2.0e-3` anchor, so the signum LR branch is now closed again. The next single question in the prescribed mainline order is therefore optimizer under the strengthened recipe: with `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, does swapping `signum` to `adam` now produce a healthier curve or competitive FVU, or does `gated` still clearly prefer `signum` even after preprocess improved conditioning?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` mainline and return to the current family reference point. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`. Judge this run by the full trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `adam` now avoids the old mid-training blow-up and finishes competitively against the `0.142923` signum anchor, it earns exactly one LR callback on the same Hadamard recipe next; if it is flatter, noisier, or clearly worse again, lock `signum` as the optimizer for the strengthened `gated` mainline and stop the optimizer branch.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `optimizer`. It also follows the requested sequence cleanly: the Hadamard-enabled signum anchor now has a completed local LR bracket, so the most informative remaining mainline question is whether the improved conditioning changes the optimizer verdict before revisiting loss, preprocess, or any K movement.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 54 showed that lowering the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor from `LR=2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` does not beat the current best: the run remained healthy but finished slightly worse at `0.143790`, so the signum LR branch is localized and should now be treated as closed around `2.0e-3`.","Round 55 should isolate the optimizer question on the strengthened `gated` anchor by testing `OPTIMIZER=adam` at fixed `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`, evaluating curve shape as much as endpoint."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated+adam` on the Hadamard-enabled anchor is competitive or better with a healthier curve, run exactly one Adam LR callback next on the same recipe.","If `gated+adam` is clearly worse again, keep `signum` as the optimizer for the strengthened `gated` mainline and move on to the next prescribed recipe axis."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0065.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"With the `gated` mainline stalled for twelve rounds and recent single-stage selector probes (`group_topk`, `bucketed_topk`, `codebook_topk`) all failing to beat it, the next highest-value matched architecture probe is `two_stage_residual`: it remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over static libraries, but distributes the fixed `K=128` budget across two sequential residual passes. This round answers one question only: under the matched `signum`/`LR=2.0e-3`/`EF=12` recipe, is that staged residual decomposition intrinsically strong enough to justify any later follow-up, or should it be ruled out immediately.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `two_stage_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 65 policy by changing exactly one primary variable: architecture. `two_stage_residual` is a more informative remaining probe than batch-coupled top-k variants because it stays single-sample deployable, and it tests a distinct multi-stage static-library decomposition that is closer to LUTurbo's lookup-plus-selective-compensation execution model than another small selector tweak.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 65 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `two_stage_residual` after recent single-stage selector variants all underperformed matched `gated`.","`two_stage_residual` is extended-compatible with LUTurbo because its final reconstruction can be exported as the sum of two fixed-size sparse weighted sums over static decoder libraries, with a fixed stage split of the total `K`.","Judge this probe strictly as a family-worthiness test against matched `gated` K128: if it is clearly worse, discard it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, record the result but still return to the mainline per policy."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` is clearly worse than matched `gated`, discard the family and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","If `two_stage_residual` is roughly competitive, record it as a possible staged lookup-plus-compensation direction but still return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy.","If `two_stage_residual` unexpectedly beats matched `gated`, schedule at most one later follow-up after the mandated return to the `gated` mainline."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
