research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0097.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed soft-codebook two-stage family has now improved the frontier through `K=96`, so the next clean step is to complete the high-K map at `K=128` and determine whether the same architecture also becomes the strongest high-quality anchor.","summary":"Run one parameter-only follow-up at `K=128` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This completes the allowed high-K sweep for the current winning family and establishes whether `K=128` is another non-dominated routed point or whether `K=96` is already the better tradeoff.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This is a straightforward exploitation step with only `K` changed, and it follows directly from repeated wins at `K=64` and `K=96`. Running `K=128` now is justified because `K=96` already captured the smaller-K tradeoff; the open question is whether the family also owns the top-quality anchor. The main risk is that the gain from `96` to `128` may be too small to justify the extra K, but measuring that is exactly the point of this round.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["r97 should extend `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to `K=128` after frontier improvements at `K=64` and `K=96`.","The `K=96` point already serves the smaller-K high-quality tradeoff, so `K=128` should now be measured to complete the family map at the top anchor.","Keep all recipe fields fixed and change only `K` to isolate whether the routed soft-codebook advantage reaches the `K=128` endpoint."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` wins at `K=128`, treat it as the new primary EF=12 backbone across the explored K range and begin targeted cleanup sweeps on the most valuable anchors.","If it is only marginally better than `K=96`, prefer the `K=96` point as the stronger Pareto tradeoff and start targeted tuning from there.","If it clearly loses at `K=128`, conclude that the family peaks below the maximum K and prioritize follow-up work around `K=96` instead of chasing the largest anchor."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0169.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0175.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under the mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, where the bucket gate only changes stage-1/2 selector scores and all decoded terms still come from static libraries `{U,V}`, codebook `C`, and residual dictionary `B`. This is `扩展兼容` with a clean LUTurbo export path, but the matched EF=2 selector is likely not worth continuing because bucketed dual scorers raise encoder selection cost to about `2.5x h×n`, so the policy should reject it before spending a long training run.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune one cost knob at a time (`TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`) to improve the feasible Pareto point without changing architecture.","If a future bucketed revisit is desired, only do it as a cost-reduction study on the bucketed family itself with primary variable `TRUNK_RANK` or `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`, not as another matched-architecture probe."],"notes_to_memory":["`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: bucket mixing changes selector-side scoring only; decode remains a finite weighted sum over static trunk/codebook/residual libraries.","At matched `K=128, EF=2`, the bucketed two-stage soft-codebook family estimates to about `selection_cost=2.5x` and is therefore over the `1.5x` hard budget; this makes it a likely fast policy-reject probe rather than a training candidate."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: architecture is the only changed dimension, while `K/EF/optimizer/LR` are pinned to the mainline recipe. I am choosing an intentionally decisive probe: it is informative even if rejected, because the low-EF budget constraint is now the main gate and this family is known to be runtime-heavier. This does not claim the family is universally bad; it only answers whether it is worth continuing on the current feasible low-cost frontier.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` with the mainline recipe unchanged otherwise. The family is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) via a static trunk library plus static codebook and residual dictionaries, but its matched EF=2 selector cost is expected to exceed budget (`~2.5x h×n`), so the likely result is a cheap policy rejection that cleanly answers: this architecture is not worth continuing as a low-cost mainline candidate right now.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0095.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0017.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 16 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=32` did not collapse and still maintained a smooth late-stage FVU descent, so the next single question is whether LUTurbo can push cost one more notch lower before quality degradation becomes too steep. This round changes only `K`, moving from `32` to `24` while keeping the same family and recipe fixed, to measure the next deployable point on the low-K cost-quality frontier.","summary":"Continue the active topk low-K lane: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `32` to `24` to test whether the frontier still extends to a cheaper decomposition without an unacceptable reconstruction jump.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active mainline family, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` rule, and follows directly from the observed K-lane evidence. The main risk is that `K=32 -> 24` may cross the practical quality boundary, but the K32 curve still improved smoothly through the end, so a finer step to `24` is more defensible than jumping straight to `16`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 15 (`K=64`) reached `FVU=0.19926`; round 16 (`K=32`) reached `FVU=0.24943`, so the low-K frontier is still valid but degradation is now material.","The `K=32` run kept a smooth late descent instead of flattening early, which suggests the recipe is capacity-limited rather than unstable and justifies one finer K step before declaring the boundary.","For LUTurbo, this lane is valuable because it directly probes lower online selection and weighted-sum cost under a fixed export-compatible topk recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=24` remains reasonably close to `K=32`, continue once more to `K=16` to locate the practical minimum deployable point.","If `K=24` degrades sharply or the late curve flattens much earlier, treat `K=32` as the current low-K boundary for this recipe.","If `K=24` is borderline, compare it against `K=32` as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 quality anchor alone."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0059.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the matched `topk` probe came back only slightly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, the next highest-value single architecture question is whether a simpler export-compatible scoring path can retain most of the quality while offering a cheaper route for online selection and coefficient computation. `factorized_topk` keeps the same static-dictionary finite weighted-sum reconstruction form as `topk/gated`, but replaces direct latent scoring with a low-rank mixing stage before top-k selection, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `factorized_topk` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a LUTurbo-oriented family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `factorized_topk`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `factorized_topk`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `factorized_topk` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its low-rank scoring path may better match LUTurbo's total online-cost target; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 59 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `factorized_topk` is a stronger LUTurbo-oriented probe than opening another heavier residual family because it preserves the same export contract while plausibly reducing support-scoring complexity; the main risk is that reusing the `gated`-tuned recipe understates its ceiling, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 58 showed that matched `topk` under the strengthened `gated` recipe is only modestly worse (`0.146999` vs `0.142923`), so simpler export-compatible architectures remain worth probing when the `gated` mainline stalls.","`factorized_topk` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the final reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to a low-rank scoring stage before top-k support selection.","Round 59 should judge `factorized_topk` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `factorized_topk` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `factorized_topk` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its scoring path may align better with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `factorized_topk` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0109.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 107 and 108 now make `LR=2.4e-3` the reproducible best signum setting for `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=128` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, so the next single mainline question is optimizer choice. Testing `OPTIMIZER=adam` on that settled recipe will show whether this family's remaining limitation is optimization dynamics rather than signum step size, and the decision should be based on the whole curve shape versus the archived signum anchor, not just the endpoint.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `OPTIMIZER` from `signum` to `adam`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=2.4e-3` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after localizing the signum LR branch: same family, same `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` pinned, and exactly one primary variable changes. The main risk is that `adam` may want a different LR than `signum`, but this first optimizer comparison is still the correct isolated question before spending any round on an optimizer-local LR callback.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 109 opens the optimizer branch for the confirmed `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 mainline after `signum` with `LR=2.4e-3` reproduced the best curve and endpoint.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the settled signum anchor at `K=128`, `EF=12`, `LR=2.4e-3`, especially whether `adam` is smoother or more competitive through mid and late training rather than only comparing final FVU.","If `adam` is promising, it earns exactly one optimizer-local LR callback next; if it is clearly worse or unstable, keep `signum` and move on to loss or preprocess before touching `K`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adam` is competitive with or better than signum at `LR=2.4e-3`, give `adam` exactly one LR callback next within `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `adam` is clearly worse or unstable at `LR=2.4e-3`, keep `signum` as the optimizer and move to the next single-axis mainline recipe question before touching `K`.","Do not change loss, preprocess, or architecture until the optimizer branch is cleanly resolved."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0027.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0054.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 53 answered only the upward side of the re-opened LR question on the Hadamard-strengthened `gated` anchor: `LR=2.4e-3` stayed healthy but finished slightly worse than the current `0.142923` best, so the remaining single question is whether the new preprocess actually wants a smaller step size instead of a larger one. With `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, does lowering `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` improve the full curve, or does `2.0e-3` remain the best shared mainline setting even after preprocess changed conditioning?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`, anchored on the current family reference point so it remains policy-clean. It also follows the requested mainline sequencing better than opening a new family or retuning K again: after the Hadamard-enabled anchor rejected the upward LR callback at `2.4e-3`, the most informative remaining single question is the symmetric downward callback before declaring the LR axis settled.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 53 showed that on the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` anchor, raising `LR` to `2.4e-3` does not improve over `LR=2.0e-3`; the curve stayed healthy but the endpoint regressed slightly to `0.143811` versus the `0.142923` anchor.","Round 54 should isolate the remaining LR question on the same strengthened anchor by testing the downward callback to `LR=1.6e-3` at fixed `gated`, `K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves the Hadamard-enabled `gated@128` curve or endpoint, adopt it as the new anchor or run one tight confirmation before revisiting other axes.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is also worse or uniformly slower, close the LR branch and keep `LR=2.0e-3` as the shared mainline recipe before considering any further family-local recipe work."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
