research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0066.json:56:      "Keep all recipe fields pinned explicitly to avoid launcher drift: `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=8`, `EF=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0113.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0122.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.7e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j，其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此可映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。当前 family 在 EF=2 时 selection_cost 约 1.25x，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束；r121 将 LR 从 3.0e-3 下调到 2.4e-3 后 FVU 变差，说明降幅可能过大，本轮只把 LR 调到 2.7e-3，测试是否能在保持预算与架构不变的前提下取得比 2.4e-3 更好的收敛，同时避免 3.0e-3 可能的轻微优化噪声。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 2.7e-3 仍不优于 3.0e-3，则 signum 的 LR 轴可视为基本洗净，下一轮切到 optimizer 并联动 LR。","若 2.7e-3 曲线优于 2.4e-3 但仍略逊 3.0e-3，可将 3.0e-3 视为当前 signum 最优点并停止继续细扫 LR。","若 K=128 相对 K=96 的 FVU 优势不足以覆盖更高 deploy 成本，再回到 K 轴做系统性价比比较。"],"notes_to_memory":["family 不变，兼容性仍为扩展兼容，导出路径不变：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + residual 字典库。","本轮继续严格单变量，只测 LR 中间点 2.7e-3，用于判断 r121 的退化是否来自 LR 下调过度。","评估时需同时记录 FVU、总耗时、tokens_per_sec、final_total_tokens，区分是训练更短还是吞吐变化带来的时间差。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守了单变量原则，并按当前策略顺序继续在主线 family 上完成 LR 轴细化。风险是 LR 轴可能已经接近饱和，但 2.7e-3 是由 r121 结果直接导出的最小可解释补点，优先级仍高于过早切 optimizer。","summary":"继续围绕预算内主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 做学习率补点：固定 K=128、EF=2、signum，仅把 LR 设为 2.7e-3，判断 2.4e-3 的退化是否因降得过低。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0028.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0205.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"smaller_k","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 b_i 来自单个静态向量库；factorized scorer 仅用于在线打分与选址，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时仍是单库查表加权求和，因此属于直接兼容。基于 r204 已在 K=64、EF=2 下拿到 0.44x / 0.3013 的 <0.5x 点，本轮继续保持 architecture、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，仅将 K 从 64 下探到 32，预计 deployment cost 可由约 0.06x 进一步降到约 0.03x，使 total_cost 约落在 0.41x，补全更低成本端覆盖，并检验该 family 在更短查表链路下的 FVU 退化斜率。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 K=32 仍保持可接受 FVU，可继续在 factorized_topk 上单变量下探 FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM，争取把 encoder cost 也往下压。","如果 K=32 的 FVU 退化过大，则保留 K=64 作为 <0.5x 主点，并转去 topk 或 lowrank_residual 的低成本对照以补前沿形状。"],"notes_to_memory":["factorized_topk 在 LUTurbo 链路中可直接导出为单静态字典的 top-k 查表加权和，兼容性稳定，不因 scorer factorization 改变 decoder 形式。","本轮继续只改 K，沿 deployment 成本轴下探，避免把 encoder 降本与 lookup 降本混在一起。"],"primary_variable":"k","self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则，目标明确指向 <0.5x 区域扩点。主要风险是 K=32 可能把 FVU 推高过快，但这正是当前低开销 regime 需要量化的 tradeoff。","summary":"在直接兼容 family factorized_topk 上做单变量低开销下探：固定 EF=2、signum、LR=3e-3，仅把 K 从 64 降到 32，目标是把 total_cost 从 0.44x 进一步压到约 0.41x，并补全 <0.5x Pareto 前沿的更低部署成本端。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0126.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0038.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `gated` mainline has already shown smooth, still-improving curves at `K=128`, `K=96`, and `K=64`, but Round 38 should first fill the missing clean-baseline step in the prescribed order. Re-running the exact `gated` reference recipe with all reference aux/runtime knobs explicitly pinned answers one question only: does the true anchor still reproduce a clean curve under the current stack before we spend another round on lower `K` or renewed recipe tuning?","summary":"Run a clean control on the current `gated` mainline reference recipe. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=1.6e-3`, and explicitly lock the known reference aux/runtime settings so the next comparison is grounded in a fresh, fully specified anchor curve. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just terminal FVU: recent `gated` runs at `K=96` and `K=64` were still improving late, so we need a refreshed `K=128` control before deciding whether to continue down the K ladder or revisit LR.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the EF=12 constraint, and avoids opening a new branch. It also repairs the sequencing gap in the current mainline by adding the missing clean baseline before any further K move. The main risk is that it may not improve the frontier numerically, but right now the more important value is a fresh, comparable anchor curve for the next decision.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 38 backfills the missing clean-baseline step for the active `gated` mainline with the exact reference recipe explicitly pinned at `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=1.6e-3`.","Recent `gated` K sweeps at `K=96` and `K=64` both had smooth, still-improving curves, so a refreshed `K=128` control is needed before interpreting any further K descent or LR changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If the clean `gated@128` control reproduces the expected anchor with a healthy late curve, resume the K ladder and test `K=32` next to locate where `gated` stops beating `topk`.","If the refreshed baseline comes in materially different from the recorded anchor, treat baseline reproducibility as the immediate issue and avoid drawing more family-quality conclusions from the recent K sweep alone."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0163.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After another failed `K=24, EF=16` routed residual probe, the severe-stagnation policy still favors a fundamentally different existing architecture over more recipe tuning. `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is the most informative next candidate because bucketed specialization is the one structural motif that clearly helped the current frontier-winning backbone, and stripping away the two-stage soft-codebook machinery may reveal whether bucketing itself can produce a better small-K tradeoff at `K=24` under the fixed modern signum recipe.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `bucketed_lowrank_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed at the current signum baseline. This continues severe-stagnation recovery with a materially different existing family, targets the valuable `K=24` frontier slot, and tests whether the bucketing inductive bias remains useful without the multi-stage soft-codebook path.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean single-variable architecture probe and is more defensible than returning to optimizer or preprocessing tweaks after repeated misses. The risk is that removing the soft-codebook/two-stage path may give up too much capacity, but the bucketing mechanism has enough prior signal from the live frontier to justify one direct test in the current `K=24, EF=16` lane.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 163 continues severe-stagnation architecture search after routed low-rank two-stage residual also failed to improve the `K=24, EF=16` lane.","Hypothesis: `bucketed_lowrank_residual` isolates the bucketing bias that appears useful in the best current family while removing the failing two-stage soft-codebook machinery, making it the next most informative architecture-only probe at `K=24`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to test whether simpler bucketed residual coding extends further down the frontier.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed soft-codebook backbone, test another fundamentally different existing family at `K=24` rather than returning to scalar recipe tweaks.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, treat plain bucketed residual coding as noncompetitive in the current EF=16 regime and continue severe-stagnation search with the next distinct architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0086.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0013.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `signum` learning-rate sweep has now mapped a narrow optimum region around `1.7e-3` to `1.75e-3`, with no clear additional gain from pushing LR higher. This round changes only the loss-shaping axis by lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` from the current implicit baseline `0.03125` to `0.015625` while keeping `topk/signum/K128/EF12/LR=1.7e-3` fixed, to test whether a weaker auxiliary dead-feature pressure improves late-stage reconstruction once the main LR regime is already near its peak.","summary":"Stay on the `topk` mainline and move to the next recipe axis after LR refinement: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `LR=1.7e-3` fixed, and reduce `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.015625` to answer whether lighter auxiliary regularization yields a better training curve and lower final FVU.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the active family unchanged and modifies only one non-core recipe variable, which fits the single-variable rule and avoids the optimizer-callback policy trap encountered earlier. The risk is that lowering `AUXK_ALPHA` may weaken dead-feature management and hurt utilization, but at this stage the more important question is whether the current LR-tuned regime is now over-regularized in reconstruction terms.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.7e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.015625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["The signum LR sweep suggests the practical optimum is near `1.7e-3`; pushing to `1.75e-3` did not yield a meaningful additional gain.","With LR mostly mapped, the next clean single-variable question is whether current loss shaping is slightly over-constraining reconstruction.","Judge this round by full curve shape plus terminal FVU: if lower `AUXK_ALPHA` improves late descent without obvious instability, the mainline recipe should shift on the loss axis rather than continuing micro-LR sweeps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.015625` improves FVU and keeps the curve smooth, continue tuning aux loss strength within the same topk recipe.","If the lower aux weight hurts stability or feature health without improving reconstruction, revert to `0.03125` and treat LR-tuned signum as the current clean anchor.","If the effect is neutral, the topk mainline may be recipe-saturated at K=128 and the next useful step will be a K move once policy order permits."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0160.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0213.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"TRUNK_RANK","value":"16"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {u_r} 是静态 trunk 向量库，{b_i} 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算系数 beta_r 与 alpha_i，导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 时可拆成 trunk 库查表加权和与 residual 库查表加权和，两部分都满足静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此兼容性为扩展兼容。基于 r210 已在当前 family 上拿到 0.69x / 0.1256 且 tokens_per_sec 约 166.6k、总耗时 291s，当前最值得回答的单一问题不是再换 family，而是该点的高成本是否主要由 trunk 过宽导致；本轮仅将 TRUNK_RANK 下调到 16，测试能否在保持明显优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU 前提下，把 total_cost 尽量压向并最好压入 <0.5x 区域。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 进入 <0.5x 且 FVU 仍明显优于 topk@EF1,K64，则固定该 family 后只沿 K 轴补一个点。","如果 TRUNK_RANK=16 的 FVU 明显崩塌或训练代价没有进一步优势，则说明 lowrank_factorized_residual 在低开销区仍过度依赖 trunk 容量，后续应回到更短链路 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["r210 说明 lowrank_factorized_residual 在低 EF 下具备很强质量潜力，且运行吞吐优于近期 topk 线；当前主要矛盾是成本而非训练不稳。","TRUNK_RANK 同时影响 encoder 与 deployment 两侧成本，是把该 family 从 0.69x 拉回低开销区的最高信息量单变量旋钮。"],"primary_variable":"trunk_rank","self_review":"这轮严格只改一个主变量 trunk_rank，不再重复声明 K、EF、optimizer、LR，避免再次触发 param_only 的多主轴拒绝。选择 16 而不是 32，是因为目标是优先补 <0.5x 区域覆盖；更激进地下压 trunk 才更可能一次性把该高质量点推进到低开销前沿，但风险是 coarse trunk 表达会被过度削弱。","summary":"在扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual 上做一次低开销 param-only 探索：仅将 TRUNK_RANK 设为 16，验证能否以更小 trunk 库把当前 0.69x/0.1256 的高质量点推进到 <0.5x 区域。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0125.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A bucketed two-stage soft-codebook backbone may recover a better K=16 tradeoff under the fixed EF=16 regime by constraining competition locally, reducing the routing fragility seen in the routed variant while remaining more structured than the plain non-routed model.","summary":"The plain two-stage soft-codebook K=16 control nearly matched but did not beat the incumbent, and the recent optimizer/preprocessing tweaks were clear failures. Severe stagnation therefore calls for another fundamentally different existing architecture rather than more recipe perturbations. I am testing `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=16 with the stable signum recipe because it is the next most structurally distinct registered family that has already shown some promise at this slot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a legitimate architecture change under the severe-stagnation policy, not another minor tweak. The main risk is that EF=16 regime shift continues to suppress all K=16 candidates, but probing the bucketed family is still a cleaner next test than revisiting optimizer or preprocessing knobs again.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 125 continues severe-stagnation architecture exploration after Hadamard and Adam failed and the plain non-routed K=16 control only matched the incumbent.","`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is the next structurally distinct existing soft-codebook family worth probing at K=16 under fixed EF=16.","Keep the override set minimal so attribution stays on the bucketed architecture rather than another coupled recipe change."],"next_hypotheses":["If the bucketed K=16 result improves, follow with K=32 on the same family to test whether locality helps across the low-to-mid-K band under EF=16.","If the bucketed family also fails, move to another fundamentally different existing family rather than returning to optimizer or preprocessing tweaks on the same backbones.","If several architecture families cluster near the old K=16 anchor but none beat it under EF=16, treat fixed-EF regime shift as the dominant explanation and prioritize experiments that diagnose that regime explicitly."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0097.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 95 and 96 established a clean, repeatable `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` K128 baseline at `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next single mainline question is the first within-family learning-rate probe. Lowering `LR` to `1.6e-3` tests whether this asymmetric soft-codebook two-stage recipe is currently slightly underdamped and could trade a bit of early speed for better late-stage descent and a lower terminal FVU; the decision should come from the whole curve shape versus the archived baseline, not just the last point.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed sequence after a clean baseline repeat: stay on the same family, keep `K` and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and change exactly one primary variable, `lr`. The main risk is that `1.6e-3` may simply slow a recipe that is already well tuned at `2.0e-3`, but that is the highest-value first LR-localization question before opening the optimizer branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 97 is the first LR probe for the confirmed `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EF=12`, and `signum`.","Judge this run by the full trajectory against the archived `LR=2.0e-3` baseline, especially whether the lower step size improves late descent or only slows the whole curve.","If `LR=1.6e-3` regresses or converges too slowly, the next LR probe should return upward rather than continuing downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves endpoint or late-curve shape versus `2.0e-3`, archive it as the new mainline LR for `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly slower or worse, test only the symmetric upward probe at `LR=2.4e-3` next before opening the optimizer branch.","Do not change optimizer, loss, preprocess, or `K` until the signum LR bracket is localized."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
