research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0130.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual family has already produced non-dominated gains at K=16,24,32,64,96 under the fixed EF=16 signum recipe; running the same architecture at K=128 isolates the K-axis and tests whether the bucketed locality advantage extends to the high-K anchor, potentially replacing the old routed anchor with a better absolute-FVU backbone.","summary":"Run a parameter-only follow-up on bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual at K=128 with the same stabilized EF=16 signum recipe to map the high-K endpoint of the newly winning family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"promote_to_mainline","self_review":"This stays within the one-variable rule by changing only K on the current strongest family. It does not yet satisfy the operator hint to explore optimizer/loss/preprocessing, but it is the cleanest immediate frontier-closing measurement after the K=96 win.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 130 should close the K-axis map for bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual by testing K=128 under the same EF=16 signum recipe used for the recent K=16..96 wins.","Keep the override set minimal and fully explicit so attribution remains on K alone and avoids recipe drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If K=128 wins clearly, treat bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual as the new EF=16 backbone from mid-K through the anchor regime.","If K=128 is close but noisy relative to the prior anchor, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting it as default high-K choice.","If K=128 regresses, keep bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual as the low/mid-K winner and pivot the next round to optimizer or loss exploration on an existing high-K architecture."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0018.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 17 showed that `topk/signum/LR=1.6e-3/EF=12` at `K=24` still descended smoothly through the late phase rather than flattening early, so the current recipe appears capacity-limited but still stable. This round changes only `K`, moving from `24` to `16`, to answer whether LUTurbo can reach the next allowed lower-cost point before reconstruction degradation becomes clearly impractical.","summary":"Continue the active topk low-K frontier mapping: keep `ARCHITECTURE=topk`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed, and reduce `K` from `24` to `16` to test whether the deployable cost-quality frontier extends one more step down.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `topk` mainline, changes exactly one primary variable (`k`), respects the fixed `EF=12` and allowed-K constraints, and follows directly from the observed curve shape at `K=24`. The main risk is a steeper quality drop and higher dead-feature pressure at `K=16`, but `K=24` still showed smooth late improvement, so the next informative single question is whether the frontier boundary is at `K=16` or below `K=24`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 17 (`K=24`) reached `FVU=0.2722620368003845`, a modest degradation from `K=32`, and its late-phase slope remained negative instead of collapsing into an early plateau.","Compared with `K=32`, the `K=24` run showed higher `dead_pct` and `auxk` pressure in the late phase, suggesting capacity is getting tight, but the training dynamics still looked stable enough to justify one more K-only step.","For LUTurbo, this is still the most direct way to probe lower online selection and weighted-sum cost while staying within the same export-compatible topk recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=16` remains reasonably close to `K=24`, continue once more to `K=8` to locate the true lower boundary of the current recipe.","If `K=16` degrades sharply or late-phase improvement largely disappears, treat `K=24` or `K=32` as the practical low-K boundary for this topk/signum regime.","If `K=16` is borderline, compare it against `K=24` as a deployment tradeoff point rather than against the K128 anchor alone."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0067.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Rounds 65 and 66 established a clean, reproducible `two_stage_residual` mainline baseline at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, so the next highest-value single question is whether a modest learning-rate reduction improves late-stage convergence without giving up the strong early progress. This round tests only that: does lowering `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` produce a smoother or better `two_stage_residual` training curve under the same matched recipe.","summary":"Run a single learning-rate adjustment within the `two_stage_residual` mainline by keeping `ARCHITECTURE=two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, and changing only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"mainline_improvement","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the prescribed mainline order: the clean baseline has been confirmed, so the next step is a single LR test before touching optimizer, loss, or K. A modest LR reduction is the most interpretable first move because it probes whether the staged residual architecture is currently slightly underdamped near convergence rather than underpowered.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 67 is the first mainline recipe adjustment for `two_stage_residual` after the clean baseline repeat reproduced the Round 65 result.","Judge this run by curve shape as well as endpoint: the question is whether a slightly lower LR improves stability or late-stage descent relative to the archived `2.0e-3` baseline.","If `1.6e-3` is worse or simply slower everywhere, the next LR move should likely be upward rather than making more small downward steps."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` improves the endpoint or gives a cleaner descending curve, archive it as the new `two_stage_residual` mainline recipe.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is clearly worse or just slower than `2.0e-3`, revert to the archived baseline and test a modest LR increase next.","If the curve shape is mixed, keep optimizer fixed and use one more LR probe before considering any optimizer change."],"primary_variable":"learning_rate"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0054.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0210.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"1"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"候选 family: lowrank_factorized_residual。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_r beta_r u_r + Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 u_r 是静态 trunk 向量库，b_i 是静态 residual 向量库；在线侧只计算系数 beta_r 与 alpha_i，并在 LUTurbo/Lottable 端导出为两个静态向量库上的有限加权和，因此属于扩展兼容。r209 对 topk@EF1,K96 的继续加大查表预算被 policy 拦截，说明单纯沿 topk 的 K 轴上探不稳；本轮保持 K=64、EF=1、optimizer、LR 不变，只把 architecture 从 topk 切到 lowrank_factorized_residual，测试在仍瞄准 <0.5x 区域的前提下，加入极轻 low-rank trunk 与 factorized residual scorer 后，是否能显著优于 topk@0.31x 的 FVU。按现有成本表外推，该配置有希望落在低开销区或其边界附近，同时提供比纯单库 topk 更强的表达。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 lowrank_factorized_residual@EF1,K64 成功落入 <0.5x 且明显优于 topk@EF1,K64，则下一步固定该 family，单变量扫描 K 或 TRUNK_RANK，补齐低开销前沿。","如果该配置仍超出 <0.5x 或 FVU 改善有限，则说明低开销区需要更短链路而非增加 trunk 分支，下一步应回到 topk/factorized_topk 或探索更小静态库方案。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_factorized_residual 的导出形式是 trunk 静态库加 residual 静态库的有限加权和，满足 LUTurbo 扩展兼容约束。","本轮只改 architecture，保持 K=64 和 EF=1 不变，便于判断在同等低字典规模与相近 lookup 预算下，增加轻 trunk 是否值得。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"该提案遵守单变量原则，并直接回应 r209 的 policy_reject：不再继续沿 topk 的 K 轴加预算，而是测试更有信息量的新低成本 family。主要风险是 deployment 侧 trunk 成本可能把 total_cost 推到 0.5x 附近甚至略上，但这仍能为低开销区提供关键边界信号。","summary":"切换到扩展兼容的 lowrank_factorized_residual，固定 K=64、EF=1、signum、LR=3e-3，只改变 architecture，验证轻量 trunk+residual 结构能否在低开销区附近拿到明显优于 topk 的 FVU。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0076.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0225.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"候选 family: jumprelu。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；JumpReLU 只改变单样本在线侧的阈值化支持形成与系数计算，不改变 decoder 端的单库有限加权和形式，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。r223 已确认 `topk@EF1,K248` 的向上 LR 分支没有收益，r224 也确认 lowrank_factorized_residual 的 scorer 压缩在 <0.5x 目标区仍落后于同成本 topk；因此当前最有信息量的下一步，不是继续清洗已饱和 family 的 recipe，而是在不增加 total_cost 的前提下测试新的同成本 selector 机制。严格锚定 r222，只改一个 env 参数 `ARCHITECTURE=jumprelu`，保留 `EF=1,K=248,signum,LR=3.0e-3,AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 不变，验证 learned-threshold 支持塑形能否在相同 `total_cost≈0.49x` 下，把 <0.5x 区域 FVU 压到当前 topk 最佳 0.1462 以下，或者至少给出比 topk 更有希望的曲线形状而不拖慢训练。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `jumprelu@EF1,K248` 在相同 0.49x 成本下优于 `topk@K248` 的 FVU=0.1462，且 tokens_per_sec / duration_sec 没有明显恶化，则下一轮基于本轮做一次 clean repeat，确认它是否能成为新的 <0.5x 直接兼容锚点。","如果 `jumprelu` 与 topk 质量接近但运行代价更差，则将其仅记录为历史参考，不继续占用低开销主线轮次。","如果 `jumprelu` 明显差于 topk，则关闭这条 plain-selector thresholding 支线，下一轮转向另一条同成本或近邻成本的新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["本地 `selection_cost_estimate()` 显示 `jumprelu@EF1,K248` 与 `topk@EF1,K248` 的 combined_ratio 同为约 0.49x，因此这是一次纯 selector 机制比较，而不是成本变化导致的混杂实验。","r223 与 r224 分别对 topk recipe 继续清洗、以及 lowrank_factorized_residual scorer 压缩给出负面信号；当前应优先测试新的同成本 family，而不是继续沿这两条线做局部小修。","`jumprelu` 保持单静态库导出契约，属于直接兼容 family；若它也失败，则说明当前 <0.5x 区域里 plain single-library selector 的主导瓶颈更可能是表示容量而非支持塑形规则。"],"reference_round":222,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效参考轮 r222 只改 `ARCHITECTURE` 一个 env 参数，K、EF、optimizer、LR、AUXK_ALPHA 和所有运行时参数全部保持不变。选择 `jumprelu` 而不是继续回到 topk/group_topk，是因为它在历史上虽未成为主线，但比纯 grouped 竞争更接近“同成本下改变支持塑形”的独立问题，同时不会额外抬高部署或选择成本。","summary":"相对 r222 的 `topk@EF1,K248,AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` 做一次严格 param_only architecture probe，仅切换到 `jumprelu`，测试在相同 0.49x 成本下，阈值化支持塑形是否能把 <0.5x 前沿继续压低。","touched_files":[]}
