research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0047.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 46 answered the `K=64` transfer question positively: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) did not merely hold up, it materially improved the prior `gated@64` result and now owns the frontier at that support. The next single question is where this downward transfer breaks for LUTurbo-relevant cost reduction: if we keep the same improved recipe fixed and reduce only `K` to `32`, does `gated` remain competitive enough to establish a stronger lower-cost point, or does the family advantage collapse below the high-K regime?","summary":"Continue the active `gated` mainline and keep the improved recipe fixed: `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `K` from `64` to `32` to test whether the recipe improvement extends one more step down the allowed support ladder. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if training remains smooth and finishes clearly below the current `K=32` control (`0.249427`), then `gated` has earned a meaningful lower-cost foothold; if the curve degrades sharply or the endpoint lands near or above the control, treat the current `gated` advantage as largely confined to `K>=64`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_cost","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the active `gated` family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `K`. It follows the current mainline logic because the clean baseline, LR, optimizer, loss, and preprocess questions have already been resolved on this recipe, and the last two rounds showed successful transfer from `K=128` to `K=96` and then to `K=64`. The main risk is that `K=32` may sit beyond the range where the improved gating recipe is effective, but that is precisely the highest-value remaining single-variable question for mapping LUTurbo-relevant cost-quality tradeoffs.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 46 established that the improved `gated` recipe transfers beyond the `K=128` anchor: `gated@64` improved materially over the prior `K=64` result and now holds that frontier point.","Round 47 isolates the next cost-quality question by testing whether the same recipe remains effective at `K=32`, where LUTurbo online cost would drop further but support pressure becomes much tighter."],"next_hypotheses":["If improved `gated@32` clearly beats the existing `K=32` control with a healthy curve, continue once more to `K=24` under the same recipe to locate the next break point.","If `gated@32` fails to beat the control or shows clearly worse curve shape, stop the downward sweep and treat `K=64` as the lowest strong gated point under the current recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0042.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0135.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"architecture_value_signal","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_residual","family_stage":"matched_probe","hypothesis":"候选架构的最终重构公式为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i。low-rank trunk 基库 U 与 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 matched architecture probe 严格保持主线的 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，只把 architecture 改为更简单的 lowrank_residual，用来回答一个问题：在当前低 EF 可行区间内，soft codebook coarse branch 是否仍然必要，还是 low-rank trunk + 单阶段 residual 已足够形成更优的成本/时延权衡。该架构在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 约 0.62x h×n，低于当前主线的 1.25x，若 FVU 没有明显恶化且运行更快，则值得作为低成本备选继续保留。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 lowrank_residual 的 FVU 接近主线且吞吐更好，则说明当前 EF=2 下 coarse codebook 的边际收益有限，下一轮回到主线后应重新审视更简单 family 的成本优势。","若 lowrank_residual 明显劣于主线，则说明 soft codebook coarse branch 在低 EF 下仍然必要，下一轮回到 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 继续做成本轴微调。","若 lowrank_residual 介于主线与 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 之间且更快，可将其记为低成本备用点，但不替代当前最佳 FVU 主线。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮仍是单次 matched architecture probe，严格保持 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改 architecture。","lowrank_residual 为扩展兼容 family，且在 EF=2 下 selection_cost 明显低于当前两阶段主线，适合回答 coarse codebook 是否必要。","r134 的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual probe 被 policy_reject，因此本轮改用另一个已知兼容且更低成本的父节点进行架构价值判断。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"遵守本轮架构探针约束，没有联动改 recipe。选择 lowrank_residual 而非继续重复被拒的 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual probe，可以更直接测试 soft codebook 分支本身的必要性；风险是该 family 可能在 K=128 下 FVU 明显偏弱，但这正是探针需要确认的信号。","summary":"做一个新的 matched architecture probe：仅把 architecture 改为 lowrank_residual，其余保持 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 不变，测量去掉 soft codebook 与第二阶段 refinement 后，这个更低成本父节点是否还值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0246.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"K","value":"96"}],"expected_win":"lower_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"frontier_mapping","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；低秩 factorized scorer 只改变单样本在线侧的打分与选择链路，不改变 decoder 端的单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿导出形式，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 reference_round=r230 只改一个 env 参数 `K=96`，保持 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`、`OPTIMIZER=signum`、`LR=0.003` 及其余配置不变，测试真正低秩 scorer 配方在约 0.19x 总成本位置是否能补出一枚新的超低开销 Pareto 点，并回答 r244 的负信号究竟来自 family 本身，还是来自默认 hidden-dim 已退化为接近 plain topk 成本的错误成本槽位。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `factorized_topk@K96,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 在显著低于当前左端 0.28x 成本的同时，把 FVU 压到接近或优于 `topk@K32` 的 0.3199，且运行时长没有明显恶化，则下一轮继续相对本轮单变量下探 `K=64`，绘制真正 factorized scorer 左侧前沿。","如果该点质量明显差于 `topk@K32` 且没有明显运行优势，则关闭 `factorized_topk` 的低 hidden-dim 低 K 主线，不再把它作为 `<0.5x` 区域优先方向。","如果该点质量尚可但时长或吞吐异常恶化，则把问题归因为实现/运行时负担，而不是简单归因为结构优劣，并停止继续在这条线加密。"],"notes_to_memory":["r244 的 `factorized_topk@K96` 负信号并不能直接判死真正的低秩 scorer，因为该轮未继承 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96`，默认 hidden-dim 在 EF=1,K=96 下会回到 384，encoder 成本槽位已接近 plain topk。","r242-r245 说明在 0.34x 附近继续比较 plain topk / jumprelu / factorized_topk 默认 hidden / group_topk 的边际信息已快速下降；更高价值的问题是 factorized scorer 能否把 frontier 向 0.2x 左侧推进。","本轮必须同时比较 `val_fvu`、`tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens`；若只是更便宜但训练明显更慢，应明确记为负面系统信号。"],"reference_round":230,"self_review":"这轮严格遵守单变量原则：相对有效 reference r230 只改 `K`，不联动 architecture、EF、optimizer、LR 或 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`。选择这一步而不是继续在 r242 的 0.34x 槽位开新 family，是因为连续三轮失败已经说明当前问题不在 support-rule 小改，而在于还没有真正测试过‘低 hidden-dim factorized scorer + 中低 K’这个更贴合低开销目标的配方。","summary":"回到 r230 的真正低秩 factorized scorer 锚点，仅把 `K` 从 256 降到 96，优先验证 `factorized_topk@FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 能否在约 0.19x 总成本处补出新的左侧 Pareto 点；这比继续在 0.34x 槽位重复 family 对照更符合当前低开销探索目标。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0104.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0052.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 51 completed the downward K mapping: the strengthened `gated` recipe (`signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`) now owns every allowed frontier point from `K=128` down to `K=4`. With the K axis fully mapped, the next single question is whether the most deployment-stressed point is slightly overdriven: if we keep the same `gated@4` recipe fixed and lower only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, does the ultra-low-K training curve become smoother and finish lower, or is `2.0e-3` still the right setting even at the minimum support?","summary":"Stay on the active `gated` family and hold the newly established minimum-support point fixed at `K=4` with `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to test whether the current ultra-low-K recipe is mildly overstepping rather than capacity-limited. Judge the run by the full trajectory as well as the endpoint: if the lower LR reduces early noise and yields a better finish than the current `gated@4` result (`0.447286`), then low-K gated wants a different step size than the `K=128` anchor; if the curve slows uniformly or the endpoint worsens, keep `2.0e-3` as the shared mainline LR across the whole K grid.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, respects the fixed `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` rule, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. It also avoids reopening the K axis now that the allowed grid has been completely mapped and instead asks the highest-value remaining recipe question at the most stressed deployment point. The main risk is that the poorer ultra-low-K quality is mostly capacity-driven rather than step-size-driven, but a single LR callback at `K=4` is the cleanest way to distinguish those explanations without introducing another family or coupled change.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"4"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 51 completed the full allowed-K sweep for the improved `gated` recipe: it now holds frontier points at `K=4,8,16,24,32,64,96,128` under `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`.","Round 52 returns from K mapping to recipe refinement and isolates the LR question specifically at `K=4`, where LUTurbo online cost is minimal and training dynamics are most likely to expose over-aggressive step size."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated@4` improves with `LR=1.6e-3`, run at most one nearby LR confirmation on the same `K=4` recipe to localize the low-K optimum.","If `LR=1.6e-3` is worse or only slower, keep `2.0e-3` as the shared mainline LR and consider the remaining low-K gap primarily a capacity issue rather than a tuning issue."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0163.json:1:{"change_type":"architecture","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"probe","hypothesis":"候选 probe family 的最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i alpha_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 是单个静态字典库上的固定向量，alpha_i 是单样本门控后选出的稀疏系数，因此最终表示是单静态向量库上的有限加权和，可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为直接兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 约 1.0x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束，且仍低于当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的约 1.25x。本轮严格保持 K=128、EXPANSION_FACTOR=2、OPTIMIZER=signum、LR=3.0e-3 与主要 recipe 不变，只将 architecture 从 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 改为 gated，回答唯一问题：在当前低 EF 可部署 regime 下，增加简单门控是否足以让单库路线更接近主线质量，还是它仍会明显落后于带 trunk、soft-codebook 和 staged refinement 的主线结构。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 gated 明显落后于当前主线，则说明简单门控单库路线在当前 regime 下不值得继续，下一轮回到主线。","若 gated 与当前主线差距小于预期且运行代价更优，则记录其为低成本直接兼容备选，但下一轮仍按要求回到主线。","若 gated 意外优于当前主线，则说明当前主线 family 的系统级收益需要重新审视，但本轮仅做架构价值判断，不连续展开新 family。"],"notes_to_memory":["gated 满足 LUTurbo 导出契约，兼容性为直接兼容。","本轮严格是 matched architecture probe：EF、K、optimizer、LR 与主要 recipe 全部固定，只改 architecture。","r159-r162 已覆盖 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual、lowrank_residual、factorized_topk、topk；本轮补充 gated 这一剩余可行直接兼容低成本路线。","评估时必须同时检查 FVU、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，避免把质量差异与吞吐波动混淆。"],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"这轮遵守架构探针规则，只改一个主变量 architecture，并保持主线的 K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变。选择 gated 是因为它是当前尚未在这一严格 matched 配方下补齐的可行直接兼容单库对照，能回答简单门控是否足以弥补纯 topk 路线表达不足这一剩余问题。","summary":"插入一个严格匹配的架构探针：将当前主线 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 替换为 gated，其余 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3 全部保持不变，用一轮干净对照判断这种简单门控的直接兼容单库架构是否值得继续。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0018.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"On the current `K=32, EF=12` anchor with `lowrank_two_stage_residual` and `LR=3.2e-3`, increasing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.01` to `0.0625` may further improve feature utilization and push FVU lower if the aux effect is beneficial at this higher-learning-rate regime.","summary":"Continue the isolated aux sweep on the current best anchor by holding architecture, K, expansion factor, optimizer, and LR fixed while changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.0625`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the controller's exploitation guidance and changes exactly one parameter from the latest successful run. It also directly tests the next suggested aux point after the small nonzero aux setting was accepted.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0625"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 18 continues exploitation on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` high-quality anchor by increasing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.01` to `0.0625` at `K=32, EF=12, LR=3.2e-3`.","This maps whether the apparent aux benefit at the current anchor strengthens with a larger coefficient or whether the best point is near a small nonzero aux setting."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` improves again, keep the stronger aux-enabled anchor and then test whether the same setting transfers to a smaller-K frontier point.","If it is worse than `0.01`, treat the aux optimum as small and revert to the better of `0.0` and `0.01` for future anchor tuning.","If the result is close but noisy, prioritize a confirming rerun of the better aux setting before moving to another variable."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0111.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0080.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128 anchor now looks stable across two consecutive runs, so the next single question is whether the current `LR=2.0e-3` is still slightly too large for this stronger backbone and leaving late-stage quality on the table. A conservative downward probe to `1.6e-3` cleanly tests whether a smaller step yields a smoother mid/late descent and a better finish, without mixing in optimizer or loss changes.","summary":"Stay on the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline and change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3`, while keeping `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and the baseline aux/runtime settings fixed. Judge the run by the full curve against Rounds 78-79, especially whether the lower LR improves late descent or just slows the entire trajectory; if it regresses or converges too slowly, the next LR probe should return upward rather than continuing downward.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays on the same family, keeps EF pinned to 12, and changes exactly one primary variable: `lr`. The tradeoff is that a lower LR may simply undertrain a recipe that is already stable at `2.0e-3`, but that is the cleanest first LR-localization question after the baseline repeat and is safer than opening the optimizer branch too early.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 80 starts LR localization on the confirmed `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline by probing `LR=1.6e-3` against the stable `2.0e-3` K128/EF12/signum anchor.","Interpretation should prioritize curve shape: if `1.6e-3` is smoother but clearly slower with no late recovery, treat the family as preferring the original or higher LR rather than continuing downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` underperforms or converges too slowly, test only `LR=2.4e-3` next on the same family and anchor recipe.","If `LR=1.6e-3` improves late descent and final FVU, confirm that lower-LR anchor once before touching optimizer.","Do not switch optimizer or move K until the signum LR direction is settled for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at K128."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0132.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。由于 r131 的 optimizer 分支被 policy_reject，先停止继续扫 optimizer；本轮只回答一个问题：在主线 baseline（signum, LR=3.0e-3）上去掉 auxiliary K loss（AUXK_ALPHA=0.0）后，是否能改善训练末段收敛形状并在不增加选择成本、不过度拖慢 tokens_per_sec/总耗时的前提下降低 FVU。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 曲线更平滑且终点更好，可继续围绕 aux loss 强度做单变量细扫。","若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 终点变差或训练早期明显失稳，则说明 auxiliary 信号仍有价值，回到 baseline 后再考虑 preprocess 轴。","若 AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 与 baseline 几乎等价，则结束 loss 轴试探，后续再评估更细的部署成本变量如 TRUNK_RANK 或 NUM_CODES。"],"notes_to_memory":["LUTurbo 导出形式未变，family 仍为扩展兼容；本轮不引入新 family。","EF=2 继续满足 selection_cost 预算；K 保持 128，避免把部署查表成本变化与 loss 轴混杂。","r131 optimizer 分支被 policy_reject，因此本轮转向更保守的 loss 轴单变量试探，而不是继续扩张 optimizer 搜索。"],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：family、EF、K、主优化器和 LR 都固定，只改 AUXK_ALPHA。该提案避开了刚被 policy 拒绝的 optimizer 分支，继续在兼容且成本可行的主线 family 上获取可解释信号；风险是 auxiliary loss 关闭后可能导致早期 support 学习变差，因此必须结合曲线形状与运行代价共同判断。","summary":"在已稳定复现的 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线上做一次 loss 轴最小改动：固定 EF=2、K=128、signum、LR=3.0e-3，仅关闭 auxiliary K loss，判断该辅助项是否在当前低 EF 可行区间内已经成为收敛噪声。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0060.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Round 59 ruled out `factorized_topk` as a strong matched alternative under the current `gated` recipe: at `0.229180` it was clearly too weak, so the next single architecture question should move to a different export-compatible support-formation mechanism rather than another heavier scoring path. `jumprelu` preserves LUTurbo's static-vector finite weighted-sum reconstruction contract while replacing the learned input-conditioned gate with per-latent thresholding, so this round asks one clean yes/no question: under the exact current mainline recipe (`K=128`, `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`), is `jumprelu` competitive enough in full-curve behavior to justify any later follow-up as a potentially cheaper deployment family?","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, `USE_HADAMARD=1`, and the same runtime knobs, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `gated` to `jumprelu`. Judge this probe by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays smooth and remains reasonably close to the `0.142923` `gated` anchor, it is worth keeping in reserve because its thresholded support path may reduce LUTurbo online selection overhead versus a full gating branch; if it is clearly worse across the curve, archive it as a non-promising matched alternative and return to the `gated` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the Round 60 matched-probe rule by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, and the settled mainline recipe fixed. `jumprelu` is a sensible LUTurbo-oriented probe because it preserves the same static library weighted-sum output form while simplifying support shaping relative to `gated`; the main risk is that the matched `gated`-tuned recipe may not be ideal for its threshold dynamics, but that is acceptable for a family-worthiness screen.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"BATCH_SIZE","value":"1"},{"key":"GRAD_ACC_STEPS","value":"8"},{"key":"MICRO_ACC_STEPS","value":"1"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"},{"key":"DEAD_FEATURE_THRESHOLD","value":"10000000"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"},{"key":"COMPILE_MODEL","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 59 showed that matched `factorized_topk` is not promising under the strengthened mainline recipe: its `0.229180` endpoint is far from the `gated@128` anchor, so that family should not be prioritized for LUTurbo-oriented follow-up.","`jumprelu` remains LUTurbo-compatible because the reconstruction is still a finite weighted sum over a static decoder library with fixed `K`; the architectural change is confined to threshold-based support shaping before top-k selection.","Round 60 should judge `jumprelu` purely as a family-worthiness probe against the current `gated@128` anchor: if it is clearly worse or unstable, archive it and return to the `gated` mainline next round; if it is competitive, keep exactly one later follow-up slot available."],"next_hypotheses":["If matched `jumprelu` is clearly worse than the strengthened `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round and close this probe.","If matched `jumprelu` is roughly competitive with a healthy curve, still return to the `gated` mainline next round, but preserve one later revisit because its thresholded support path may better align with LUTurbo online-cost goals.","If matched `jumprelu` unexpectedly beats the current `gated` anchor, return to the `gated` mainline next round per policy but schedule exactly one later follow-up for this family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
