research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0047.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After repeated failures from gating, staged residual, batch-budget, and codebook families, the next fundamentally different mechanism is a low-rank feature-mixing encoder without residual trunks: `factorized_topk` at `K=24, EF=12` may improve latent scoring efficiency enough to recover a better mid-K FVU tradeoff than the recent non-frontier architectures.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `factorized_topk` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by continuing the search over qualitatively different built-in families instead of any further scalar sweep.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, K, and EF adjustments because 12 no-improve rounds means minor tuning is exhausted. I also kept the comparison at K=24 for direct frontier relevance while testing a family that is structurally different from the recent low-rank residual, gating, routing, and codebook branches.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"factorized_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 47 continues severe-stagnation recovery with another fundamentally different built-in family after `residual_vq` also failed badly at K=24.","Keep the run architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with all recipe fields pinned explicitly.","`factorized_topk` tests whether a low-rank mixing stage before support selection helps mid-K quality without the heavier residual or discrete machinery used in recent failed branches."],"next_hypotheses":["If `factorized_topk` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to see whether the factorized scoring helps more under tighter sparsity.","If `factorized_topk` clearly loses at K=24, reject this branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `group_topk` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `factorized_topk` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
