research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0084.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_two_stage_residual` has now had its K128 signum recipe mostly clarified, and the operator allows exactly one matched architecture probe. The highest-value single probe is `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual`: it preserves the same low-rank staged static-library decomposition while changing only the support-selection mechanism. If routing cannot beat or closely pressure the current `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor under the exact same `K=128, EF=12, signum, LR=2.0e-3` recipe, then this extra routing complexity is not worth continuing in the current LUTurbo-aligned regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching only `ARCHITECTURE` to `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` while keeping the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the baseline loss/runtime settings unchanged. Judge the probe by the whole curve, not just endpoint FVU: if routing stays smooth and materially challenges the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, it remains worth later reserve consideration; if it is clearly weaker or less stable, close the family-worthiness question and return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the matched-probe rule: one probe only, one primary variable only, and `K`, `OPTIMIZER`, `LR`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` stay fixed. I chose `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` because it is the cleanest structural contrast to the current mainline without abandoning the same low-rank staged export contract. The risk is that routing adds online selection complexity, so even a small FVU gain may not justify follow-up; this round is explicitly a worthiness screen, not a promotion commitment.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.03125"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 84 uses the single allowed matched architecture probe on `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Interpret this as a family-worthiness check only: because routing adds selection complexity, only a clear and stable reconstruction advantage would justify future continuation."],"next_hypotheses":["Return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless, per the operator instruction.","If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` is clearly worse or less stable, keep focus on mainline loss/preprocess clarification rather than reopening routed variants.","If it wins clearly, note it as a reserve candidate but still resume mainline recipe clarification next round before any further architecture churn."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
