research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0128.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"32"}],"expected_win":"lower_selection_cost","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。其中 U(Vx) 可导出为静态 trunk 向量库，{c_m} 为静态 soft-codebook 库，{b_i} 为静态 residual 字典库，因此最终仍是多个静态向量库上的有限加权和，可落到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的‘查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿’推理链路，兼容性为扩展兼容。r127 的 matched probe 说明两阶段 refinement 在 EF=2 下仍有真实 FVU 价值，但其 selection_cost 明显高于单阶段父节点；因此本轮回到主线 family，只改 NUM_CODES=32，测试是否能在保持两阶段结构优势的同时压低 encoder 选择成本，缩小与 lowrank_soft_codebook_residual 的成本差距。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 NUM_CODES=32 仅小幅伤害 FVU 但显著降低 selection_cost，则继续沿 num_codes 轴补一个中间点细化 Pareto。","若 NUM_CODES=32 明显恶化 FVU 且时间收益有限，则恢复默认 code 配方，转向 STAGE1_RATIO 或 preprocess/loss 轴。","若 NUM_CODES=32 维持接近主线 FVU 且训练更快，则把它作为两阶段 family 的低成本变体保留在兼容 frontier 候选中。"],"notes_to_memory":["本轮已从 matched architecture probe 回到主线 family，遵守‘probe 后下一轮回主线’规则。","两阶段 family 的兼容性与导出路径不变：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + residual 字典库。","本轮只改 NUM_CODES，目标不是追更低绝对 FVU，而是测试两阶段主线能否改善 selection_cost/FVU Pareto。","评估时必须同时记录 selection_cost、FVU、总耗时、tokens_per_sec、final_total_tokens，避免把更长训练误判为结构收益。"],"primary_variable":"num_codes","self_review":"本轮严格保持 architecture、K、EF、optimizer、LR 不变，只改一个会直接影响 encoder 成本的主变量，符合主线推进和单变量原则。风险在于 NUM_CODES=32 可能过于激进，但这一步最直接检验两阶段主线是否还有内部降本空间。","summary":"回到 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 主线，固定 K=128、EF=2、signum、LR=3.0e-3，仅下调 NUM_CODES 到 32，测试两阶段结构能否在保留主要 FVU 优势的同时降低选择成本。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0138.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.4e-3"}],"expected_win":"lower_fvu","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j。low-rank trunk 基库 U、soft codebook 库 {c_m}、两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都是静态可导出的固定向量库，因此可导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路；兼容性判断为扩展兼容。该 family 在 EF=2 时 encoder selection_cost 约 1.25x h×n，满足 ≤1.5x 硬约束。r137 的 clean baseline 与 r132/r133/r136 在 start/mid/end FVU 和 final_total_tokens 上完全重合，且 late stage 仍显示在改善，说明当前主线 recipe 已稳定到足以进入单变量 LR 扫描；同时 r137 的总耗时上升主要来自 tokens_per_sec 异常下降而不是训练更长，因此不应把这次变慢误判为结构或配方退化。本轮只回答一个问题：在保持 family、EF、K、optimizer 不变的前提下，将 LR 从 3.0e-3 下调到 2.4e-3，是否能改善末段收敛形状并把 FVU 压到 0.0581 以下，而不引入新的选择成本或部署成本变化。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["若 LR=2.4e-3 带来更低终点 FVU 且曲线末段更平滑，则继续围绕 signum 做更细的低 LR 单变量扫描。","若 LR=2.4e-3 与 baseline 几乎等价但更慢收敛，则说明当前 3.0e-3 已接近最佳，后续再考虑单变量上调到 3.6e-3。","若 LR=2.4e-3 明显变差或更早平台化，则排除“LR 偏大”假设，后续转向优化器轴或更贴近部署成本的参数轴。"],"notes_to_memory":["lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual 的导出形式未变，仍属扩展兼容，可继续作为 LUTurbo 主线 family。","r137 clean baseline 完整复现了近期主线 FVU 曲线，说明近期成本侧小改动没有改变训练动力学。","r137 的耗时恶化主要来自 tokens_per_sec 异常下滑而非 final_total_tokens 增加，因此当前优先继续单变量 LR 扫描，而不是把该慢速样本当作 recipe 负面结论。"],"primary_variable":"lr","self_review":"遵守单变量原则：只改 LR，family、EF、K、optimizer 全部固定在当前主线参考配方。该动作符合推荐顺序，在 clean baseline 之后进入学习率轴；同时不触碰任何会改变 LUTurbo 导出形式、encoder selection_cost 或部署查表成本的参数。风险是 lower LR 可能只会让前中期更慢而不改善终点，因此必须继续同时观察曲线形状、tokens_per_sec、总耗时和 final_total_tokens，而不是只看最后 FVU。","summary":"继续主线 family，不开新架构；clean baseline 已证明当前 recipe 稳定，因此本轮进入单变量 LR 扫描，在 lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual、EF=2、K=128、signum 不变的前提下，只把 LR 下调到 2.4e-3，测试是否能改善末段收敛并取得新的 cost-FVU Pareto 改善。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0182.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"},{"key":"NUM_CODES","value":"128"}],"expected_win":"pareto_improve","experiment_tier":"mainline","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","hypothesis":"Mainline cost-reduction step on `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` with only `NUM_CODES` changed from the implicit default to `128`. Final reconstruction remains `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j`, so this family is still `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the low-rank trunk library, the static codebook library `C`, and the static residual dictionary `B`, then run `trunk lookup + codebook lookup + two sparse residual lookups + weighted sum` online. This round asks one question only: can a smaller coarse codebook preserve most of the EF=2 mainline quality while reducing both encoder selection cost and deployment lookup cost enough to improve the Pareto point. Reducing `NUM_CODES` directly shrinks `code_router`, `codebook_matmul`, and `codebook_deploy`, making it a cleaner first cost knob than changing multiple recipe terms at once.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["If `NUM_CODES=128` holds FVU close to the current mainline while reducing cost, continue along the same axis with a smaller codebook or then test `TRUNK_RANK` as the next single cost knob.","If FVU degrades sharply, revert to the current mainline codebook size and try `TRUNK_RANK` instead as the next mainline cost-reduction variable."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` remains LUTurbo `扩展兼容` under `NUM_CODES=128`; only the size of the static coarse codebook changes, not the export path.","This round isolates the coarse-codebook-size question and should reduce both selection cost and deployment cost simultaneously, unlike `STAGE1_RATIO` which mostly reallocates sparse budget without shrinking static lookup structures.","Review `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU to confirm whether any improvement comes from true efficiency rather than a shorter or cheaper run artifact."],"primary_variable":"num_codes","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: the family and main recipe stay fixed, and only `NUM_CODES` changes. This follows the stated mainline priority order by keeping EF in-budget and then applying a direct cost knob that can improve both selector cost and LUTurbo deployment cost without introducing a new architecture.","summary":"Push the mainline family forward by shrinking the coarse codebook to `NUM_CODES=128` while keeping `K=128`, `EF=2`, `signum`, and `lr=3e-3` fixed. This is a clean Pareto test for whether the current two-stage soft-codebook architecture can trade a smaller static coarse library for lower total LUTurbo cost without giving up too much reconstruction quality.","touched_files":[]}
