research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0185.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"information_gain","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","hypothesis":"最终重构公式保持为 x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_m pi_m c_m + Σ_i alpha_i^(1) b_i + Σ_j alpha_j^(2) b_j；其中 low-rank trunk 库 U、静态 soft-codebook 库 {c_m}、以及两阶段 residual 字典库 {b_i} 都可静态导出，因此可直接映射到 LUTurbo/Lottable 的“查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿”推理链路，兼容性判断为扩展兼容。当前主线在 EF=2 下 encoder selection_cost 仍在 1.5×h×n 硬约束内，且连续 3 轮围绕 `NUM_CODES` 压缩都没有改变曲线终点，说明当前瓶颈更可能在优化动态而不是 coarse codebook 容量。本轮只回答一个问题：把主变量切到 `optimizer`，并使用更保守的 `adam@1.0e-3`，是否能在不改变 family/EF/K 的前提下改善训练曲线形状或终点 FVU，而不是继续在 signum 配方周围得到同样的 plateau。","summary":"停止继续细扫 `NUM_CODES`，回到同一主线 family 的 recipe 轴；固定 `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=128, EF=2`，将主变量切到 `optimizer`，测试 `adam` 配合更保守的 `LR=1.0e-3` 是否能打破当前 signum 主线的收敛平台。","needs_sanity":false,"notes_to_memory":["family 与导出路径不变，`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` 仍是扩展兼容：trunk 库 + soft-codebook 库 + two-stage residual 字典库。","连续 3 轮 `NUM_CODES` 压缩没有改变终点 FVU，说明当前主线更值得优先澄清 optimizer/curve-shape 问题，而不是继续沿 coarse codebook 容量轴下探。","评估本轮必须同时比较 curve_start/mid/end、tokens_per_sec、总耗时与 final_total_tokens，判断收益是否来自更优优化动态，而不是更长训练或运行时波动。"],"next_hypotheses":["若 `adam@1.0e-3` 曲线更平滑且终点优于或接近 signum 主线，则给 adam 一次同轴 LR callback，例如 `1.5e-3`。","若 `adam@1.0e-3` 明显更差或更慢，则关闭 optimizer 分支，恢复 signum 主线，并回到 `TRUNK_RANK` 或 `NUM_CODES` 的成本轴。","若终点接近但吞吐明显更差，则将 adam 视为负面系统信号，即使其数值指标不差。"],"primary_variable":"optimizer","self_review":"本轮保持同一 family，不开新架构，并把问题从已经反复无增益的 codebook 容量轴转回 recipe 轴，符合当前“先把同一 family 的训练曲线看清”的要求。虽然 `optimizer` 轴联动了更保守的 `LR=1.0e-3`，但这属于避免用 signum 学习率误判 adam 的必要局部配套；主问题仍然只有一个：当前平台是否主要来自优化器动态。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0091.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`whitened_lowrank_residual` failed catastrophically at the matched K128 anchor, so the next matched architecture probe should avoid more whitening-style conditioning and instead test a different single-stage low-rank selector family. The most informative remaining probe is `lowrank_factorized_residual`: it preserves the low-rank trunk and static-library weighted-sum export path, but replaces the plain residual scorer with a factorized scorer. This answers one clean question: can a more structured single-stage selector recover enough of the two-stage mainline's quality to be worth continuing, or is the second residual stage itself the essential ingredient. If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is still clearly weaker under the exact matched `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe, then the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants are likely not worth further follow-up in the current regime.","summary":"Run one matched architecture probe by switching `ARCHITECTURE` to `lowrank_factorized_residual` while keeping `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"explore_unknown","family_name":"lowrank_factorized_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the round policy by changing exactly one primary variable, `architecture`, while keeping the mainline `K=128`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` recipe fixed. I am explicitly avoiding `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` because with the current batch-size-1 regime it collapses to ordinary top-k behavior and would not be an informative matched probe. The main risk is that `lowrank_factorized_residual` may add selector complexity without helping quality or LUTurbo online cost, so this should be judged strictly as a yes/no family-worthiness test before returning to the mainline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_factorized_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"2.0e-3"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 91 spends the single allowed matched architecture probe on `lowrank_factorized_residual` against the exact `lowrank_two_stage_residual` K128/EF12/signum/LR=2.0e-3 anchor.","Avoid `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` in this batch-size-1 regime because its adaptive budget path degenerates to ordinary top-k and is not a meaningful architecture probe.","Judge this run strictly as a family-worthiness test for a structured single-stage low-rank selector; return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round regardless of outcome."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is clearly weaker than the matched `lowrank_two_stage_residual` anchor, treat the remaining single-stage low-rank selector variants as low priority and resume mainline tuning next round.","If `lowrank_factorized_residual` is unexpectedly competitive at matched K128, record it as a structured single-stage comparison point but still return to the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` mainline next round per probe policy."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0058.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0237.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM","value":"384"}],"expected_win":"better_fvu_within_low_cost_region","experiment_tier":"full","family_name":"factorized_topk","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"候选 family: factorized_topk。最终重构公式为 x_hat = Σ_i α_i b_i，其中 {b_i} 来自单个静态向量库；低秩 factorized scorer 只改变在线侧的支持打分链路，不改变 decoder 端的静态单库查表 + 加权求和 + 选择性补偿导出形式，因此可直接导出到 LUTurbo/Lottable 推理链路，兼容性判断为直接兼容。相对 reference_round=r230 只改一个 env 参数 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=384`，保持 `ARCHITECTURE=factorized_topk`、`EXPANSION_FACTOR=1`、`K=256`、`OPTIMIZER=signum`、`LR=0.003`、`AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125` 及其余配置不变，测试把极度压缩的 scorer 容量从 96 提升到仍显著低于全宽的 384 后，是否能在约 0.44x 总成本下显著改善 FVU，从而为 `<0.5x` 区域补出比当前 `topk@0.44x` 更有竞争力的低成本点。选择这一步而不是继续沿 `topk@K248` 的 LR 线或回到 `jumprelu/codebook_topk`，是因为 r236 已明确否定保守 LR 微调，r234/r235 则分别给出异常时长和明显劣质信号；而当前策略又明确鼓励继续探索 factorized scorer 这类天然低 encoder 成本方向。","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["如果 `factorized_topk@EF1,K256,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=384` 在约 0.44x 成本处把 FVU 明显压到优于 `topk@0.44x` 的 0.1635，且 `tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens` 没有明显恶化，则相对本轮继续做一次严格 param_only clean repeat，确认这条低秩 scorer 线是否值得重新进入 `<0.5x` 主前沿。","如果 FVU 仍明显差于同成本 topk，则关闭 `factorized_topk` 的 FHD 扩容线，结论回到该 family 在当前低 EF regime 下仍不具备主线价值。","如果质量改善明显但训练显著更慢，则将其记为解释性对照而非前沿点，并优先比较其系统代价是否真的值得换取这部分 FVU。"],"notes_to_memory":["r236 已确认 `topk@K248` 的 LR 下探不是正收益：`LR=0.0027` 比 `0.003` 略差，且没有运行时优势，应关闭这条 recipe 微调线。","本地 `selection_cost_estimate()` 显示 `factorized_topk@EF1,K256,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=384` 的 combined_ratio 约为 0.44x，仍稳在当前 `<0.5x` 主战区；相较 r230 的 `FHD=96`（约 0.30x），这是一次用更多 scorer 容量换取质量、但仍不回到 full-width topk 的干净 probe。","当前低成本区最近几条新线里，`jumprelu` 暴露出异常总时长，`codebook_topk` 暴露出明显劣质，`topk` 的 recipe 微调也没有收益；继续验证 factorized scorer 的容量上限是更有信息量的下一步。","评估本轮必须同时比较 `val_fvu`、`tokens_per_sec`、`duration_sec`、`final_total_tokens`；若只是小幅质量改善但运行更慢，应直接视为负面系统信号。"],"reference_round":230,"self_review":"该提案严格遵守单变量原则：相对 r230 只改 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM`，不联动 architecture、K、EF、LR、optimizer 或其他参数。主要风险是即便把 hidden 扩到 384，factorized scorer 仍可能因 `K=256,EF=1` 下的支持质量不足而明显落后于同成本 topk；但这正是当前策略明确鼓励、且仍未被干净回答的低成本结构问题。","summary":"相对 r230 的 `factorized_topk@EF1,K256,FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=96` 做一次严格 param_only scorer 扩容 probe，仅设置 `FACTORIZED_HIDDEN_DIM=384`，验证更宽但仍低秩的 selector 能否在约 0.44x 总成本处补出新的 `<0.5x` Pareto 候选。","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0163.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/logs/agent_action_0179.json:1:{"change_type":"param_only","command":"run","env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"2"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.0e-3"}],"expected_win":"explore_unknown","experiment_tier":"proxy","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","hypothesis":"Matched architecture probe on `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` under the unchanged mainline recipe (`K=128, EF=2, signum, lr=3.0e-3`). Final reconstruction is `x_hat = U(Vx) + Σ_i alpha_i b_i`, where `U(Vx)` is a static low-rank trunk and the JumpReLU selector only changes which residual dictionary atoms `b_i` are activated and their coefficients. This is `扩展兼容`: LUTurbo/Lottable can export the trunk factors and residual dictionary as static vector libraries, then execute `trunk lookup + thresholded sparse selection + weighted lookup-sum` online. The probe asks one question only: in the low-EF feasible regime, does learned thresholding provide a better architecture tradeoff than the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline, or should this family be ruled out. Encoder selection cost should stay in the feasible band at `EF=2`, so this should produce a real signal instead of a policy reject.","needs_sanity":false,"next_hypotheses":["Return to the mainline `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` next round and tune exactly one cost knob such as `TRUNK_RANK`, `NUM_CODES`, or `STAGE1_RATIO`.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` underperforms the mainline on FVU or shows materially worse `tokens_per_sec`/runtime without compensating benefit, mark the family as not worth continuing in the low-cost regime."],"notes_to_memory":["`lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is LUTurbo `扩展兼容`: decode remains a finite weighted sum over a static low-rank trunk plus a static residual dictionary; JumpReLU only changes selector-side activation sparsity.","This matched probe stays inside the likely feasible encoder-cost regime and is more informative than another routed/bucketed-style over-budget probe.","When scoring the run, inspect `tokens_per_sec`, wall-clock time, and `final_total_tokens` together with FVU; a tiny quality gain with slower training is a negative signal."],"primary_variable":"architecture","self_review":"Single-variable discipline is preserved: only `ARCHITECTURE` changes while `K`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR`, `OPTIMIZER`, and `LR` remain fixed to the mainline recipe. This probe avoids another likely budget rejection and tests a remaining compatible architecture that can still deliver a clean go/no-go answer for the low-EF frontier.","summary":"Probe `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` as the one matched architecture change. It is LUTurbo-exportable (`扩展兼容`) through a static low-rank trunk plus static residual dictionary, and it should give a real low-cost signal on whether learned thresholding is worth continuing versus the current soft-codebook two-stage mainline.","touched_files":[]}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0046.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After hard failures from branch-mixing, thresholded sparsity, staged residual coding, and batch-level budget allocation, a discrete coarse-code baseline is the next fundamentally different mechanism worth testing: `residual_vq` at `K=24, EF=12` may recover a better mid-K tradeoff by handling shared structure with a learned codebook before sparse residual correction.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `residual_vq` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This matches the severe-stagnation policy by continuing the search over genuinely different built-in families rather than any further scalar tweak.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"residual_vq","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, K, and EF sweeps because 11 no-improve rounds means minor tuning is exhausted. I also kept K fixed at 24 for a clean read against the current frontier slot while moving to a substantially different discrete-reconstruction family.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"residual_vq"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 46 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a codebook-based family after `multi_branch_gated`, `jumprelu`, `two_stage_residual`, and `batch_topk` all failed badly at K=24.","Keep the run architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with every recipe field pinned explicitly.","`residual_vq` tests a qualitatively different coarse-plus-residual mechanism than the recent continuous sparse-coding families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `residual_vq` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test `two_code_residual_vq` at the same K to see whether a deeper discrete coarse stage helps.","If `residual_vq` clearly loses at K=24, reject this codebook branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `factorized_topk` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `residual_vq` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0073.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0131.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Now that bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual has replaced the old high-K anchor at EF=16, the highest-value next test is whether an optimizer change can further improve a smaller-K frontier point without changing architecture or capacity; specifically, Adam on the strong K=32 bucketed backbone may reduce FVU enough to tighten the low-cost Pareto region.","summary":"Run a parameter-only optimizer ablation on the current K=32 bucketed backbone: keep architecture, K, EF, and LR fixed, and swap `signum` for `adam` to test whether optimizer choice improves the low-K frontier under the new EF=16 regime.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline_optimizer_probe","self_review":"This follows the operator priority shift by probing optimizer rather than inventing a new architecture, and it keeps attribution clean by changing only the optimizer on an existing frontier model. Keeping LR fixed at 3.2e-3 makes the result easier to interpret, though it may understate Adam's ceiling if it needs a different tuned LR.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 131 should pivot from K-axis mapping to the operator-requested optimizer dimension now that bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual owns the EF=16 anchor and mid-K lane.","Probe optimizer on K=32 first because improving a smaller-K frontier point is more valuable than chasing an already-strong K=128 anchor, and K=32 is the cheapest currently exposed bucketed frontier slot."],"next_hypotheses":["If Adam improves K=32 materially, propagate the same optimizer test to K=64 on the bucketed family to see whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K frontier.","If Adam is neutral or worse at K=32 with fixed LR, keep signum as the bucketed default and pivot next to a preprocessing or loss-function ablation on the same K=32 backbone.","If Adam destabilizes training, avoid coupled LR retuning immediately and instead test a different optimizer that is more likely to behave well under the existing 3.2e-3 recipe."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0003.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Keeping `lowrank_two_stage_residual` fixed and dropping only `K` from 24 to 16 will test whether this family can extend the Pareto frontier to a smaller-support point without unacceptable FVU degradation.","summary":"Run a parameter-only follow-up on `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=16`, with the rest of the recipe pinned to the current low-K baseline (`EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This directly repairs the prior policy-rejected round by isolating `K` as the sole changed variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the cleanest next probe: it targets the current frontier objective, changes one primary variable, and avoids recipe drift by explicitly pinning the baseline fields.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 4 should be a pure K-isolation run on `lowrank_two_stage_residual`, fixing the prior variable-isolation failure by explicitly pinning architecture, EF, optimizer, LR, and AUXK_ALPHA.","For low-K frontier mapping, treat `K=16` as the next decision point before considering more structural changes."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=16` stays competitive, continue to `K=8` on the same family to map the low-K tail.","If `K=16` degrades too much, keep `K` in the 16-24 band and test a routed variant for better support allocation.","If `K=16` is close but noisy, keep the family fixed and tune stage allocation instead of changing the broader recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0014.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0161.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `lowrank_residual` also failed at `K=24, EF=16`, the severe-stagnation policy still calls for another fundamentally different existing architecture rather than more recipe changes. `lowrank_grouped_residual` is the next informative candidate because it changes support allocation through grouped local competition instead of global residual selection, two-stage composition, codebooks, routing, or gating, and its only prior probe was at `K=16`, so `K=24` is the right slot to test whether grouping opens a non-dominated small-K tradeoff.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_grouped_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed at the current signum baseline. This continues severe-stagnation recovery with a materially different existing family, targets the still-valuable `K=24` frontier slot, and avoids returning to minor optimizer or preprocessing tweaks that have repeatedly failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean single-variable architecture probe and better matches the current policy than another recipe retune. The main risk is that grouped competition may still be too weak in the present EF=16 regime, but it remains structurally distinct from the recent sequence of two-stage, plain residual, multi-branch, gating, VQ, and soft-codebook failures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 161 continues severe-stagnation architecture search after plain low-rank residual coding also failed to improve the `K=24, EF=16` lane.","Hypothesis: `lowrank_grouped_residual` is the next materially different existing family because grouped local competition may allocate limited support better at small K than the recently exhausted global residual, two-stage, soft-codebook, VQ, and gating-style variants."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to test whether grouping helps further down the frontier.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed backbone, test another fundamentally different existing family at `K=24` rather than returning to scalar recipe tweaks.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, deprioritize grouped low-rank residual coding in the current EF=16 regime and continue severe-stagnation search with the next distinct architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0020.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Now that `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` is integrated, an architecture-only run at `K=16, EF=12` can test whether router-guided support selection improves the mid-low-K frontier over the current `lowrank_two_stage_residual` point (`FVU=0.10792168974876404`) without changing optimization or width.","summary":"Round 19 was rejected on isolation grounds before producing a training result, so the clean follow-up is to execute the already-integrated family as a pure architecture comparison. Run `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=16, EF=12` with the established low-K signum recipe and no code changes this round.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"incubating","self_review":"This fixes the previous policy issue by removing code edits from the round and keeping the experiment to a single primary variable: architecture. The main risk is that the routed variant may need router-strength calibration, but the first priority is obtaining a valid comparable datapoint at the target frontier slot.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 19 was policy-rejected before execution because code-edit introduction and architecture change were coupled; treat the family as already integrated and schedule a pure architecture-only run next.","Use the exact low-K baseline recipe when evaluating `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` so the comparison against the current `K=16, EF=12` frontier point is clean."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` wins at `K=16`, run the same family at `K=24, EF=12` to test transfer along the adjacent frontier slot.","If it is close but worse than baseline, keep the family alive and test a smaller routing perturbation in a later code round.","If it clearly loses at `K=16`, return to `lowrank_two_stage_residual` and resume smaller-K frontier work there."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0153.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After the plain non-bucketed two-stage soft-codebook family also lost at `K=24`, the next severe-stagnation move should be another fundamentally different existing architecture rather than more recipe tuning. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest remaining structurally distinct soft-codebook variant for this slot because grouped competition changes capacity allocation more materially than scalar hyperparameters and may produce a better small-K Pareto tradeoff under the fixed EF=16 recipe.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed at the current stable recipe. This follows policy guidance to stop minor tweaks after prolonged stagnation, keeps the probe on a valuable smaller-K slot, and tests whether grouped selection can outperform both the exhausted bucketed backbone and the weaker plain two-stage variant in the current EF=16 lane.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean single-variable architecture test using an already registered family. The main risk is that grouped competition may again be too restrictive, but that is still a more policy-consistent next action than continuing optimizer or preprocessing tweaks after they both failed. `K=24` remains the highest-value unclaimed smaller-K slot where a non-dominated tradeoff would still matter even without beating the `K=32` anchor on absolute FVU.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 153 continues severe-stagnation recovery by trying another fundamentally different existing architecture at `K=24, EF=16` after plain `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` also failed to open a new frontier point.","`lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is selected because grouping changes support allocation more materially than recent scalar recipe tweaks while staying within the existing registered family set.","Keep the recipe pinned to signum + `LR=3.2e-3` + no Hadamard so attribution stays on the grouped architecture rather than optimizer or preprocessing drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to map whether grouping improves the low-K tradeoff curve further down the frontier.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed backbone, test another structurally distinct existing family such as `lowrank_residual_vq` or `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` at `K=24` rather than returning to scalar tuning.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, treat grouped soft-codebook routing as noncompetitive in the current EF=16 small-K lane and move to the next fundamentally different existing architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
