research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0053.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`bucketed_lowrank_residual` came closer than the recent discrete and grouped branches but still lost at `K=24`, so the next severe-stagnation move should test a fundamentally different non-lowrank family rather than another refinement of the low-rank lane. `gated` at `K=24, EF=12` may improve mid-K support quality by learning soft feature admission before hard selection, potentially recovering a non-dominated tradeoff without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `gated` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows severe-stagnation policy by making a clean architecture jump away from the recent low-rank and discrete branches while keeping the experiment anchored on the frontier-relevant mid-K slot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"gated","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided another low-rank variant because round 52 already showed that structured low-rank changes are not enough to beat the current `K=24` frontier point. I also avoided code repair or scalar sweeps because policy requires a fundamentally different architecture-only move after 17 no-improve rounds.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"gated"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 53 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a pure `gated` architecture test after `bucketed_lowrank_residual` came closer than recent branches but still lost at K=24.","Keep the run pinned at `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` so architecture is the only primary variable.","`gated` tests whether a simpler non-lowrank learned admission mechanism works better in the mid-K regime than the recent low-rank, grouped, and discrete branches."],"next_hypotheses":["If `gated` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test it at K=16 to see whether gating helps more under tighter sparsity.","If `gated` clearly loses at K=24, retire this branch and move to another fundamentally different built-in family rather than any scalar sweep.","If `gated` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
