research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent failures suggest the extra low-rank/gating structure may be hurting rather than helping, so a simpler coarse-to-fine residual stack may recover mid-K quality: `two_stage_residual` at `K=24, EF=12` could outperform the recent non-lowrank misses and potentially challenge the current `K=24` frontier point without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `two_stage_residual` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by trying another fundamentally different built-in architecture and avoids any further minor scalar sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, and expansion-factor tweaks because nine no-improve rounds means scalar tuning is exhausted. I also moved away from low-rank, whitening, and gating after repeated clear losses, while keeping K fixed at a frontier-relevant value for a clean architecture-only read.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 44 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a simpler non-lowrank residual architecture after `multi_branch_gated` and `jumprelu` both failed badly at K=24.","Keep the test architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with all recipe fields explicitly pinned.","`two_stage_residual` checks whether hierarchical residual coding helps mid-K without the added complexity of low-rank trunks or learned gating."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to see whether staged residual coding helps more under tighter budgets.","If `two_stage_residual` clearly loses at K=24, reject this branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `batch_topk` or `residual_vq` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `two_stage_residual` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain is localized or extends across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0140.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After bucketed, plain two-stage, routed, and gated soft-codebook backbones all failed to beat the current `K=32, EF=16` bucketed point, the next severe-stagnation move should test a genuinely different existing architecture rather than return to scalar tweaks. `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest remaining soft-codebook-adjacent candidate by prior quality and may transfer better to `EF=16` at `K=32` by allocating capacity asymmetrically across stages instead of via buckets, routing, or gating.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=32, EF=16` with `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This follows the severe-stagnation guidance to stop minor tweaks and test a fundamentally different existing architecture on the most valuable exposed small-K frontier slot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a policy-clean architecture-only move on the same high-value `K=32` target under fixed `EF=16`. I chose the asymmetric two-stage variant because it offers a real structural departure from the already-failed bucketed, routed, plain, and gated branches while still having a stronger prior than older discarded non-soft-codebook families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 140 continues severe-stagnation recovery by testing `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32, EF=16` after the bucketed, plain two-stage, routed, and gated soft-codebook variants all failed to improve the current frontier point.","Keep optimizer, LR, and aux fixed so the result isolates architecture alone on the highest-value exposed small-K slot.","This run asks whether asymmetric stage allocation is a better inductive bias than bucketing, routing, or gating under the current EF=16 regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` improves the `K=32, EF=16` point, propagate it to `K=64` before returning to any recipe tuning.","If it is close but slightly worse at `K=32`, consider one preprocessing or optimizer probe on this asymmetric backbone rather than discarding it immediately.","If it clearly loses at `K=32`, treat the remaining soft-codebook architecture space as close to exhausted under the current recipe and pivot to under-explored runtime axes on the existing bucketed backbone."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0132.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0120.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At K=16, a group-local competition mechanism on top of soft codebook residualization may outperform the current frontier by enforcing more diverse support usage than the recent gated, bucketed, or whitened variants. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is already integrated and showed some signal at neighboring K values, so it is the cleanest fundamentally different K=16 probe under severe stagnation.","summary":"Severe stagnation has reached 21 non-improving rounds, so this round should not do another tweak or another fresh code-edit branch. The most defensible next move is a fundamentally different existing architecture at the valuable smaller-K slot: test `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16` with the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK recipe to see whether grouped competition helps where recent gating, bucketing, and whitening variants did not.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"incubating","self_review":"This keeps one hypothesis and uses an already integrated family, which is appropriate after several unsuccessful new-family branches. The main risk is that grouping may remain too restrictive, but it is still a genuinely different support-allocation mechanism and the K=16 slot is the highest-value place to test it now.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 120 should satisfy severe-stagnation policy with a fundamentally different existing architecture rather than another minor tweak or another new code-edit family.","`lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is already integrated and has been tested at K=8 and K=24, so K=16 is the highest-value missing smaller-K slot for this family under the fixed recipe.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture alone at K=16."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at K=16, follow with K=24 confirmation only if needed to map whether the grouped benefit persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at K=16, continue severe-stagnation search with another fundamentally different existing family rather than more soft-codebook two-stage variants.","If it is close but noisy at K=16, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0082.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0054.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After low-rank, discrete, bucketed, and gated branches all failed to beat the `K=24` frontier point, the next severe-stagnation move should test a fundamentally different routing mechanism without the low-rank trunk or codebook machinery. `routed` at `K=24, EF=12` may improve support allocation in the mid-K regime by learning input-dependent feature preference before hard top-k selection, potentially recovering a better FVU/K tradeoff than the recent losing families.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `routed` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows severe-stagnation policy by making another architecture-only jump rather than any scalar sweep or code repair, while staying anchored on the frontier-relevant mid-K slot.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided another low-rank or discrete variant because those branches have already been sampled repeatedly and are not improving the frontier. I also avoided code edits because policy has been rejecting coupled repair rounds; this keeps the experiment architecture-only with all recipe fields pinned.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 54 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a pure `routed` architecture test after `gated` also failed badly at K=24.","Keep the run pinned at `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` so architecture is the only primary variable.","`routed` tests whether simple input-dependent support routing, without low-rank trunks or discrete codebooks, works better in the mid-K regime than the recent losing branches."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test it at K=16 to see whether routing helps more under tighter sparsity.","If `routed` clearly loses at K=24, retire this branch and move to another fundamentally different built-in family rather than any scalar sweep.","If `routed` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0142.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0087.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Plain gating clearly loses at `K=8`, but the low-K bottleneck may still be the hardness of support selection rather than the low-rank residual backbone itself. The next single-variable probe should test whether the smoother `JumpReLU` selector helps the low-rank residual family recover quality at the allowed low-K anchor `K=8`.","summary":"Run one parameter-only architecture comparison at `K=8` with `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. Success criterion: beat the current `K=8` frontier anchor FVU (`0.12280897796154022`) and show that smoothing support selection improves low-K reconstruction where hard top-k gating failed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This stays within the allowed K set, avoids repeating the failed gating hypothesis, and tests a genuinely different existing mechanism at the most decision-relevant low-K anchor. It is a better next move than another rerun because the `lowrank_gated_residual` miss at `K=8` was clear rather than borderline.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 87 should pivot from plain gating to a smoother support-selection mechanism at the same allowed low-K anchor after `lowrank_gated_residual` clearly lost at `K=8` (`0.12682607769966125`) versus the incumbent `K=8` frontier (`0.12280897796154022`).","New hypothesis: `JumpReLU` may help specifically in the tight-budget `K=8` regime by smoothing latent selection without requiring a new family integration step, while keeping the low-rank residual backbone and the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK_ALPHA=0.0 recipe constant.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` also loses clearly at `K=8`, that is evidence that support-selection tweaks alone are unlikely to displace the soft-codebook anchor in the allowed low-K lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` wins at `K=8`, test the same family at `K=16` to see whether the gain extends beyond the lowest allowed anchor.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=8`, do one confirmatory rerun before retiring the idea.","If it clearly loses at `K=8`, shift away from selector-only changes and toward a more structural existing mechanism or a carefully differentiated new family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0060_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"A conditional mixture of residual dictionaries may recover the mid-K lane where fixed residual mechanisms have stalled: `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` keeps the strong low-rank trunk, then lets a learned sample-level router mix several residual scoring branches before final top-k selection, potentially matching heterogeneous residual regimes better than a single encoder.","summary":"Repaired `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` so the original round-60 experiment can run under DDP. The crash was caused by inherited `encoder.weight` and `encoder.bias` from `LowRankResidualSparseCoder` being unused in the new family, which triggered the prior-iteration reduction error. Patched `_mixed_acts()` so the inherited residual encoder is an always-on anchor branch alongside the routed branches, then re-ran the concrete factory-dispatch checks. Validation passed: all parameters now receive gradients, and the exact smoke target `architecture=lowrank_multi_branch_residual, K=24, EF=12` instantiates, runs forward, and backward successfully.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_multi_branch_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a repair only; the architecture name, hypothesis, and env overrides are unchanged. The fix addresses the precise DDP-unused-parameter blocker without redesigning the experiment. I also corrected the validation path by smoke-testing the actual architecture class through `_get_sae_class()` at the exact failing `(architecture, K, EF)` instead of relying on the base `SparseCoder` constructor.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_multi_branch_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair round 60 attempt 1: `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` crashed under DDP because inherited `encoder.weight` and `encoder.bias` were unused in the forward pass.","Patched `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` so the inherited residual encoder participates as an always-on anchor branch in `_mixed_acts()`, eliminating the unused-parameter reduction bug.","Verified on the concrete architecture class via `_get_sae_class('lowrank_multi_branch_residual')` that all parameters now receive gradients.","Exact integration smoke passed for `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` at `K=24, EF=12` with forward/backward on the real architecture class."],"next_hypotheses":["Run the original `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` experiment again at the same pinned `K=24, EF=12, signum, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` recipe now that the DDP blocker is fixed.","If the repaired run is competitive but slightly worse at `K=24`, test `K=16` to see whether conditional branch specialization helps more under tighter sparsity.","If the repaired run still fails, inspect the new failure mode directly rather than changing architecture or hyperparameters."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
