research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0035.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0004.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Keeping `lowrank_two_stage_residual` fixed and dropping only `K` from 16 to 8 will test whether this family can add a further non-dominated low-support point on the Pareto frontier, accepting some FVU increase if the tradeoff remains competitive.","summary":"Continue the same-family low-K sweep with a parameter-only run at `K=8`, while pinning the existing low-K recipe (`ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). The `K=16` result was good enough to justify tracing the tail lower before switching families or introducing routing changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the current frontier logic cleanly: one variable changes, the recipe stays controlled, and the next most informative question is whether the same family still holds up at substantially smaller support.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 4 extends the controlled K sweep for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` from 16 to 8 with all other recipe fields pinned.","The current low-K lane is yielding monotonic frontier points at K=32, 24, and 16, so the most informative next step is to test whether the same family remains Pareto-relevant at K=8 before trying a new architecture."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=8` stays competitive, continue to `K=4` on the same family to finish mapping the low-K tail.","If `K=8` degrades sharply, hold `K` near 16-24 and test a routed variant to improve support allocation.","If `K=8` is borderline but promising, keep the family fixed and adjust stage allocation rather than changing the broader recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0110.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After eleven non-improving rounds, the next worthwhile move is another fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; a plain low-rank gated residual model may outperform the recent codebook, VQ, and adaptive-budget branches at K=24 by using a simpler support-selection mechanism on top of the proven low-rank trunk.","summary":"Severe stagnation remains active, and the most recent fundamentally different branches (`lowrank_residual_vq`, `adaptive_budget_topk`, `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual`) all lost clearly at `K=24`. The next clean test should stay on the valuable smaller-K anchor but switch to another distinct mechanism: run `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=24` with the stable EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe. This isolates architecture alone and checks whether a simpler gated selector can recover the mid-K lane better than the more elaborate recent branches.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than tuning within a losing branch, keeps K in the allowed set, and targets a meaningful frontier slot. The risk is that older-budget evidence for `lowrank_gated_residual` at nearby K was only modest, but it is still a more defensible next mechanism than continuing codebook or adaptive-budget variants after repeated failures.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` also lost clearly at `K=24`, dynamic-budget routing looks unpromising for the current EF=12 mid-K lane.","Round 110 should probe `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe as another fundamentally different support-selection mechanism.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result remains attributable to architecture alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the simpler gated mechanism scales across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another distinct existing family rather than returning to codebook or adaptive-budget tweaks.","If it is close but noisy at `K=24`, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0010.json:27:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0133.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The runtime currently cannot test the operator-requested loss axis because `sparsify/trainer.py` hardcodes `loss = out.fvu + aux`. Add a minimal configurable `loss_fn` to `sparsify/` and test a robust reconstruction objective on the strongest low-K EF=16 backbone: `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at K=32. A Huber-style loss may reduce sensitivity to a small set of hard residual outliers and improve evaluated FVU at the smallest exposed frontier point without changing architecture or capacity.","summary":"Make a scoped code change under `sparsify/` to add a configurable training loss, then run the current K=32 bucketed backbone with `LOSS_FN=huber` as the only scientific variable change.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline_loss_probe","self_review":"This is the cleanest way to satisfy the operator priority shift after Adam and Hadamard both regressed: loss-function exploration is currently impossible without a small runtime edit. The proposed edit is tightly scoped to `sparsify/`, preserves default behavior with `loss_fn=fvu`, and keeps the experiment scientifically single-variable once the knob exists.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"LOSS_FN","value":"huber"},{"key":"HUBER_DELTA","value":"1.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/trainer.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 133 should unlock the operator-requested loss-function axis by adding a minimal configurable `loss_fn` in `sparsify/` while preserving the current default `fvu` path.","Use the K=32 bucketed EF=16 signum backbone as the first loss probe because smaller-K Pareto improvements are more valuable than further perturbing the already-strong K=96/K=128 anchor points.","Keep the implementation minimal: validate `loss_fn` in config, preserve existing behavior for `fvu`, and add a robust `huber` alternative computed in the trainer so the architecture code stays unchanged."],"next_hypotheses":["If Huber training improves K=32 materially, propagate the same loss function to K=64 on the bucketed family to see whether the gain extends across the mid-K frontier.","If Huber is neutral or worse, keep `fvu` as the default and consider a second loss probe such as normalized L1 on the same K=32 bucketed recipe.","If the loss-function code path is unstable or creates invalid comparisons, revert to the default `fvu` path and resume exploration on the remaining supported runtime axes."],"primary_variable":"loss_function"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0109.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The plain `adaptive_budget_topk` failure suggests dynamic support allocation needs a stronger representational backbone, not that the mechanism is useless; adding adaptive-budget selection on top of the proven low-rank residual trunk may produce a better K=24 tradeoff than either plain adaptive-budget or the recent soft-codebook branches.","summary":"Severe stagnation is active and recent fundamentally different probes have still lost, so the next step should be a new architecture rather than another recipe tweak. Add and test `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` under `sparsify/` only: reuse the winning low-rank residual trunk, replace fixed per-sample TopK selection with an adaptive-budget selector, and evaluate it first at the valuable `K=24` anchor with the stable EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe. This is one clean architectural hypothesis: dynamic budget allocation may only become competitive once paired with the stronger low-rank decomposition.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by making a fundamentally different architecture move instead of another scalar adjustment. It is higher risk than reusing an existing family, but the search has already shown that plain dynamic-budget selection and several recent soft-codebook variants are not enough on their own; combining the adaptive selector with the strongest low-rank backbone is the most defensible next unknown to test.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 108 showed plain `adaptive_budget_topk` is a catastrophic miss at `K=24`, so any further dynamic-budget exploration should only continue if paired with a substantially stronger backbone.","Round 109 should test a new family `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` that keeps the proven low-rank residual trunk and changes only the support-allocation mechanism to adaptive budget.","Because this introduces a new architecture string, complete the full registration chain and exact smoke test before training: whitelist, factory dispatch, concrete class, then instantiate/forward/backward with the exact launch string."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_adaptive_budget_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, run the same fixed recipe at `K=16` or `K=32` to map whether the gain is localized or broad across the mid/low-K band.","If it runs cleanly but clearly loses at `K=24`, treat dynamic-budget routing as unpromising even with a strong low-rank backbone and move to a different mechanism entirely.","If the new family fails at sanity or first backward, repair the integration/runtime issue before drawing any scientific conclusion about the architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0069.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` has now taken the frontier at `K=16`, `K=8`, `K=4`, and `K=2`; testing the same fixed recipe at `K=1` determines whether this family can cover the full low-K Pareto frontier and potentially beat the current `K=1` anchor from `lowrank_two_stage_residual`.","summary":"Run one controlled parameter-only experiment at `K=1` with `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed so `K` is the only changed variable.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This remains the strongest single-variable continuation. The family has produced four consecutive frontier wins as K decreased, so the highest-value next question is whether that dominance extends all the way to `K=1` before returning to broader architecture exploration.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"1"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 69 tests whether `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, now on the frontier at `K=16`, `K=8`, `K=4`, and `K=2`, can extend to the extreme endpoint at `K=1` under the same fixed recipe.","Keep architecture and recipe fixed (`EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`) so `K` is the only changing dimension.","Success criterion is beating the current `K=1` frontier anchor (`lowrank_two_stage_residual`, FVU `0.17282412946224213`) and confirming whether this family spans the full low-K frontier."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=1` wins, treat `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` as the dominant low-K family and shift focus back to mid-K/new-family search.","If `K=1` is close but slightly behind, consider one confirmatory rerun before concluding the family bottoms out at `K=2`.","If `K=1` clearly loses, keep `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` as strongest in the `K=2-16` band and resume new-family search for the `K=1` slot."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0145.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` worsened the `K=16` bucketed run, so the next exploitation step should test whether the current low-K bucketed recipe is learning-rate mismatched rather than fundamentally saturated. A lower `LR=4e-4` is the highest-priority single-variable probe because it is explicitly suggested by the latest result and may improve convergence stability at the current practical lower-bound anchor.","summary":"Run a pure learning-rate sweep on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16`, keeping architecture, optimizer, aux loss, preprocessing, and `EF=16` fixed while changing only `LR` from `3.2e-3` to `4e-4`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the exploitation policy after four non-improving rounds, avoids new architectures, and changes exactly one parameter. I chose the `K=16` anchor because it is the most valuable exposed small-K bucketed point after `K=8` failed, and improving it would matter more for the frontier than polishing already-strong high-K anchors.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 145 continues exploitation on the bucketed backbone after the stronger aux-loss probe underperformed, shifting to an LR-only test at the most valuable low-K anchor.","This round isolates whether the `K=16` bucketed recipe is overshooting under `LR=3.2e-3`; `LR=4e-4` is the first lower-LR probe because it is closer to the current working regime than `2e-4` while still being a substantial stability test."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=4e-4` improves `K=16`, propagate that LR to `K=24` to test whether the gain generalizes across the low-K bucketed frontier.","If `LR=4e-4` underperforms but training is smooth, test the remaining lower LR `2e-4` before concluding that this backbone truly prefers the higher step size.","If `LR=4e-4` clearly slows convergence too much, restore `LR=3.2e-3` as the bucketed baseline and shift the next round to a preprocessing or optimizer probe rather than further low-LR descent."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0169.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Under severe stagnation and the explicit operator shift away from architecture churn, the highest-information single-variable probe is preprocessing on the strongest small-K backbone: enabling Hadamard rotation on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32, EF=16` may improve conditioning enough to lower FVU without giving up the strategically valuable small-K point.","summary":"Run a parameter-only preprocessing probe on the current best `K=32, EF=16` family by enabling `USE_HADAMARD=1` while pinning architecture, K, EF, optimizer, LR, and aux loss. This tests a materially under-explored dimension requested by the operator hints, keeps the experiment attributable to one change, and targets the more valuable small-K frontier slot rather than spending another round on high-K refinement or another weak architecture family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This respects the current constraints: one hypothesis, no architecture invention, K chosen from the allowed set, EF pinned to 16, and all core recipe fields explicitly set in env overrides. Main risk: earlier whitening-style variants were unstable, so a pure rotation may still be neutral or harmful, but it is a much cleaner preprocessing probe than reviving another discarded family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"1"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 169 should stop architecture churn and probe preprocessing instead, per operator guidance.","Use the strongest existing small-K backbone (`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32, EF=16`) so the Hadamard result is informative for frontier improvement rather than confounded by a weak family."],"next_hypotheses":["If Hadamard improves the `K=32` point, transfer the same preprocessing change to `K=64` on the same family to test whether the gain persists across the low/mid-K frontier.","If Hadamard is neutral or worse, keep preprocessing off for this backbone and shift the next round to a loss-shaping probe such as Matryoshka training on the same fixed `K=32, EF=16` recipe.","If Hadamard destabilizes training, deprioritize activation rotation in this regime and move to an optimizer-focused probe with an explicitly retuned LR rather than another architecture swap."],"primary_variable":"other_param"}
